{"type":"message","id":"12dfdea9","parentId":"44659494","timestamp":"2026-04-13T07:24:58.342Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The api.log shows that the api_server tried to start on port 3104 but failed with \"address already in use\". Then the classifier.log shows it was previously running on 3104 successfully. But the current process (66439) is listening on port 3105. So there were multiple restarts.\n\nThe log I see in classifier.log is the old one. The current 500 error on port 3105 is happening now. Let me check if the current process has any logs.\n\nWait - the api.log shows the server startup messages are interleaved. The most recent startup says \"starting on port 3104\" but then there's no recent log after that. Let me look at the raw files with timestamps.\n\nActually, looking at the log more carefully - the api.log and classifier.log are getting mixed up. The \"Loaded embedding classifier\" message is from the classifier startup, not the api log. And the \"Started server process [117161]\" is from the api server.\n\n\nThe current 500 error is puzzling since the last successful requests in the logs are from an earlier run. There should be a current api.log that's being written to, but the uvicorn server output might be going elsewhere. Let me check if there's an actual error being returned or if the logs are just not showing the latest requests.\n\nWait - port 3105 is actually handled by pid 66439 (python3.8), not the uvicorn instance. So port 3105 must be a different service entirely, not the scene-classifier. But the scene-classifier should be on 3104 according to the old config. Let me verify what's actually running on each port.\n\nSo the Python scene-classifier v2 on 3105 is returning 500 errors, and the logs I checked earlier don't show any recent activity - they're from an older instance. The current logs must be elsewhere. Let me look at the classifier logs to find recent errors.","thinkingSignature":"0392c7