{"type":"message","id":"6205543f","parentId":"23071c94","timestamp":"2026-04-13T07:25:53.153Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Found it! The scene-classifier v2 has the **same numpy.float32 bug** that was supposedly fixed before. The error is:\n\n```\nValueError: [TypeError(\"'numpy.float32' object is not iterable\"), TypeError('vars() argument must have __dict__ attribute')]\n```\n\nThis is exactly the same error that was mentioned in the ephemeral memory from the previous session:\n> \"3104 classifier 500 错误根因：numpy.float32 无法 JSON 序列化，修复只需类型转换\"\n\nThe workspace skill version (which was supposedly the fixed version) is loaded from:\n`/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/skills/scene-classifier/models/scene_classifier.pkl`\n\n\nBut the v8 version is still broken. Looking at the scene-classifier setup, there seem to be two different installations - one in the workspace skills directory and another in the v8 directory - and the active v8 instance is the one failing. The numpy.float32 serialization issue was already identified and supposedly fixed in the workspace version, yet the v8 logs are still showing the same error. This suggests either the fix wasn't properly applied to the v8 deployment, or there's a separate instance running that's still using the old code.","thinkingSignature":"aaf1d7ea94714dd9ff2a08a74db795fd6fea47622ed33d287a92978a6f48aa8b"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_54l7qgtk9nno_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"numpy\\|float32\\|serialize\\|jsonable\" /home/ai/.openclaw/v8/scene-classifier/src/pipeline/orchestrator.py 2>/dev/null | head -20; echo \"---\"; ls /home/ai/.openclaw/v8/scene-classifier/src/ 2>/dev/null; echo \"---\"; find /home/ai/.openclaw/v8/scene-classifier -name \"*.py\" | head -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":33775,"output":373,"cacheRead":18601,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":52749,"cost":{"input":0.0101325,"output":