{"type":"message","id":"e9d04bf3","parentId":"0a821374","timestamp":"2026-04-13T07:26:18.357Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see - the `process` method returns `classify_result[\"confidence\"]` directly without converting it to a Python float. The `_log` method has the conversion, but the return value also includes `confidence` directly from the classify_result. The issue is that `classifier.predict()` returns numpy types, and the return statement at line 104-111 passes them directly without conversion.\n\nThe fix was supposedly applied in the April 13 session, but let me check the current state of the scene_classifier.py to see if the fix was applied there.","thinkingSignature":"791b7af69df35c304be3a38f6ed7d1e2d215c268567e5acb4e12a83c3705cba3"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_jrywa6k13chw_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"item()\\|float(\\|int(\" /home/ai/.openclaw/v8/scene-classifier/classifier/scene_classifier.py 2>/dev/null | head -20; echo \"---\"; sed -n '60,95p' /home/ai/.openclaw/v8/scene-classifier/classifier/scene_classifier.py 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":36182,"output":217,"cacheRead":18601,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":55000,"cost":{"input":0.010854599999999999,"output":0.0002604,"cacheRead":0.0011160599999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.012231059999999998}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776065170138,"responseId":"062bcd92beeb9ea74066516c43800820"}}
