{"type":"message","id":"551fc0e1","parentId":"37af2a24","timestamp":"2026-04-13T07:34:45.316Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the full picture. Let me plan the concrete actions:\n\n**Memory chain fix:**\nThe session-summary hook is working (it generated the file). The AGENTS.md startup already has step 6. The issue is that the session-summary.md file from the PREVIOUS session (before the current /new) exists, but when the current session started, it seems the summary wasn't injected properly.\n\nLooking at the bootstrap event: `openclaw:bootstrap-context:full` - this is fired AFTER the first reply. But the session-summary.md file exists and is readable. The question is whether the OpenClaw system reads it automatically or not.\n \nI think the real issue is that AGENTS.md step 6 is there but it's not being triggered reliably. I should make the bootstrap-context hook actually load session-summary files directly instead of relying on step 6 to do it. Let me check if there's already a bootstrap hook registered in the system.","thinkingSignature":"8632e98fbf2651d9a699bbe6d473c7670bf74c9eaae26991e7136951fb28e2cc"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_jv5kl0k7sesi_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"=== hooks目录 ===\"; ls ~/.openclaw/hooks/ 2>/dev/null; echo; echo \"=== bootstrap-context ===\"; find ~/.openclaw/hooks -name \"*bootstrap*\" 2>/dev/null; echo; echo \"=== 检查gateway hooks配置 ===\"; cat ~/.openclaw/config.json 2>/dev/null | python3 -m json.tool 2>/dev/null | grep -A20 \"hooks\" | head -30"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":48403,"output":309,"cacheRead":18601,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":67313,"cost":{"input":0.0145209,"output":0.00037079999999999996,"cacheRead":0.0011160599999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.01600776}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776065664708,"responseId":"062bcf8109720a43027a67623986972f"}}
{"type":"message","id":"cfadaaaa","parentId":"551fc0e1","timestamp":"2026-04-13T07:34:45.403Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_jv5kl0k7sesi_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"=== hooks目录 ===\nHOOK.md\nauto-score-classify\ncontext-hook.js\nhandler.js\nhandler.ts\non-command-error.sh\non-message.sh\nself-improvement.js\nsession-summary\n\n=== bootstrap-context ===\n\n=== 检查gateway hooks配置 ==="}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":55,"aggregated":"=== hooks目录 ===\nHOOK.md\nauto-score-classify\ncontext-hook.js\nhandler.js\nhandler.ts\non-command-error.sh\non-message.sh\nself-improvement.js\nsession-summary\n\n=== bootstrap-context ===\n\n=== 检查gateway hooks配置 ===","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/main"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776065685392}}
{"type":"message","id":"ce186816","parentId":"cfadaaaa","timestamp":"2026-04-13T07:34:52.565Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting! There's a `context-hook.js` in the hooks directory. Let me look at that - it might be related to the bootstrap-context. Also there's no `bootstrap-context` directory found, which means the bootstrap-context event might be emitted by the gateway itself (not a custom hook).\n\nLet me look at the context-hook.js - this might be what injects context into sessions.\n\nAlso, I notice the hooks directory has some interesting files:\n- context-hook.js\n- self-improvement.js\n- session-summary (directory)\n- on-message.sh\n- on-command-error.sh\n\nLet me check these.","thinkingSignature":"a970177ce14d20d44551cd99aa3c2964fc016099ebd950afb50a977b2fd2e7e1"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_c5ix40blaula_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/hooks/context-hook.js 2>/dev/null | head -50; echo \"---\"; ls ~/.openclaw/hooks/auto-score-classify/ 2>/dev/null | head -10"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":48777,"output":190,"cacheRead":18601,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":67568,"cost":{"input":0.0146331,"output":0.00022799999999999999,"cacheRead":0.0011160599999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.01597716}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776065685405,"responseId":"062bcf94d72a7a24d0da49b76a09020a"}}
{"type":"message","id":"7c1791a8","parentId":"ce186816","timestamp":"2026-04-13T07:34:52.645Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_c5ix40blaula_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"/**\n * Context Hook for OpenClaw\n * \n * 监听消息事件，自动调用保护层context模块\n * \n * 支持的事件:\n * - message:receive: 用户发送消息\n * - message:send: AI 发送消息\n * - agent:response: Agent 回复\n */\n\nconst handler = async (event) => {\n  try {\n    // 检查是否有全局上下文接口\n    if (!global.openclaw || !global.openclaw.addContextMessage) {\n      // 尝试加载保护层\n      try {\n        const protection = await import(process.env.HOME + '/.openclaw/protection/index.js');\n        await protection.default.init();\n      } catch (e) {\n        console.log('[ContextHook] 保护层未加载，跳过');\n        return;\n      }\n    }\n\n    // 处理用户消息\n    if (event.type === 'message' || event.type === 'message:receive') {\n      const content = event.message?.content || event.content || '';\n      if (content) {\n        global.openclaw?.addContextMessage('user', content, event.taskId);\n        console.log('[ContextHook] 用户消息已记录:', content.slice(0, 30));\n      }\n    }\n\n    // 处理 Agent 回复\n    if (event.type === 'message:send' || event.type === 'agent:response') {\n      const content = event.response?.content || event.content || '';\n      if (content) {\n        global.openclaw?.addContextMessage('assistant', content, event.taskId);\n        console.log('[ContextHook] AI回复已记录:', content.slice(0, 30));\n      }\n    }\n\n  } catch (error) {\n    console.error('[ContextHook] 错误:', error.message);\n  }\n};\n\nmodule.exports = handler;\nmodule.exports.default = handler;---\nHOOK.md\nhandler.js"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":46,"aggregated":"/**\n * Context Hook for OpenClaw\n * \n * 监听消息事件，自动调用保护层context模块\n * \n * 支持的事件:\n * - message:receive: 用户发送消息\n * - message:send: AI 发送消息\n * - agent:response: Agent 回复\n */\n\nconst handler = async (event) => {\n  try {\n    // 检查是否有全局上下文接口\n    if (!global.openclaw || !global.openclaw.addContextMessage) {\n      // 尝试加载保护层\n      try {\n        const protection = await import(process.env.HOME + '/.openclaw/protection/index.js');\n        await protection.default.init();\n      } catch (e) {\n        console.log('[ContextHook] 保护层未加载，跳过');\n        return;\n      }\n    }\n\n    // 处理用户消息\n    if (event.type === 'message' || event.type === 'message:receive') {\n      const content = event.message?.content || event.content || '';\n      if (content) {\n        global.openclaw?.addContextMessage('user', content, event.taskId);\n        console.log('[ContextHook] 用户消息已记录:', content.slice(0, 30));\n      }\n    }\n\n    // 处理 Agent 回复\n    if (event.type === 'message:send' || event.type === 'agent:response') {\n      const content = event.response?.content || event.content || '';\n      if (content) {\n        global.openclaw?.addContextMessage('assistant', content, event.taskId);\n        console.log('[ContextHook] AI回复已记录:', content.slice(0, 30));\n      }\n    }\n\n  } catch (error) {\n    console.error('[ContextHook] 错误:', error.message);\n  }\n};\n\nmodule.exports = handler;\nmodule.exports.default = handler;---\nHOOK.md\nhandler.js","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/main"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776065692633}}
{"type":"message","id":"545a924f","parentId":"7c1791a8","timestamp":"2026-04-13T07:35:14.896Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me understand the full picture:\n\n1. `session-summary` hook - generates session summaries ✅ working\n2. `context-hook.js` - listens to messages, integrates with protection layer\n3. The `bootstrap-context:full` event seems to be emitted by the gateway itself, not a custom hook\n\nThe key insight: **the `bootstrap-context` event is emitted by the gateway**, not by a custom hook file I can edit. This means I can't directly modify when it fires or what it contains (without modifying OpenClaw core).\n\nHowever, I can modify the `session-summary` hook to produce a better output that WILL be picked up by step 6 of AGENTS.md (which already exists but wasn't properly executed).\n \nSo the real problem is that when a new session starts, the bootstrap context fires after the first response rather than before, and it doesn't include the session summary. Step 6 in the startup sequence should theoretically pull in the latest session summary, but something's preventing that from working. Let me trace through what step 6 is actually supposed to do versus what's happening in practice.\n\nThe memory search I ran returned nothing, which suggests it's not finding the relevant files. And the exec command for finding session files came back empty too. So either step 6 isn't being executed at all, or it's failing silently. I need to create a test to confirm whether the memory retrieval is actually working or if there's a deeper issue with how the session summary gets injected into the context.\n\nActually, I'm realizing the bootstrap-context event might be the key here—it fired after my first reply at 07:17:27, but the initial prompt that kicked off this session only contained the system prompt and startup instructions. It didn't include any session history or prior context. So when the bootstrap event fired later, it was too late; the session had already started without that information. The real fix would be ensuring bootstrap fires before the session begins, but that seems to be an OpenClaw core issue rather than something I can address directly.\n\nFor now, I should focus on what I can actually control: making sure step 6 of AGENTS.md is working properly, and fixing the bootstrap timing issue since it's critical for memory chaining. Let me check if there's a gateway configuration that controls when bootstrap events fire, or if I need to work around it another way. Meanwhile, I can verify that the framework components are healthy.","thinkingSignature":"dfb99885bf66a5462f88e46516ce69fad3e7e3e896e8970ad442327f04628e77"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ohvmpq5gnz1k_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"=== scene-classifier 测试 ===\"; curl -s --connect-timeout 3 -X POST http://localhost:3105/classify -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" -d '{\"text\":\"帮我写个Python脚本\"}' 2>/dev/null | python3 -m json.tool 2>/dev/null | head -20; echo; echo \"=== scorer 测试 ===\"; curl -s --connect-timeout 3 -X POST http://localhost:3103/api/score -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" -d '{\"text\":\"帮我写个Python脚本\"}' 2>/dev/null | python3 -m json.tool 2>/dev/null | head -20; echo; echo \"=== bootstrap-context hook ===\"; grep -r \"bootstrap\\|session-start\\|session.end\" ~/.openclaw/hooks/ 2>/dev/null | grep -v \".js.map\" | head -10; echo; echo \"=== gateway配置 ===\"; cat ~/.openclaw/config.json 2>/dev/null | python3 -m json.tool 2>/dev/null | head -50"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":49358,"output":741,"cacheRead":18601,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":68700,"cost":{"input":0.0148074,"output":0.0008891999999999999,"cacheRead":0.0011160599999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.01681266}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776065692646,"responseId":"062bcf9b776588e27cd182a524fb399a"}}
