[\n                \"Bash\",\n                \"Read\",\n                \"Edit\",\n                \"Write\",\n                \"Glob\",\n                \"Grep\",\n                \"WebFetch\",\n                \"WebSearch\",\n                \"Mildred\",\n                \"Task*\"\n            ],\n            \"env\": {\n                \"ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL\": \"https://zhenze-huhehaote.cmecloud.cn/api/coding/v1\",\n                \"ANTHROPIC_AUTH_TOKEN\": \"J99ouXWKXO8Zg5tLqv92YVsPNFhwuZc-z6z2ioeg7VE\",\n                \"ANTHROPIC_MODEL\": \"minimax-m2.5\"\n            }\n        }\n    },\n    \"models\": {\n        \"providers\": {\n            \"ollama\": {\n                \"baseUrl\": \"http://172.23.96.1:11434\",\n                \"models\": [\n                    {\n                        \"id\": \"qwen2.5:14b\",\n                        \"name\": \"\\u672c\\u5730-qwen2.5-14b\"\n                    }\n                ]\n            },","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/main"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776065715080}}
{"type":"message","id":"aedca770","parentId":"1bf58add","timestamp":"2026-04-13T07:35:36.318Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can see:\n\n1. **scene-classifier** (port 3105): ✅ Working - it returned a classification for \"帮我写个Python脚本\" as \"clarify\" with 0.69 confidence\n2. **scorer** (port 3103): ✅ Working - it returned a score of 0\n3. **bootstrap hook** exists as `handler.ts` - it fires on `agent:bootstrap` events\n\nThe key issue is: the session-summary hook says:\n> \"session 结束时（/new 或 /reset）生成结构化摘要，写入 memory/，供下次 bootstrap 读取。依赖 context.previousSessionEntry.sessionFile 读取刚结束的 session 内容。\"\n \nLooking at the session-summary hook's dependency on `context.previousSessionEntry.sessionFile` - when a session ends via /new, the previous session entry should be available for the hook to read from. But the HOOK.md also mentions it fires on `agent:bootstrap` before workspace files are injected, which is a different event timing.\n\nLet me trace the actual sequence: when /new happens, the gateway creates a new session and fires agent:bootstrap, but the old session's context might not be accessible yet since it's still being finalized. The timing between session cleanup and the bootstrap event could be causing the hook to miss the previous session entry.\n\nI should check the OpenClaw docs to understand how hooks are registered and what events they can listen to, since the session-summary hook isn't showing up in the hooks directory listing - it might be registered differently. The `agent:bootstrap` hook fires synchronously and can modify the bootstrap context before the agent initializes, which is exactly what I need. But the session-summary hook also needs to run at the same time to access the previous session's data through `context.previousSessionEntry.sessionFile`. The real problem is that bootstrap was firing after the first reply instead of before the agent started, so the synchronous hook mechanism should solve that timing issue. The session-summary hook only has a handler.js file with no HOOK.md metadata, so it likely relies on a default naming convention to register itself. The key difference seems to be that the bootstrap hook has proper metadata (HOOK.md) with the event type declared, while session-summary might be missing that registration, which could explain why it's not firing at the right time.\n\nRather than continuing to debug the hook registration, I should focus on what's actually fixable: making sure step 6 of AGENTS.md executes reliably to read session-summary files, and modifying the bootstrap hook to directly include session-summary content in the context it injects.","thinkingSignature":"119cf9232b3053b062973d7db35b8d85e2133f23aaf965463e9e1926154507fa"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_phhjjazyumqp_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/ai/.openclaw/hooks/handler.ts"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":51023,"output":568,"cacheRead":18601,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":70192,"cost":{"input":0.0153069,"output":0.0006816,"cacheRead":0.0011160599999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.017104559999999998}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776065715091,"responseId":"062bcfb2acc04798aa8be8b46451cece"}}
{"type":"message","id":"0d30003d","parentId":"aedca770","timestamp":"2026-04-13T07:35:36.394Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_phhjjazyumqp_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"/**\n * Self-Improvement Hook for OpenClaw\n * \n * Injects a reminder to evaluate learnings during agent bootstrap.\n * Fires on agent:bootstrap event before workspace files are injected.\n */\n\nimport type { HookHandler } from 'openclaw/hooks';\n\nconst REMINDER_CONTENT = `## Self-Improvement Reminder\n\nAfter completing tasks, evaluate if any learnings should be captured:\n\n**Log when:**\n- User corrects you → \\`.learnings/LEARNINGS.md\\`\n- Command/operation fails → \\`.learnings/ERRORS.md\\`\n- User wants missing capability → \\`.learnings/FEATURE_REQUESTS.md\\`\n- You discover your knowledge was wrong → \\`.learnings/LEARNINGS.md\\`\n- You find a better approach → \\`.learnings/LEARNINGS.md\\`\n\n**Promote when pattern is proven:**\n- Behavioral patterns → \\`SOUL.md\\`\n- Workflow improvements → \\`AGENTS.md\\`\n- Tool gotchas → \\`TOOLS.md\\`\n\nKeep entries simple: date, title, what happened, what to do differently.`;\n\nconst handler: HookHandler = async (event) => {\n  // Safety checks for event structure\n  if (!event || typeof event !== 'object') {\n    return;\n  }\n\n  // Only handle agent:bootstrap events\n  if (event.type !== 'agent' || event.action !== 'bootstrap') {\n    return;\n  }\n\n  // Safety check for context\n  if (!event.context || typeof event.context !== 'object') {\n    return;\n  }\n\n  // Skip sub-agent sessions to avoid bootstrap issues\n  // Sub-agents have sessionKey patterns like \"agent:main:subagent:...\"\n  const sessionKey = event.sessionKey || '';\n  if (sessionKey.includes(':subagent:')) {\n    return;\n  }\n\n  // Inject the reminder as a virtual bootstrap file\n  // Check that bootstrapFiles is an array before pushing\n  if (Array.isArray(event.context.bootstrapFiles)) {\n    event.context.bootstrapFiles.push({\n      path: 'SELF_IMPROVEMENT_REMINDER.md',\n      content: REMINDER_CONTENT,\n      virtual: true,\n    });\n  }\n};\n\nexport default handler;\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776065736383}}
{"type":"message","id":"f942f35b","parentId":"0d30003d","timestamp":"2026-04-13T07:35:55.234Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the bootstrap hook mechanism. The `handler.ts` receives an `event` with `event.context.bootstrapFiles`, and it pushes virtual files into it. These files are then injected into the agent's context before the first reply.\n\nSo to fix the memory chain, I can modify `handler.ts` to also read the session-summary file and inject it as a bootstrap file. This way:\n1. The session-summary hook generates the summary when session ends ✅ (already working)\n2. When the new session starts, the bootstrap hook reads the latest summary file and injects it ✅ (this is what I need to add)\n\nBut wait - the session-summary hook runs at session end, and the bootstrap hook runs at session start. \n\nThe timing issue is that when the new session starts, the session-summary hook from the previous session should have already written the summary file. So when the bootstrap hook runs, it can read that file and inject it. The flow would be: old session ends → session-summary hook writes summary → new session starts → bootstrap hook reads summary and injects it. Let me verify if session-summary fires synchronously or if there's a timing gap I need to account for.\n\nActually, I should focus on what's controllable here. The bootstrap hook can read the latest session-summary file and inject it, which would make AGENTS.md step 6 somewhat redundant but guarantee the summary gets into context. The session-summary hook's filename with \"YYYY-MM-DD\" in it means today's file is ready when the new session starts. I'll modify the bootstrap hook to handle this injection.\n\nNow I'm checking the session file naming to see if there's an ordering problem - the sessions.json lists them by key, but the actual files have timestamp suffixes that might not be lexicographically sorted correctly.\n\nThe fix is straightforward: modify handler.ts to read the session-summary hook's output and inject it into the bootstrap context before the agent starts. This ensures the previous session's summary is available when AGENTS.md step 6 runs, and it addresses the bootstrap timing issue. For the framework, the scene-classifier is working now after the fix, the scorer is healthy, and cron jobs are running.","thinkingSignature":"d2d096a2fa262d396fc8fba409499beeaa8d094594e892d1714a533513d654bd"},{"type":"text","text":"\n现在我完全理解问题了。让我做三件事：\n\n1. **修改 bootstrap hook** —— 让它主动读取 session-summary 文件，注入到新 session 上下文\n2. **修复 scene-classifier scorer 配置** —— config.json 里指向 3104（废弃），应该指向 3105\n3. **验证修复**\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_6l0eeg2hmmoc_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/ai/.openclaw/hooks/session-summary/handler.js"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":52063,"output":545,"cacheRead":18601,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":71209,"cost":{"input":0.0156189,"output":0.000654,"cacheRead":0.0011160599999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.01738896}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776065736396,"responseId":"062bcfc88530a7bed92eedcf25673a67"}}
{"type":"message","id":"22b09405","parentId":"f942f35b","timestamp":"2026-04-13T07:35:55.320Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_6l0eeg2hmmoc_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"/**\n * session-summary hook\n *\n * 触发时机: /new 或 /reset\n * 行为: \n *   1. 读取上一个 session 的内容\n *   2. 读取 ephemeral/ 中的记忆碎片\n *   3. 调 LLM 生成结构化摘要 + entity 升格决策\n *   4. 写入 memory/YYYY-MM-DD-summary.md\n *   5. 执行 entity 升格（创建/更新 memory/entities/*.md）\n * 降级: LLM 失败时写规则摘要，不报错\n */\n\nimport fs from \"node:fs\";\nimport path from \"node:path\";\nimport os from \"node:os\";\nimport http from \"node:http\";\n\n// ─── Constants ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nconst MEMORY_DIR = path.join(\n  process.env.OPENCLAW_WORKSPACE_DIR ||\n    path.join(os.homedir(), \".openclaw\", \"workspace\"),\n  \"memory\"\n);\nconst EPHEMERAL_DIR = path.join(MEMORY_DIR, \"ephemeral\");\nconst ENTITIES_DIR = path.join(MEMORY_DIR, \"entities\");\nconst LLM_TIMEOUT_MS = 20_000;\n\n// ─── Types (JSDoc) ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\n/**\n * @typedef {Object} SessionEntry\n * @property {string} [sessionFile]\n * @property {string} [sessionId]\n */\n\n/**\n * @typedef {Object} HookContext\n * @property {SessionEntry} [previousSessionEntry]\n * @property {SessionEntry} [sessionEntry]\n */\n\n/**\n * @typedef {Object} EphemeralEntry\n * @property {string} timestamp\n * @property {string} sessionKey\n * @property {string} text\n * @property {string} textPreview\n * @property {object} classification\n * @property {object} scoring\n */\n\n// ─── Session File Resolution ──────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\n/**\n * 从 context 中提取 session 文件路径。\n * 优先使用 previousSessionEntry（旧 session，即刚结束的那个）。\n * @param {HookContext} context\n * @returns {string|null}\n */\nfunction resolveSessionFile(context) {\n  const prev = context?.previousSessionEntry;\n  if (prev?.sessionFile) return prev.sessionFile;\n\n  const curr = context?.sessionEntry;\n  if (curr?.sessionFile) return curr.sessionFile;\n\n  return null;\n}\n\n// ─── Message Extraction ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\n/**\n * @param {unknown} content\n * @returns {string}\n */\nfunction extractTextFromBlocks(content) {\n  if (Array.isArray(content)) {\n    for (const block of content) {\n      if (\n        block &&\n        typeof block === \"object\" &&\n        block.type === \"text\" &&\n        typeof block.text === \"string\"\n      ) {\n        return block.text;\n      }\n    }\n  }\n  return \"\";\n}\n\n/**\n * 从 .jsonl 文件中提取最新 N 条 user/assistant 消息。\n * @param {string} filePath\n * @param {number} [messageCount=40]\n * @returns {Promise<string>}\n */\nasync function extractMessages(filePath, messageCount = 40) {\n  try {\n    const content = await fs.promises.readFile(filePath, \"utf-8\");\n    const lines = content.trim().split(\"\\n\").slice(-messageCount * 2);\n    /** @type {string[]} */\n    const messages = [];\n\n    for (const line of lines) {\n      if (!line.trim()) continue;\n      try {\n        /** @type {{ type: string, message?: { role: string, content: unknown } }} */\n        const entry = JSON.parse(line);\n        if (entry.type !== \"message\") continue;\n        const msg = entry.message;\n        if (!msg?.role || !msg?.content) continue;\n        if (msg.role !== \"user\" && msg.role !== \"assistant\") continue;\n\n        const text =\n          typeof msg.content === \"string\"\n            ? msg.content\n            : extractTextFromBlocks(msg.content);\n\n        if (!text || text.startsWith(\"/\")) continue;\n        messages.push(`${msg.role}: ${text}`);\n      } catch {\n        // skip malformed lines silently\n      }\n    }\n    return messages.slice(-messageCount).join(\"\\n\");\n  } catch {\n    return \"\";\n  }\n}\n\n// ─── Ephemeral Memory Reading ─────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\n/**\n * 读取当天的 ephemeral 文件，按 sessionKey 过滤。\n * @param {string} sessionKey\n * @returns {Promise<{entries: EphemeralEntry[], preview: string}>}\n */\nasync function readEphemeralEntries(sessionKey) {\n  /** @type {EphemeralEntry[]} */\n  const allEntries = [];\n  \n  try {\n    const today = new Date().toISOString().slice(0, 10); // YYYY-MM-DD\n    const files = await fs.promises.readdir(EPHEMERAL_DIR);\n    \n    for (const file of files) {\n      if (!file.endsWith('.jsonl') || !file.startsWith(today)) continue;\n      const filePath = path.join(EPHEMERAL_DIR, file);\n      try {\n        const content = await fs.promises.readFile(filePath, 'utf-8');\n        const lines = content.trim().split('\\n');\n        for (const line of lines) {\n          if (!line.trim()) continue;\n          try {\n            const entry = JSON.parse(line);\n            if (entry.sessionKey === sessionKey) {\n              allEntries.push(entry);\n            }\n          } catch { /* skip */ }\n        }\n      } catch { /* skip file errors */ }\n    }\n  } catch { /* ephemeral dir may not exist */ }\n  \n  // 去重（相同 text 的条目只保留最新）\n  const seen = new Set();\n  const uniqueEntries = allEntries.filter(e => {\n    const key = e.text.slice(0, 100);\n    if (seen.has(key)) return false;\n    seen.add(key);\n    return true;\n  });\n  \n  // 限制最多 20 条，防止 token 爆炸\n  const entries = uniqueEntries.slice(-20);\n  \n  // 生成预览文本\n  const preview = entries.length > 0\n    ? entries.map(e => `[${e.classification?.scene || '?'}] score=${e.scoring?.score || 0} \"${e.textPreview || e.text.slice(0, 80)}\"`).join('\\n')\n    : '';\n  \n  return { entries, preview };\n}\n\n// ─── LLM Generation ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\n/**\n * @param {string} sessionContent\n * @param {string} ephemeralPreview\n * @returns {string}\n */\nfunction buildSummaryPrompt(sessionContent, ephemeralPreview) {\n  return `你是一个会话摘要生成器，同时负责记忆升格决策。\n\n给定以下对话记录和实时捕获的记忆碎片，生成：\n1. 一个结构化摘要\n2. 需要升格为 entity 页的记忆条目（只有真正重要的、涉及系统/项目/偏好的才升格）\n\n## 对话记录：\n${sessionContent || \"(无会话内容)\"}\n\n## 记忆碎片（来自 ephemeral/，按 sessionKey 聚合）：\n${ephemeralPreview || \"(无碎片)\"}\n\n要求：\n- 主题：一句话概括，少于20字\n- 关键决策：列出所有决策，没有则写\"无明确决策\"\n- 重要发现：列出有价值的结论/教训，没有则写\"无\"\n- 待跟进：列出未完成事项，没有则写\"无\"\n\n## entity 升格决策：\n识别记忆碎片中值得创建或更新 entity 页的内容。只有以下类型才升格：\n- 系统组件状态变化（如：3104修好了、3103配置改了）\n- 用户偏好发现（如：喜欢中文、务实风格）\n- 项目进度更新（如：项目X现在做到哪了）\n- 关键结论或教训（如：方案A比方案B好，别再踩这个坑）\n\n格式（严格按此格式，摘要和entity分开）：\n---\n## 摘要\n## 主题\n{主题}\n\n## 关键决策\n{决策列表}\n\n## 重要发现\n{发现列表}\n\n## 待跟进\n{待办列表}\n\n## entities\n{如果需要升格，格式：ENTITY|create|entity-name|文件路径|第1行标题|正文内容（多行）\n如果没有entity需要升格，写：NONE\n示例：ENTITY|create|scene-classifier|memory/entities/scene-classifier.md|# Entity: scene-classifier|## 基本信息\\n- 状态: 已修复\\n## 更新\\n### 2026-04-13\\n修复了...}\n---`;\n}\n\n/**\n * @param {string} sessionContent\n * @returns {string}\n */\nfunction buildFallbackPrompt(sessionContent) {\n  return `你是一个会话摘要生成器。\n给定以下对话记录，生成一个结构化摘要。\n\n## 对话记录：\n${sessionContent}\n\n要求：\n- 主题：一句话概括，少于20字\n- 关键决策：列出所有决策，没有则写\"无明确决策\"\n- 重要发现：列出有价值的结论/教训，没有则写\"无\"\n- 待跟进：列出未完成事项，没有则写\"无\"\n\n格式（严格按此格式）：\n## 主题\n{主题}\n\n## 关键决策\n{决策列表}\n\n## 重要发现\n{发现列表}\n\n## 待跟进\n{待办列表}`;\n}\n\n/**\n * 调用 gateway LLM 接口生成摘要。\n * 超时 20s 后自动销毁请求并降级。\n * @param {string} sessionContent\n * @param {string} ephemeralPreview\n * @returns {Promise<{summary: string, entities: Array<{action:string,name:string,file:string,content:string}>}>}\n */\nasync function generateSummaryWithEntities(sessionContent, ephemeralPreview) {\n  const prompt = buildSummaryPrompt(sessionContent, ephemeralPreview);\n  \n  const postData = JSON.stringify({\n    model: \"minimax/MiniMax-M2.7\",\n    messages: [{ role: \"user\", content: prompt }],\n    temperature: 0.3,\n    max_tokens: 800,\n  });\n\n  return new Promise((resolve) => {\n    let settled = false;\n    const doResolve = (v) => {\n      if (settled) return;\n      settled = true;\n      resolve(v);\n    };\n\n    const req = http.request(\n      \"http://127.0.0.1:3102/v1/chat/completions\",\n      {\n        method: \"POST\",\n        headers: {\n          \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\",\n          \"Content-Length\": Buffer.byteLength(postData),\n        },\n      },\n      (res) => {\n        let data = \"\";\n        res.on(\"data\", (c) => (data += c));\n        res.on(\"end\", () => {\n          try {\n            const parsed = JSON.parse(data);\n            const text = parsed.choices?.[0]?.message?.content || \"\";\n            const result = parseLLMOutput(text.trim());\n            doResolve(result);\n          } catch {\n            doResolve(generateFallbackResult(sessionContent));\n          }\n        });\n      }\n    );\n\n    req.on(\"error\", () => doResolve(generateFallbackResult(sessionContent)));\n\n    // 20s 单边超时\n    const timer = setTimeout(() => {\n      try { req.destroy(); } catch { /* noop */ }\n      doResolve(generateFallbackResult(sessionContent));\n    }, LLM_TIMEOUT_MS);\n\n    req.on(\"close\", () => clearTimeout(timer));\n\n    req.write(postData);\n    req.end();\n  });\n}\n\n/**\n * 解析 LLM 输出，提取摘要和 entity 升格指令。\n * @param {string} text\n * @returns {{summary: string, entities: Array<{action:string,name:string,file:string,content:string}>}}\n */\nfunction parseLLMOutput(text) {\n  const entities = [];\n  \n  // 提取 entity 块\n  const entityMatch = text.match(/## entities\\n([\\s\\S]*?)(?:---|$)/);\n  const entityBlock = entityMatch ? entityMatch[1].trim() : '';\n  \n  if (entityBlock && entityBlock !== 'NONE') {\n    const lines = entityBlock.split('\\n');\n    for (const line of lines) {\n      const parts = line.split('|');\n      if (parts.length >= 5 && parts[0] === 'ENTITY') {\n        const action = parts[1].trim(); // create | update\n        const name = parts[2].trim();\n        const file = parts[3].trim();\n        const content = parts.slice(4).join('|').trim();\n        entities.push({ action, name, file, content });\n      }\n    }\n  }\n  \n  // 提取摘要部分\n  let summary = text.replace(/## entities\\n[\\s\\S]*?(?:---|$)/, '').trim();\n  // 去掉 ## 摘要 标记（如果LLM输出了）\n  summary = summary.replace(/^## 摘要\\s*/, '');\n  \n  return { summary: summary.trim(), entities };\n}\n\n/**\n * @param {string} sessionContent\n * @returns {{summary: string, entities: Array}}\n */\nfunction generateFallbackResult(sessionContent) {\n  const firstLine = (sessionContent.split(\"\\n\")[0] ?? \"\").slice(0, 60).replace(/[#*]/g, \"\").trim();\n  const summary = `# Session 摘要\n\n## 主题\n${firstLine || \"会话摘要\"}\n\n## 关键决策\n无\n\n## 重要发现\n无\n\n## 待跟进\n见原始对话记录\n`;\n  return { summary, entities: [] };\n}\n\n// ─── Entity Writing ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\n/**\n * @param {string} name\n * @param {string} content\n * @returns {Promise<void>}\n */\nasync function writeEntityFile(name, content) {\n  try {\n    await fs.promises.mkdir(ENTITIES_DIR, { recursive: true });\n    const filePath = path.join(ENTITIES_DIR, `${name}.md`);\n    const header = `# Entity: ${name}\\n\\n`;\n    await fs.promises.writeFile(filePath, header + content + '\\n', 'utf-8');\n    console.log(`[session-summary] Entity written: ${name}.md`);\n  } catch (e) {\n    console.error(`[session-summary] Entity write failed: ${name}`, e);\n  }\n}\n\n// ─── Fallback ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\n/**\n * @param {string} content\n * @param {string} date\n * @param {string} time\n * @returns {string}\n */\nfunction buildFallbackSummary(content, date, time) {\n  const firstLine = (content.split(\"\\n\")[0] ?? \"\").slice(0, 60).replace(/[#*]/g, \"\").trim();\n  const preview = firstLine || \"会话摘要\";\n  return `# Session: ${date} ${time}\n\n## 主题\n${preview}\n\n## 关键决策\n无\n\n## 重要发现\n无\n\n## 待跟进\n见原始对话记录\n`;\n}\n\n// ─── File Writing ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\n/**\n * @param {string} summary\n * @param {string} date\n * @param {string} time\n * @param {string} sessionKey\n * @returns {Promise<void>}\n */\nasync function writeSummaryFile(summary, date, time, sessionKey) {\n  const slug = slugFromSummary(summary, time);\n  const filename = `${date}-${slug}.md`;\n  const filePath = path.join(MEMORY_DIR, filename);\n\n  await fs.promises.mkdir(MEMORY_DIR, { recursive: true });\n\n  const fullContent = [\n    `# Session: ${date} ${time}`,\n    \"\",\n    \"<!-- summary-only -->\",\n    summary,\n    \"\",\n    `<!-- source: ${sessionKey} -->`,\n  ].join(\"\\n\");\n\n  await fs.promises.writeFile(filePath, fullContent, \"utf-8\");\n  console.log(`[session-summary] Written: ${filename}`);\n}\n\n/**\n * @param {string} summary\n * @param {string} time\n * @returns {string}\n */\nfunction slugFromSummary(summary, time) {\n  const match = summary.match(/^## 主题$\\s*([^\\n]+)/m);\n  if (!match) return time.replace(/:/g, \"\");\n\n  return match[1]\n    .toLowerCase()\n    .replace(/[^a-z0-9\\u4e00-\\u9fff]+/g, \"-\")\n    .replace(/^-+|-+$/g, \"\")\n    .slice(0, 40) || time.replace(/:/g, \"\");\n}\n\n// ─── Core ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\n/**\n * @param {{ type: string, action: string, sessionKey: string, context: HookContext, messages: unknown[] }} event\n */\nasync function run(event) {\n  const isTarget = event.type === \"command\" && (event.action === \"new\" || event.action === \"reset\");\n  if (!isTarget) return;\n\n  const now = new Date();\n  const date = now.toISOString().split(\"T\")[0];\n  const time = now.toISOString().split(\"T\")[1].split(\".\")[0].slice(0, 5);\n\n  // 1. 解析 session 文件路径（优先 previousSessionEntry）\n  const sessionFile = resolveSessionFile(event.context || {});\n\n  // 2. 读取消息内容\n  const content = sessionFile ? await extractMessages(sessionFile) : \"\";\n\n  // 3. 读取 ephemeral 记忆碎片\n  // 从 previousSessionEntry.sessionId 获取前一个 session 的 key（sessionId = sessionKey）\n  const prevSessionId = event.context?.previousSessionEntry?.sessionId || event.sessionKey;\n  const { entries, preview: ephemeralPreview } = await readEphemeralEntries(prevSessionId);\n\n  // 4. 生成摘要 + entity 升格（失败则降级）\n  const { summary, entities } = content.trim().length > 50\n    ? await generateSummaryWithEntities(content, ephemeralPreview)\n    : { summary: buildFallbackSummary(content || \"(无会话内容)\", date, time), entities: [] };\n\n  // 5. 写入 memory/（后台，不等待）\n  writeSummaryFile(summary, date, time, event.sessionKey).catch((err) => {\n    console.error(\"[session-summary] Write error:\", err);\n  });\n\n  // 6. 执行 entity 升格（后台，不等待）\n  for (const entity of entities) {\n    if (entity.action === 'create' || entity.action === 'update') {\n      writeEntityFile(entity.name, entity.content).catch((err) => {\n        console.error(\"[session-summary] Entity write error:\", err);\n      });\n    }\n  }\n}\n\n// ─── Entry Point ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nexport default function handler(event) {\n  run(event).catch((err) => {\n    console.error(\"[session-summary] Uncaught error:\", err);\n  });\n}\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776065755307}}
{"type":"message","id":"29b137f1","parentId":"22b09405","timestamp":"2026-04-13T07:36:46.649Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the full picture. The session-summary hook:\n\n1. Listens for `command:new` or `command:reset` events\n2. Reads the previous session's messages from `previousSessionEntry.sessionFile`\n3. Reads ephemeral entries\n4. Generates a summary using LLM\n5. Writes to `memory/YYYY-MM-DD-slug.md`\n6. Writes entity files\n\nThe key insight: this hook fires on `command:new` or `command:reset`, which is BEFORE the new session starts. So when the old session ends (via /new), this hook generates the summary for the old session.\n\n\nThe hook runs after the command is issued but before the new session initializes, which means the summary should be ready by the time the new session bootstraps. The bootstrap handler could read the latest summary file at that point, but there's a timing issue—the hook writes to memory asynchronously while the new session might start reading bootstrap files before that write completes.\n\nLooking at the event flow, `session-summary` fires on `session:end` while `bootstrap` fires on `agent:bootstrap`, but examining the actual event data shows `agent:bootstrap` fires after the first reply in the current session, not before session start. This means bootstrap files are injected too late to include the session summary that was just generated.\n\nThe real issue is that `agent:bootstrap` isn't firing at the right time in the session lifecycle. I should modify the bootstrap handler to read the session-summary file directly from the hooks directory, since it has access to the hook environment at startup.\n\nMy approach: update handler.ts to read the most recent session-summary file and inject it into the context as a virtual file, fix the sceneClassifier config to point to the right port, and verify everything works together.","thinkingSignature":"e12053ce8df1fb6b72ea575325d5dfd897297a31e6c77bc56374b29df911a9c7"},{"type":"text","text":"\n现在我完全理解了整个链路。问题很清楚：\n\n- `session-summary` hook 在 `/new` 时运行，写入摘要 ✅\n- `bootstrap` hook（handler.ts）监听 `agent:bootstrap` 事件，但这个事件在我第一条回复之后才触发，所以 session-summary 的内容从来没被注入\n\n修复方案：在 bootstrap hook 里主动读 session-summary 文件，在新 session 启动时注入。\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_n2qbi9etkkup_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/home/ai/.openclaw/hooks/handler.ts","edits":[{"oldText":"/**\n * Self-Improvement Hook for OpenClaw\n * \n * Injects a reminder to evaluate learnings during agent bootstrap.\n * Fires on agent:bootstrap event before workspace files are injected.\n */\n\nimport type { HookHandler } from 'openclaw/hooks';\n\nconst REMINDER_CONTENT = `## Self-Improvement Reminder\n\nAfter completing tasks, evaluate if any learnings should be captured:\n\n**Log when:**\n- User corrects you → `.learnings/LEARNINGS.md`\n- Command/operation fails → `.learnings/ERRORS.md`\n- User wants missing capability → `.learnings/FEATURE_REQUESTS.md`\n- You discover your knowledge was wrong → `.learnings/LEARNINGS.md`\n- You find a better approach → `.learnings/LEARNINGS.md`\n\n**Promote when pattern is proven:**\n- Behavioral patterns → `SOUL.md`\n- Workflow improvements → `AGENTS.md`\n- Tool gotchas → `TOOLS.md`\n\nKeep entries simple: date, title, what happened, what to do differently.`;\n\nconst handler: HookHandler = async (event) => {\n  // Safety checks for event structure\n  if (!event || typeof event !== 'object') {\n    return;\n  }\n\n  // Only handle agent:bootstrap events\n  if (event.type !== 'agent' || event.action !== 'bootstrap') {\n    return;\n  }\n\n  // Safety check for context\n  if (!event.context || typeof event.context !== 'object') {\n    return;\n  }\n\n  // Skip sub-agent sessions to avoid bootstrap issues\n  // Sub-agents have sessionKey patterns like \"agent:main:subagent:...\"\n  const sessionKey = event.sessionKey || '';\n  if (sessionKey.includes(':subagent:')) {\n    return;\n  }\n\n  // Inject the reminder as a virtual bootstrap file\n  // Check that bootstrapFiles is an array before pushing\n  if (Array.isArray(event.context.bootstrapFiles)) {\n    event.context.bootstrapFiles.push({\n      path: 'SELF_IMPROVEMENT_REMINDER.md',\n      content: REMINDER_CONTENT,\n      virtual: true,\n    });\n  }\n};\n\nexport default handler;","newText":"/**\n * Self-Improvement + Session-Summary Bootstrap Hook for OpenClaw\n * \n * Injects:\n * 1. Self-Improvement reminder during agent bootstrap\n * 2. Previous session's summary (memory/*-session-summary.md) as bootstrap context\n * \n * Fires on agent:bootstrap event before workspace files are injected.\n */\n\nimport fs from 'node:fs';\nimport path from 'node:path';\nimport os from 'node:os';\nimport type { HookHandler } from 'openclaw/hooks';\n\nconst SELF_IMPROVEMENT_REMINDER = `## Self-Improvement Reminder\n\nAfter completing tasks, evaluate if any learnings should be captured:\n\n**Log when:**\n- User corrects you \\`.learnings/LEARNINGS.md\\`\n- Command/operation fails \\`.learnings/ERRORS.md\\`\n- User wants missing capability \\`.learnings/FEATURE_REQUESTS.md\\`\n- You discover your knowledge was wrong \\`.learnings/LEARNINGS.md\\`\n- You find a better approach \\`.learnings/LEARNINGS.md\\`\n\n**Promote when pattern is proven:**\n- Behavioral patterns \\`SOUL.md\\`\n- Workflow improvements \\`AGENTS.md\\`\n- Tool gotchas \\`TOOLS.md\\`\n\nKeep entries simple: date, title, what happened, what to do differently.`;\n\n/**\n * Find and read the most recent session-summary file.\n * Looks in memory/ for *-session-summary.md files, returns most recent by mtime.\n */\nasync function getLatestSessionSummary(): Promise<string | null> {\n  try {\n    const memoryDir = path.join(\n      process.env.OPENCLAW_WORKSPACE_DIR || path.join(os.homedir(), '.openclaw', 'workspace'),\n      'memory'\n    );\n    \n    const files = await fs.promises.readdir(memoryDir);\n    const summaryFiles = files.filter(f => f.endsWith('-session-summary.md'));\n    \n    if (summaryFiles.length === 0) return null;\n    \n    // Sort by mtime descending\n    const withMtime = await Promise.all(\n      summaryFiles.map(async (f) => ({\n        file: f,\n        mtime: (await fs.promises.stat(path.join(memoryDir, f))).mtimeMs,\n      }))\n    );\n    withMtime.sort((a, b) => b.mtime - a.mtime);\n    \n    const latest = withMtime[0].file;\n    const content = await fs.promises.readFile(path.join(memoryDir, latest), 'utf-8');\n    \n    // Strip <!-- summary-only --> and <!-- source: ... --> tags for clean injection\n    const cleaned = content\n      .replace(/<!-- summary-only -->/g, '')\n      .replace(/<!-- source:[^>]*>/g, '')\n      .trim();\n    \n    return `## 上一页会话摘要 (from ${latest})\n\n${cleaned}`;\n  } catch {\n    return null;\n  }\n}\n\nconst handler: HookHandler = async (event) => {\n  // Safety checks for event structure\n  if (!event || typeof event !== 'object') {\n    return;\n  }\n\n  // Only handle agent:bootstrap events\n  if (event.type !== 'agent' || event.action !== 'bootstrap') {\n    return;\n  }\n\n  // Safety check for context\n  if (!event.context || typeof event.context !== 'object') {\n    return;\n  }\n\n  // Skip sub-agent sessions to avoid bootstrap issues\n  const sessionKey = event.sessionKey || '';\n  if (sessionKey.includes(':subagent:')) {\n    return;\n  }\n\n  if (!Array.isArray(event.context.bootstrapFiles)) {\n    return;\n  }\n\n  // 1. Inject self-improvement reminder\n  event.context.bootstrapFiles.push({\n    path: 'SELF_IMPROVEMENT_REMINDER.md',\n    content: SELF_IMPROVEMENT_REMINDER,\n    virtual: true,\n  });\n\n  // 2. Inject previous session summary (memory chain key step)\n  const summary = await getLatestSessionSummary();\n  if (summary) {\n    event.context.bootstrapFiles.push({\n      path: 'PREVIOUS_SESSION_SUMMARY.md',\n      content: summary,\n      virtual: true,\n    });\n  }\n};\n\nexport default handler;"}]}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":56604,"output":2046,"cacheRead":18601,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":77251,"cost":{"input":0.0169812,"output":0.0024552,"cacheRead":0.0011160599999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.020552459999999998}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776065755322,"responseId":"062bcfda1e6fbd33d0b4b320e5ec56a6"}}
