{"type":"message","id":"3125e3d9","parentId":"76b7e5a2","timestamp":"2026-04-13T07:49:51.927Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to think about the best way to integrate wiki-auto-learn into the framework. Let me think deeply about this.\n\nCurrent framework:\n1. ephemeral - captures fragments in real-time via hooks\n2. session-summary - generates structured summary at end of session\n3. bootstrap - injects previous session summary into new session context\n\nThe wiki-auto-learn system:\n- Ingests raw sources (docs, notes, papers) into entities/\n- Has multiple scripts (wiki-auto-learn.py, wiki-7h-loop.sh, etc.)\n- No cron, no hooks, completely standalone\n\nThe question is: what's the right integration point?\n\nLet me think about the data flow:\n\n\nWiki ingestion is fundamentally different from session memory—it's long-term knowledge accumulation rather than conversational context. If I trigger it from session-summary hooks, I'd be creating an unbounded loop since wiki updates could themselves generate more sessions. The cleanest path is keeping ephemeral and session-summary focused on conversation state, while routing wiki ingestion through a separate cron job that runs on a different cycle, like memory-keeper. Actually, the cleanest approach is Option D: make wiki-auto-learn a session that's launched by the session-summary hook, similar to how the v8 system works—spawning an isolated sub-agent for complex work. But I need to think through the trigger conditions more carefully. The real question isn't when to run the wiki ingestion, but what should trigger it: when new raw sources appear, when a session produces notable decisions worth capturing as entities, or on a scheduled interval for general maintenance?\n\nThe most practical setup would be a cron job running wiki-auto-learn periodically, with session-summary creating/updating entity pages when significant decisions are made during sessions, and the keeper simply monitoring progress without duplicating what the learner already does. I'm thinking through how session-summary could also update entities when key decisions happen, while keeping the architecture clean and avoiding duplication. The cleanest approach would be a cron job running wiki-auto-learn hourly to handle raw source ingestion, then leveraging the session-summary hook to directly create or update entity pages when significant decisions surface during conversations—rather than spawning separate agents. The framework should manage ingestion and entity updates as distinct responsibilities, with a daily maintenance cron to handle cross-references and structural integrity. The architecture I'm settling on has three distinct layers: ephemeral captures conversation fragments in real-time, session-summary extracts entities and updates memory on a schedule, and then there's a separate async process that maintains the actual knowledge base by ingesting raw sources into the entity system.\n\nBut I need to think through the timing more carefully—the session-summary hook runs synchronously and can write entities, while wiki-auto-learn runs as a cron job, so I need to clarify whether session-summary is doing the entity extraction or if that's delegated to the async learner. I need to focus on what's actionable here rather than getting caught up in the technical details. The real insight is that the two systems serve different purposes—they don't need to be tightly coupled. What matters is ensuring session-summary can write to entities and the cron jobs actually run.","thinkingSignature":"8d4185c1a9e66ea102bd1d9c3ccc39ab53d38e4fbd94634c395807202edc42d8"},{"type":"text","text":"想了一下，核心问题在于：\n\n**wiki-auto-learn 和 session-summary 是两个不同维度的东西，强行并轨会乱。**\n\n| 系统 | 驱动 | 内容 |\n|------|------|------|\n| session-summary | /new 触发 | 从会话提炼实体页（决策、发现、偏好） |\n| wiki-auto-learn | 原始文档 | 从 docs/papers/notes 提炼实体页（知识积累） |\n\n**正确的分层：**\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│  Raw Sources (docs/notes/papers)        │  ← wiki-auto-learn 摄取\n└────────────────┬────────────────────────┘\n                 ↓\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│  entities/ (49个)                       │  ← 知识沉淀\n└─────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                 ↑ session-summary 写入\n                 │\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│  ephemeral → session-summary → 实体页   │  ← 对话驱动\n└─────────────────────────────────────────┘\n\ncron: wiki-auto-learn 每小时 (知识积累)\ncron: memory-keeper 每天4点 (维护/交叉引用)\n```\n\n**session-summary hook 现在的代码已经支持 entity 升格**（看过了），每次 session 结束如果 LLM 判断有值得沉淀的内容，会直接写 entities/。\n\n所以实际需要做的事只有一件：\n\n> **把 wiki-auto-learn.py 挂到 cron，每小时跑一次。**\n\n其他两个 cron（memory-maintain/keeper）职责不变，不碰 wiki-auto-learn 的流程，避免重复调度。\n\n要我把这个 cron 建起来吗？"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":938,"cacheRead":87254,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":88192,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0.0011256,"cacheRead":0.0052352399999999995,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0063608399999999995}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776066556641,"responseId":"062bd2fc7162cb529773425ef56bb1e3"}}
