{"type":"message","id":"1cb2299c","parentId":"1c201864","timestamp":"2026-04-13T07:52:45.561Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_wc2u9cq0hp4k_1","toolName":"cron","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"id\": \"b3c6834e-c671-4b21-b6d4-0dc9c86f0e84\",\n  \"agentId\": \"main\",\n  \"sessionKey\": \"agent:main:main\",\n  \"name\": \"wiki-learn\",\n  \"enabled\": true,\n  \"createdAtMs\": 1776066765541,\n  \"updatedAtMs\": 1776066765541,\n  \"schedule\": {\n    \"kind\": \"cron\",\n    \"expr\": \"0 * * * *\",\n    \"tz\": \"Asia/Shanghai\",\n    \"staggerMs\": 300000\n  },\n  \"sessionTarget\": \"isolated\",\n  \"wakeMode\": \"now\",\n  \"payload\": {\n    \"kind\": \"agentTurn\",\n    \"message\": \"执行 ~/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/wiki-learn-once.sh 并将输出追加到 ~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/log.md\"\n  },\n  \"delivery\": {\n    \"mode\": \"announce\"\n  },\n  \"state\": {\n    \"nextRunAtMs\": 1776067359287\n  }\n}"}],"details":{"id":"b3c6834e-c671-4b21-b6d4-0dc9c86f0e84","agentId":"main","sessionKey":"agent:main:main","name":"wiki-learn","enabled":true,"createdAtMs":1776066765541,"updatedAtMs":1776066765541,"schedule":{"kind":"cron","expr":"0 * * * *","tz":"Asia/Shanghai","staggerMs":300000},"sessionTarget":"isolated","wakeMode":"now","payload":{"kind":"agentTurn","message":"执行 ~/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/wiki-learn-once.sh 并将输出追加到 ~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/log.md"},"delivery":{"mode":"announce"},"state":{"nextRunAtMs":1776067359287}},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776066765549}}
{"type":"message","id":"409024c1","parentId":"1cb2299c","timestamp":"2026-04-13T07:52:54.853Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Hmm, I used `agentTurn` with `isolated` session, but the message is a bash command, not really an agent task. And the schedule has staggerMs added automatically.\n\nActually, the issue is the cron is using agentTurn with a bash command, which is inefficient. It should probably use systemEvent or a direct script execution. But the OpenClaw cron system doesn't have a \"run shell script\" payload type directly.\n\nLet me think about this - for periodic script execution, we could:\n1. Use systemEvent with a sessionTarget=isolated - the isolated agent would then run the script\n2. But that's overkill - we just want to run a bash script\n\n\n3. The cron system is really built for triggering agent sessions rather than direct script execution, so the agentTurn approach is technically correct even if it feels heavy for a simple bash command.\n\nThe real problem is the staggerMs - if the user wants the job to run at the top of every hour, that 5-minute random delay could push it past the hour boundary. I should remove that and let the cron expression handle the timing instead. Though realistically with cron scheduling, there's usually some drift to account for anyway.\n\nI think the current setup is fine for now. Let me just verify the cron is actually set up correctly.","thinkingSignature":"72b65fbf805c9212ba4474df5ca2e9f2aa9f2dcf520c3aaacf5adb014cad83bd"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_g30wg5q5lq96_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"~/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/bin/openclaw cron list 2>/dev/null | head -15"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":74663,"output":316,"cacheRead":18714,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":93693,"cost":{"input":0.0223989,"output":0.0003792,"cacheRead":0.00112284,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.02390094}},"stopReason":"toolUse","ti