{"type":"message","id":"e56a11bc","parentId":"440de793","timestamp":"2026-04-13T08:09:47.889Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Hmm, the issue is that the script is showing \"当前 41\" which is not right. There should only be 30 entities after the previous run. Let me check what happened. It seems like the entities that were removed (those 11) were removed from the entities/ directory to archive, but then new ones were added when the previous run's post-prune kicked in. Wait, no - the previous run ended with 30. So why is it now showing 41?\n\nOh! I see - the entities that were in the ARCHIVE from before (from the earlier manual prune) are still in archive. The newly added ones from the skills/ directory (17 of them) that were created in the previous run went to entities/, then got pruned to archive. \n\nBut then the post-prune phase added them back in and pruned them again. After that final cleanup we had 30, but now the count shows 41 - which doesn't match. Let me verify what's actually in the entities directory right now to see where the extra 11 came from.","thinkingSignature":"3538967be080771dd79c3d57f7d71fd1f8a9ebf3d7a882d08f40910bed1e6d8f"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_80i4nidsl2vw_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls ~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/entities/ | wc -l; ls ~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/entities/ | sort"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":87441,"output":270,"cacheRead":18887,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":106598,"cost":{"input":0.0262323,"output":0.00032399999999999996,"cacheRead":0.0011332199999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.027689520000000002}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776067778488,"responseId":"062bd7c16731324b52b8570e487ac79e"}}
