{"type":"message","id":"5c8be57c","parentId":"6d343373","timestamp":"2026-04-13T08:10:12.333Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, that's 41 and many of the claude-code ones that were supposed to be pruned are back. That's because `claude-code-40-tools-complete-report.md` etc. are being recreated from the skills/ directory scan as `claude-code-40-tools-complete-report` (note: no `.md` extension in the directory name, but when the entity file is created it gets `.md`).\n\nWait no - the skills/ directories are like `~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/claude-code-40-tools-complete-report/`. When we create an entity from that, the name would be `claude-code-40-tools-complete-report` without the `.md` extension. \n\nBut these files already existed from before. Looking at the file listing, I'm seeing multiple versions of the same report with different suffixes like `-complete-final`, `-final-ultimate`, and `-production`. Some of these are showing as duplicates from earlier manual pruning operations, which suggests the directory scan is recreating files that were already archived. Wait, looking more carefully at the naming - some have underscores in the directory names (which are the actual skill directories), and the script converts them to hyphens when creating entity files. But these already exist with hyphens. So these must be the ORIGINAL entity files that were never actually in the skills/ directory scan - they're coming back from somewhere else, maybe the archive was restored? No, the script moves files to archive, not restores.\n\nI think what's happening is the script is picking up skill directories with these long names and creating entity files from them, even though these names are very unusual for skill directories. Let me check what skill directories actually exist - there's `task_orchestrator` and `v8_classifier` with underscores that become hyphens, but these longer `claude-code-*-report` names seem different. Looking at the timestamp from the ls output and the stat info for the file I moved to archive earlier, it's clear the archive operation happened after the script ran and completed, which means the file got moved after the operation finished. So these entity files shouldn't exist anymore unless they're being recreated by the script itself. I'm wondering if `claude-code-40-tools-complete-report` is actually a skill directory that exists, which would explain why the script keeps creating these entity files even after I moved them to archive. Let me check what's actually in the skills/ directory and review the current state of entities to understand the cycle of additions and prunings.","thinkingSignature":"fb91dd714a18d58099da59de4cfe0e521ecd76588da49735dded2c9db4c23e20"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_fs1p8efuswkg_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/ | grep -i claude | head -20; echo \"---\"; echo \"=== 41个entities详情 ===\"; for f in ~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/entities/*.md; do lines=$(wc -l < \"$f\"); status=$(grep \"^status:\" \"$f\" 2>/dev/null | head -1); echo \"$lines $status $(basename $f)\"; done | sort -n | head -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":87967,"output":627,"cacheRead":18887,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":107481,"cost":{"input":0.0263901,"output":0.0007524,"cacheRead":0.0011332199999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.02827572}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776067788046,"responseId":"062bd7ccfb74f805dac7cb429882311d"}}
