{"type":"message","id":"872078c2","parentId":"c1fd7856","timestamp":"2026-04-13T08:10:28.977Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the full picture:\n\n1. The `skills/` directory has skill directories like `claude-code-architecture`, `claude-code-commands`, etc. (5 of them)\n2. But there are also skill directories like `claude-code-40-tools-complete-report`, `claude-code-architecture-overview`, etc. These are NOT real skill directories - they were created when the wiki-learn script previously created entity files in the `skills/` directory thinking they were skill directories!\n\nWait no - looking at the skills/ output, there's no `claude-code-40-tools-complete-report` in the skills directory. So where did these entity files come from?\n\n\nLet me trace through what actually happened here. I pruned 16 entities earlier and moved them to archive, including `claude-code-40-tools-complete-report.md`. Then when the wiki-learn script ran, it scanned the skills/ directory and created entities from what it found there, but something's not adding up about which files got created versus which ones I manually moved.\n\nLooking at the directory listing, there are only 5 actual Claude Code skills visible, yet somehow 16+ of these entity files exist with names like `claude-code-architecture.md` and `claude-code-commands.md`. I think what's happening is that when the script created an entity for `claude-code-architecture`, it might have also created duplicate or similar entity files that are cluttering up the entities directory.\n\nThe real issue is that I'm running this manually multiple times instead of just letting the cron job handle it. When I do run it repeatedly, the space check at the beginning keeps saying \"41 entities, can only add -6\" because the previous cleanup already hit the target of 30, but then the prune step kicks in again and removes the newly added entities I just created. It's caught in a loop where it's pruning