{"type":"message","id":"177f4c23","parentId":"cc4fdcac","timestamp":"2026-04-13T08:10:53.982Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see! There are 26 skill directories. When the script scans skills/, it finds all 26 and tries to create entities for them if they don't exist in entities/. But the problem is: some of these skill directories have underscores (`task_orchestrator`, `v8_classifier`, `v8_scorer`), and the entity files use hyphens. So the script thinks these don't exist and tries to create them.\n\nFor example:\n- `skills/task_orchestrator/` → entity created as `task_orchestrator.md` (underscore preserved)\n- But we already have `task-orchestrator.md` (hyphen) which was manually created\n\n\n- Same issue with `v8_scorer` creating a duplicate instead of using the existing `v8-scorer.md`\n\nThis explains why the skills/ directory scan keeps finding 17 \"new\" entities—it's creating duplicates with underscores while the actual entities use hyphens. The real culprit is that after pruning down to 30, the script then tries to add all 26 untracked skills, which pushes us right back over the limit.\n\nSo the actual problem isn't that we're constantly adding and removing the same files—it's that the underscore-named skills don't have matching hyphen-named entities yet. The script creates them, then the prune kicks in and removes them, but only if they're auto-ingested and meet the line count threshold. Those manually-created ones with hyphens never get touched because they have higher priority.\n\nLet me trace through what actually happened: after the prune reduced entities to 30, the next run found 41 total and said we could only add -6 spaces. Then it ran another prune cycle that removed 11 files—which doesn't match the 16 that should have been auto-ingested. So either some of those manually-created files are somehow getting caught in the prune, or there's something else going on with how the archive is working.\n\nActually,