{"type":"message","id":"2782b0a7","parentId":"6f6199f3","timestamp":"2026-04-13T08:11:15.550Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so there are 26 directories in skills/, and among them are:\n- 5 claude-code-* (architecture, commands, security, telemetry, tools) - these are real skills\n- The rest are auto-ingested skills\n\nBut wait - what about `claude-code-40-tools-complete-report` and others? They're NOT in the skills/ directory listing. So how did `claude-code-40-tools-complete-report.md` entity get created?\n\nUnless... the skills/ directory DID have these directories at some point (maybe from a previous wiki-learn run that created them there), but then they were removed? Or maybe I'm misreading.\n\n\nActually, looking at the skill names more carefully: `claude-code-commands` and `claude-code-telemetry` don't exist in skills/ but they're showing up as entity files with status \"auto-ingested\", which means they must have been created at some point. So the skills/ directory did contain these at an earlier time. Right now there are 26 directories in skills/, and the script would try to create entities for all of them. But the current entity count is 41, so I need to figure out how many more entities would be created from the remaining skills.\n\nThe script should create entities for the skills that don't already have corresponding entity files. I'm wondering if some entities with underscore names got created in a previous run when the script was converting underscore directories to entity files with underscores in the names, but now those same entities exist with hyphenated names instead. That could explain the duplication and why the count doesn't match what I'd expect from the 26 directories alone. the script is finding `task_orchestrator` in skills/ but there's already a `task-orchestrator.md` in entities with a hyphen, so it's not recognizing it as a match and trying to create it again. Same issue with `v8_scorer` and `