{"type":"message","id":"41f897a9","parentId":"56b4223d","timestamp":"2026-04-13T08:12:25.045Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Still showing \"当前 41\" and pruning 11 files, even after I cleaned up to 25. This means the files are being RESTORED from archive somehow, or they're still there.Wait - looking at the \"精简: agent-team-orchestration.md\" etc. These were the files that I moved to archive in the previous step. But they're being pruned from entities/ again? That means they were RESTORED or RECREATED. \n\nOh! I think I see the bug now. Let me look at what `ls \"$ENTITIES\"/*.md | wc -l` returns after my cleanup:\n\nI cleaned up: moved 16 auto-ingested files to archive. The ls now shows 25. \n\nBut the script is still reporting 41 entities before pruning. That's 41 entities when there should only be 25 after cleanup. So either my cleanup didn't actually remove the files, or something is recreating them. Let me verify the actual count right now - I just moved 16 auto-ingested files to archive and ran the cleanup, so entities/ should have 25 files. But if the script is seeing 41 again, those files must have been recreated somehow.\n\nWait, I need to check if my cleanup is actually working. The grep command is searching for \"status: auto-ingested\" with the colon and space, but what if the files in entities/ don't have that exact format in their frontmatter? Let me look at what the cleanup actually found - it reported moving 16 files, so the cleanup did run, but I should verify the grep pattern is matching correctly. So the cleanup script should be finding all 16 auto-ingested files since they all have `status: auto-ingested`, which means `ai-usage.md` and other manually-created files shouldn't be in that list. After moving those 16 files, there should be exactly 25 remaining. But somehow the current run is showing 41 entities instead of 25, which suggests something's off with how the files are being counted or the glob pattern isn't working as expected in the script.\n\nI'm noticing the script logs \"Skipped(空间不足): 17\" but never reports adding any new entities, so those 17 files shouldn't have been recreated. I think I see it now - the cleanup moves files to the archive, but the wiki-learn script checks if an entity exists using the skill directory name. So if a skill like `claude-code-architecture` was created as `claude-code-architecture.md` and then cleaned up, the script would recreate it because the entity file no longer exists, even though the archive should prevent that.\n\nWait, but the cleanup should only remove files marked as auto-ingested, so manually-created entities like `ai-usage.md` shouldn't be affected. Let me actually verify what's currently in the entities directory to see what's happening.","thinkingSignature":"e21f8f3c8bf0f934ae870a2233daada9a16820c058b9f65b66ec5a6a57e04dd5"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_kskxgdz869c2_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls ~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/entities/ | wc -l && ls ~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/entities/ | sort"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":93217,"output":634,"cacheRead":18887,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":112738,"cost":{"input":0.0279651,"output":0.0007608,"cacheRead":0.0011332199999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.02985912}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776067924490,"responseId":"062bd8539e82bbb5cdf05859f3d7e5c9"}}
