{"type":"message","id":"2f260b87","parentId":"7f64961d","timestamp":"2026-04-13T08:54:57.743Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The error is: \"Channel is required when multiple channels are configured: feishu, openclaw-weixin. Set delivery.channel explicitly or use a main session with a previous channel.\"\n\nThe wiki-learn cron job was created with `sessionTarget: \"isolated\"` and `delivery: { mode: \"announce\" }`. Since there are multiple channels (feishu and openclaw-weixin), it needs a specific channel to deliver to.\n\nThe task itself ran successfully (as seen in the summary: \"实体总数：42，新增：17个新技能实体页...\"). It just failed to deliver the announcement.\n\nI need to fix the cron job's delivery configuration. Since it's a system maintenance job, it should either:\n\n\n- Set `delivery.channel` to a specific channel\n- Or set `delivery.mode: \"none\"` since the log already records what happened\n\nNow I need to check the entities count issue - it's at 41 but should be around 30 after the auto-prune ran during wiki-learn.\n\nLooking at the cron summary, auto-prune removed 17 empty templates and cut it down to 35 targets. But we're still at 41, which suggests 6 more auto-ingested entities got added after the prune ran, or the prune threshold wasn't actually enforced properly when new items were added.\n\nThe timeline shows wiki-learn ran at 16:03 and added 17 new skills, then the prune ran and brought it from 59 down to 35 - that's when the count was 42 before the prune started. So there was a significant cleanup happening, but something changed the count after.\n\nLooking at the error status, it seems the task completed successfully but delivery failed, which means the entities are still sitting at 41. The real issue is that the cron isn't properly configured - the delivery needs a channel specified since there are multiple channels involved. I should either set the channel explicitly or switch delivery mode to \"none\" for this