{"type":"message","id":"4e11240b","parentId":"cff7a36a","timestamp":"2026-04-13T08:55:36.414Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so:\n- 41 entities total\n- 16 are auto-ingested (these are the ones that got re-added when the cron ran at 16:03)\n- The other 25 are manual/active entities\n- 26 skills in the skills directory (the ones that haven't been ingested yet)\n\nThe 16 auto-ingested ones include the claude-code reports that should have been cleaned up. The cron re-created them from the skills/ directory, but it seems the skills/ directory is still populated with the same old entity files.\n\nWait - the skills/ directory has 26 items, and these are directories. The auto-ingested entities in entities/ include:\n\n\n- claude-code-40-tools-complete-report.md\n- claude-code-architecture-overview.md\n- claude-code-architecture.md\n- claude-code-commands.md\n- ...and several others from the claude-code family\n\nBut the skills/ directory I'm looking at doesn't actually contain these markdown files - it's showing me directories like agent-team-orchestration, automation-workflows, and the claude-code variants.\n\nSo I need to figure out where these report files are actually coming from. If skills/ contains 26 directories and entities/ has 16 auto-ingested files, but the report files aren't in skills/, then either they're being generated from somewhere else or I'm misunderstanding how the auto-ingestion is working. Let me trace through the wiki-learn-once.sh script to see if those report files are being pulled from a different source or if the directory scanning logic is finding them somewhere unexpected. the skills/ directory is populated with old entity files that shouldn't be there. If these are truly directories and not files, then when I iterate over them with `*/` to get subdirectories, those old entity files would get picked up and their content would overwrite what's already in entities/. That's the bug — old entity content is being re-ingested as if it were a new skill.\n\nBut I'm confused about why `wc -l < \"$f\"` would work on a directory. Let me check the script logic again to understand what's actually happening when it processes these items.\n\nOh wait — I see the issue now. The `continue` statement checks if something is a directory with `[ -d \"$skill\" ]`, but if those old entity files ARE in the skills/ directory, the loop would try to create files with names that already exist, so the `[ -f \"$ENTITIES/${name}.md\" ]` check would skip them. But that doesn't match what I'm seeing in the output. Let me reconsider what's actually in the skills/ directory and trace through the logic more carefully. I'm realizing these auto-ingested files keep reappearing even after I thought I'd cleared them out, and there's a mismatch between what I'm seeing in the cron summary versus what's actually in the entities directory. Let me trace through the actual counts more carefully — when I manually deleted auto-ingested entities earlier, the directory went down to 25 files, but then the cron job's prune step seems to have restored them back to 41 or 42, which doesn't align with the 35 target it claimed to be working toward. So these auto-ingested files keep getting recreated whenever the cron job runs, which means the skills directory is still populated with them. The real fix is to stop re-adding auto-ingested entities that already exist—if an entity is already in the target directory, skip it instead of overwriting it with the auto-ingested status. This way, manual entities stay manual and the auto-ingested ones don't get re-imported as empty templates.","thinkingSignature":"f787083a6ab6ba8a8b5d92f632479b1f6cded58ecda515f0c437ec2327374a1d"},{"type":"text","text":"问题找到了：skills/ 目录里有旧的 entity 文件（report 类），被脚本当作 skill 目录重复摄入了。需要把 skills/ 里的旧 entity 文件移走：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_uc6eoyzcot8h_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"SKILLS=\"$HOME/.openclaw/workspace/skills\"\n