{"type":"message","id":"f40bc4e8","parentId":"c3776a25","timestamp":"2026-04-13T08:56:17.660Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So skills/ has 26 directories - all real skills. No MD files. That's clean. But then where did the auto-ingested report files come from?\n\nWait - the auto-ingested files in entities/ like `claude-code-40-tools-complete-report.md` are NOT in skills/. So the cron must have re-created them somehow... or they were there from before.\n\nLet me think about this. The entities/ has:\n- 16 auto-ingested (including reports)\n- 25 manual/active\n- Total: 41\n\nWhen I deleted all auto-ingested manually, I got 25. Then the cron ran and added 17 new from skills/ (which has 26 dirs, 9 already ingested). That brought it to 42. \n\nBut the cron claimed it ran the auto-prune down to 35, and I'm at 41 - that's 6 more than expected. Either the prune didn't actually remove all the auto-ingested files, or something else added more entities after. Let me recount the auto-ingested files to see what's actually there.\n\nLooking at the list: agent-team-orchestration, eight claude-code reports, claude-code-architecture, claude-code-commands, claude-code-security, claude-code-telemetry, claude-code-tools, and skill-vetter - that's 16 total. But when the cron ran, it should've removed 17 files as it pruned from 59 down to 42. So either the prune didn't complete fully, or the 9 previously ingested files got re-added as new entities since they're still in skills/.\n\nActually, wait - the cron added 17 NEW files from the skills/ directories, which brought it from 25 to 42. But the entity summary shows it went from 59 to 35 after pruning, which doesn't align with starting from 25. I'm reading the numbers wrong somehow.\n\nLet me reconsider: if the system started with 59 files, removed 24 to get to 35, then added 17 new ones, that would put us at 52 - but we're at 42. The numbers still don't work. Maybe the real issue is that I'm confusing what's actually in entities/ versus what's in skills/, or the deletion and addition happened in a different order than I'm thinking. So the prune threshold of 35 gets exceeded when 17 new entities are added, which then removes 17 auto-ingested files to bring it down to 42. But the numbers still don't quite add up—I need to actually check what's currently in entities/ versus what the cron run reported to figure out where the discrepancy is.\n\nThe real issue is that the auto-ingested entities keep getting recreated every time the cron runs because they're still in skills/. The cron adds new entities, the prune removes the oldest auto-ingested ones, but next time it runs those same entities get re-added from skills/ and then pruned again in a cycle. This is wasteful but not necessarily wrong—the system stabilizes around 42 instead of 30, which is higher than target but not catastrophic.\n\nTo fix this properly, I could either restrict new additions to truly new skills only, or I need to track which entities have been pruned so they don't get re-added. But honestly, the core framework is working—the cron runs, entities get managed, and the system stabilizes. The real problem is that the TARGET of 30 is too low when there are 26 real skills in skills/, so the system naturally wants to be around 30 plus whatever auto-ingested content accumulates. file. If skills/ has 26 directories and 9 are already ingested (having entity files), then 17 new ones would be added = 30 + 17 = 47, then prune 17 = 30. But we're seeing 41...\n\nOK I think I finally get it. Some skills/ directories might have already-created entity files that AREN'T in entities/ because they were removed. Like agent-team-orchestration was removed but the directory in skills/ still exists, so it gets re-added as auto-ingested.\n\nThe cycle is:\n1. Delete auto-ingested from entities/\n2. Cron runs, adds 17 new from skills/ \n3. Cron prunes 17 (the auto-ingested ones)\n4. Cycle repeats\n\nThe solution is to either mark pruned entities so they don't get re-added, or wait—there might only be 17 truly NEW skills, so the system should stabilize once everything's been ingested once.\n\nActually, the cleaner approach: track ingested skills in a file and only ingest truly new ones. Or just accept 41 as the realistic count given 26 skills exist. But there's another possibility—the pruned count of 17 plus the 25 manual entities equals 42, yet we're seeing 41, which suggests one entity was already ingested before the cron ran. Let me check what's actually in entities/ right now to figure out what's really happening.","thinkingSignature":"df7b2985015173a747ef383181d34d196d80f6eb35aa9923a64fb911e8bbd5a3"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_gchdc9gpxj26_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"=== entities/ 当前完整清单(41个) ===\"; ls ~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/entities/ | sort; echo; echo \"=== skills/ 26个目录 ===\"; ls ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/ | sort; echo; echo \"=== 比对：entities中有但skills中无 ===\"; comm -23 <(ls ~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/entities/ | sed 's/.md$//') <(ls ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/) | grep -v \"^$\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":94645,"output":1136,"cacheRead":18887,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":114668,"cost":{"input":0.0283935,"output":0.0013632,"cacheRead":0.0011332199999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.030889919999999998}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776070536528,"responseId":"062be28768bcaf01b68286e0d6468e09"}}
