{"type":"message","id":"df414580","parentId":"9994e1a0","timestamp":"2026-04-13T09:08:54.328Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good news - the entities that were pruned and should be in the blocklist ARE being correctly skipped. The blocklist has the pruned skill names. But entities is 41, which is above 30.\n\nWait - entities with `status: active` are the manual ones (19 of them based on the output). The others must be auto-ingested ones. Let me count: 41 total - 19 active = 22 auto-ingested. But the blocklist has only 9 entries.\n\nThe issue is: the cron ran 6 minutes ago and it was supposed to prune down to 30. But it ended up at 41. This means the blocklist was correct but the prune didn't work properly.\n \nSo the blocklist had 9 entries when the cron ran, but it's now showing 13 entries with duplicates - the blocklist itself got corrupted when new items were appended instead of being properly updated.\n\nLooking at the script logic, when pruning happens it should add items to blocklist AND update the AVAILABLE counter, but I'm seeing a mismatch where the blocklist grew but the available count didn't adjust accordingly. So AVAILABLE starts at 5, and the 16 already-ingested entities consume that budget. Then the script skips adding the 9 blocklisted ones, leaving 17 unaccounted for that should've been blocked by the blocklist mechanism, but they got added anyway—suggesting the grep pattern matching in the blocklist check isn't working as intended.\n\nThe real issue is that blocklist only contains 13 entries now, but the script expects it to handle all the ingested entities that were removed. I need to figure out why the blocklist isn't capturing everything it should.\n\nLooking at the AVAILABLE calculation: TARGET+BUFFER (35) minus CURRENT (41) gives -6, so AVAILABLE is 0 or negative, which means the pruning step should've run. But it seems like the pruning logic isn't actually executing to clear out the older ingested entities before adding new ones.\n\nThe script output shows \"ok\" with 41 entities, which is strange since the prune should bring it down to 30. I'm wondering if the cron job is actually running the new version of the script or if there's something else going on with how the session is being captured and logged.\n\nLooking at the payload, it's running the script directly and appending output to log.md, but the output I'm seeing might be from a different execution than what the cron actually ran. I need to figure out whether the session output matches what was actually executed or if there's a mismatch between what I tested and what ran on schedule.\n\nThe blocklist growing to 13 entries suggests the pruning did run at some point, but the entity count is still at 41, which is puzzling. Let me check the actual log file to see what really happened.","thinkingSignature":"0cec03ce5bd0ae49f4e4a49278048836343f0212ec8316fb3696a2ebfefd8c95"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_n06elv68d3j7_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"tail -5 ~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/log.md 2>/dev/null; echo; echo \"=== blocklist 去重 ===\"; sort -u ~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/.wiki-learn-blocklist > /tmp/bl && mv /tmp/bl ~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/.wiki-learn-blocklist && echo \"blocklist: $(wc -l < ~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/.wiki-learn-blocklist) 个\"; cat ~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/.wiki-learn-blocklist; echo; echo \"=== entities当前 ===\"; ls ~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/entities/ | wc -l"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":110750,"output":719,"cacheRead":18887,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":130356,"cost":{"input":0.033225,"output":0.0008627999999999999,"cacheRead":0.0011332199999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.03522101999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776071308099,"responseId":"062be58bf9414acfb86fa99a3c0d4f4c"}}
