{"type":"message","id":"00700b49","parentId":"7cd12810","timestamp":"2026-04-13T09:09:14.800Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the problem. The log shows `auto-cycle | iter X` which is from the OLD `wiki-7h-loop-v2.sh` script, NOT the new `wiki-learn-once.sh`. The cron is running the old script, not the new one!\n\nThe cron payload is:\n```\n执行 ~/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/wiki-learn-once.sh 并将输出追加到 ~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/log.md\n```\n\nBut the log shows `auto-cycle | iter 5 | sources:35 | fixed:0` which is from the wiki-7h-loop-v2.sh script which has:\n\n\n```\necho \"## [$(date +%Y-%m-%d\\ %H:%M)] auto-cycle | iter $COUNTER | sources:$ENTITY_COUNT | new:$WRITTEN | fixed:$FIXED\" >> $LOG\n```\n\nSo the cron is running the wrong script! The agent is running `wiki-learn-once.sh` but the log shows output from the old `wiki-7h-loop-v2.sh`. There's a disconnect between what the cron is supposed to run and what's actually being executed.\n\nLooking at the log entries with iterations 5, 37, 69, 101, 133 — if each cycle takes 2 minutes, that's roughly 67 minutes total, which matches the ~1 hour between 16:00 and 17:00. But if the old script runs 210 cycles over 7 hours, it should've generated far more iterations than what I'm seeing. The agent might be running the new script successfully while some other process is simultaneously executing the old one, or the log is capturing output from both.\n\nI need to check if there's a second cron job or background process running the old wiki-7h-loop script that I haven't accounted for.","thinkingSignature":"2c2f1ac0fc39a75a11da64d11ec3375e06347bef1fc729cff20a52a11faae86d"},{"type":"text","text":"日志里是 `auto-cycle`（旧 wiki-7h-loop 格式），不是 wiki-learn-once 的格式。cron 在跑旧脚本，不是新脚本。查一下：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_rybhntumtqnc_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"=== 查找 wiki-7h-loop 进程 ===\"; ps aux | grep -E \"wiki-7h|wiki-learn|wiki-trigger\" | grep -v grep |