{"type":"message","id":"c2f001e3","parentId":"448016da","timestamp":"2026-04-13T09:09:24.017Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The cron run at 17:03 for the wiki-learn job was empty (only 1808 bytes). And the `auto-cycle | iter` logs in log.md are from the OLD `wiki-7h-loop-v2.sh` script. But there's no process running that script. The log entries are old - from earlier today when the 7h loop was running.Wait - the log shows `iter 5, 37, 69, 101, 133` at 17:07-17:08. But the 7h-loop-v2.sh only writes when it runs. If there's no process, how did these entries get written?\n\nOH WAIT - I think I understand now. \n\nThe `wiki-7h-loop-v2.sh` script was running in a long session and writing those iterations to the log file over time, so those entries at 17:07-17:08 are just buffered output from that earlier execution. But that session should've exited after 7 hours since it only runs 210 cycles of 2 minutes each, which is about 7 hours total. Let me check when that script actually started.","thinkingSignature":"389322f74540f3f50e28ddf710d00683025a5070cf3225365f531bc1313c6aeb"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_tw9vx1a7ck3l_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep \"^## \" ~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/log.md | tail -10"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":112580,"output":276,"cacheRead":18887,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":131743,"cost":{"input":0.033774,"output":0.0003312,"cacheRead":0.0011332199999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.03523841999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776071354901,"responseId":"062be5b9a1cc62c9b8b0da383037b27b"}}
