{"type":"message","id":"389a2dc2","parentId":"98d59bad","timestamp":"2026-04-13T09:10:04.541Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the problem! There are MULTIPLE instances of `wiki-auto-learn.py` running as background processes from BEFORE (started at 12:44, 13:47, 14:51, 15:55, 16:59)! These are zombie processes that were started by something (maybe the old 7h loop) and they're still running and writing to `logs/wiki-ingest.log`.\n\nAlso, these `wiki-auto-learn.py` processes are writing to `logs/wiki-ingest.log`, not to `memory/log.md`. But the `log.md` has `auto-cycle` entries which are from `wiki-7h-loop-v2.sh`.\n \nWait, I'm looking at the process list more carefully—there's `wiki-auto-learn.py` running multiple times in the background, and there's also `wiki-7h-loop-v2.sh` which is a long-running 7-hour script. Both might be writing to `memory/log.md`, so I need to figure out which one is actually generating those `auto-cycle` entries. I'm realizing the log entries might not be sequential reads at all—they could be from separate runs happening at different times. The `## [2026-04-13 17:07]` timestamp is identical across multiple iterations, which suggests either buffered writes or entries appended while I was examining different parts of the file. Rather than getting caught up in the timeline discrepancy, the real issue is those `wiki-auto-learn.py` zombie processes still running from earlier today and eating up resources. There's also `wiki-learn-once.sh` from the new cron job that's running every hour. Both are likely creating those auto-ingested entity files in memory. My priority should be terminating those orphaned processes and clearing out the entities they've generated. -ingested pages, then clean up the blocklist and restart fresh.\n\nI need to stop all those zombie wiki-auto-learn.py processes, wipe out the auto-ingested entity pages, reset the blocklist to only contain the manually-created ones, and verify the new cron runs correctly without duplicating entities. Let me first identify which entities are auto-ingested versus manually created so I know exactly what to remove.","thinkingSignature":"7641d3a9e3f746624872aaddf4a284b49037247eaba8a25f6a02c09780df7193"},{"type":"text","text":"找到问题：多个 `wiki-auto-learn.py` 僵尸进程还在跑，同时 cron 在跑 wiki-learn-once.sh，两者都在写 entities。清理：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_nbyd4kz7rij4_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"=== 杀所有wiki-auto进程 ===\"\npkill -f \"wiki-auto-learn.py\" 2>/dev/null && echo \"已杀\" || echo \"无进程\"\npkill -f \"wiki-7h-loop\" 2>/dev/null && echo \"已杀7h-loop\" || echo \"无7h-loop\"\n\necho \"\"\necho \"=== 当前entities(41个) - auto-ingested统计 ===\"\ngrep -l \"status: auto-ingested\" ~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/entities/*.md 2>/dev/null | wc -l\necho \"个 auto-ingested\"\n\necho \"\"\necho \"=== 清理auto-ingested ===\"\nARCHIVE=\"$HOME/.openclaw/workspace/memory/entities-archive\"\nmkdir -p \"$ARCHIVE\"\nfor f in ~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/entities/*.md; do\n    [ -f \"$f\" ] || continue\n    if grep -q \"status: auto-ingested\" \"$f\" 2>/dev/null; then\n        mv \"$f\" \"$ARCHIVE/$(basename $f)\"\n    fi\ndone\necho \"清理完成\"\n\necho \"\"\necho \"=== entities剩余 ===\"\nls ~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/entities/ | wc -l\nls ~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/entities/ | sort"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":114436,"output":771,"cacheRead":18887,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":134094,"cost":{"input":0.0343308,"output":0.0009251999999999999,"cacheRead":0.0011332199999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.03638922}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776071381873,"responseId":"062be5d43828fbe898dba177909f82ff"}}
