{"type":"message","id":"0cdc0902","parentId":"5f1e3495","timestamp":"2026-04-13T09:32:49.133Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting! 3105 has a circuit_breaker and it works fine via curl. But the hook's fetchJSON is getting null for classification. \n\nLet me think... The curl works. The node test works. But the actual hook running in the gateway process gets null for classification.\n\nWait - maybe the issue is that the hook is actually running for each message in the CURRENT session (webchat), but the context.json being checked is `agent:main:main`. The hook writes to `agent=main=main` context.json but maybe there's a different session?\n\nActually wait, looking at the context.json path again: `~/.openclaw/sessions/agent:main:main/context.json` - this is where the hook writes. \n\nSo the current session is `agent=main=main` based on the runtime config, and the hook would write to the same path with colons. The timestamp on context.json was just updated at 17:30:59, so it's definitely being written to. But the classification is still null while scoring works - that's the real puzzle. Let me look more carefully at the auto-score-classify hook to see what's different between how it calls 3105 versus 3103.\n\nThe issue could be that 3105 is returning a field the hook doesn't expect, or the response is malformed, or maybe the promise is timing out or the result is being treated as failed. The hook uses `Promise.allSettled` to call both APIs concurrently, so if 3105's promise rejects while 3103 resolves, the classification would be null but scoring would still work. I should actually test whether the hook's fetchJSON function is even reaching 3105 properly, since the curl test works fine but something in the hook's implementation might be failing differently.","thinkingSignature":"896cb67a0148c1cd8de5c1d9f9feb1747b71ca7f19634b03eef3bb2be8f8bce0"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_187l7ytviz6k_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"=== 模拟hook内完整流程 ===\"\nnode -e \"\nconst http = require('http');\n\nfunction fetchJSON(url, body, timeoutMs = 3000) {\n  return new Promise((resolve) => {\n    const postData = JSON.stringify(body);\n    console.error('Fetching:', url, 'body:', JSON.stringify(body).slice(0,50));\n    const req = http.request(url, {\n      method: 'POST',\n      headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json', 'Content-Length': Buffer.byteLength(postData) },\n    }, (res) => {\n      let data = '';\n      res.on('data', (chunk) => (data += chunk));\n      res.on('end', () => { \n        console.error('Status:', res.statusCode, 'Data:', data.slice(0,100));\n        try { resolve(JSON.parse(data)); } catch { resolve(null); } \n      });\n    });\n    req.on('error', (e) => { console.error('NET ERROR:', e.message); resolve(null); });\n    req.setTimeout(timeoutMs, () => { console.error('TIMEOUT'); req.destroy(); resolve(null); });\n    req.write(postData);\n    req.end();\n    setTimeout(() => { try { req.destroy(); } catch {} }, timeoutMs);\n  });\n}\n\nPromise.allSettled([\n  fetchJSON('http://127.0.0.1:3105/classify', { text: '框架检测' }, 3000),\n  fetchJSON('http://127.0.0.1:3103/api/score', { text: '框架检测' }, 3000),\n]).then(([classificationResult, scoringResult]) => {\n  const classification = classificationResult.status === 'fulfilled' ? classificationResult.value : null;\n  const scoring = scoringResult.status === 'fulfilled' ? scoringResult.value : null;\n  console.log('classification:', classification ? 'OK' : 'NULL', '| scoring:', scoring ? 'OK' : 'NULL');\n});\n\" 2>&1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":33079,"output":802,"cacheRead":18887,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":52768,"cost":{"input":0.009923699999999999,"output":0.0009624,"cacheRead":0.0011332199999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.01201932}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776072746445,"responseId":"062beb2a14c83635cf4f84974894e543"}}
{"type":"message","id":"f05e24fb","parentId":"0cdc0902","timestamp":"2026-04-13T09:32:51.225Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_187l7ytviz6k_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"=== 模拟hook内完整流程 ===\nFetching: http://127.0.0.1:3105/classify body: {\"text\":\"框架检测\"}\nFetching: http://127.0.0.1:3103/api/score body: {\"text\":\"框架检测\"}\nStatus: 200 Data: {\"score\":24,\"factors\":{\"logic\":0,\"risk\":0,\"duration\":0,\"resource\":0,\"uncertainty\":0,\"dependency\":1},\nStatus: 200 Data: {\"response\":\"[LLM响应] 基于你的输入，建议操作如下：...\",\"intercepted\":false,\"scene\":\"clarify\",\"meta\":\"ambiguous\",\"co\nclassification: OK | scoring: OK"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":2037,"aggregated":"=== 模拟hook内完整流程 ===\nFetching: http://127.0.0.1:3105/classify body: {\"text\":\"框架检测\"}\nFetching: http://127.0.0.1:3103/api/score body: {\"text\":\"框架检测\"}\nStatus: 200 Data: {\"score\":24,\"factors\":{\"logic\":0,\"risk\":0,\"duration\":0,\"resource\":0,\"uncertainty\":0,\"dependency\":1},\nStatus: 200 Data: {\"response\":\"[LLM响应] 基于你的输入，建议操作如下：...\",\"intercepted\":false,\"scene\":\"clarify\",\"meta\":\"ambiguous\",\"co\nclassification: OK | scoring: OK","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/main"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776072771210}}
{"type":"message","id":"62ba8202","parentId":"f05e24fb","timestamp":"2026-04-13T09:33:07.561Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Both work fine when run as the current user. But the actual hook is getting `classification: null`. This means either:\n\n1. The hook IS failing when running in the gateway's process context\n2. The sessionKey is resolving to something wrong\n3. There's a race condition or timing issue\n\nWait - the context.json file was last modified at 17:30:59 and shows `classification: null`. But the curl/node tests work. The gateway is running as the same user (ai). So why would the hook fail?\n\nLet me check if there's something specific about how the gateway runs hooks. The gateway is `openclaw-gateway` process. Maybe the gateway forks a child process to run the hook, and that child process has a different environment?\n \nThe HOOK.md specifies `\"always\": true` for the auto-score-classify hook on the `message:preprocessed` event, and I can see the context.json was updated at 17:30:59, so the hook definitely ran. But classification is null while scoring has a value. This points to 3105 failing in the actual hook execution even though it works in my tests - possibly a timing issue where the Promise resolves after the context.json write completes.\n\nLooking at the handler code, it constructs the result with both classification and scoring, then writes to context.json before the ephemeral check. If the classification promise hasn't resolved yet when the write happens, it would still show null. But the hook awaits both promises before constructing the result, so that shouldn't be the issue. I need to check the actual context.json content more carefully.","thinkingSignature":"e3b99af6c93f8be45fb5fd071c19fe3c967a8fab496587baa8a62080b0639b91"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_hv5lmjff4r6k_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"=== context.json 完整当前内容 ===\"\ncat ~/.openclaw/sessions/agent\\:main\\:main/