\"Glob\",\n                \"Grep\",\n                \"WebFetch\",\n                \"WebSearch\",\n                \"Mildred\",\n                \"Task*\"\n            ],\n            \"env\": {\n                \"ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL\": \"https://zhenze-huhehaote.cmecloud.cn/api/coding/v1\",\n                \"ANTHROPIC_AUTH_TOKEN\": \"J99ouXWKXO8Zg5tLqv92YVsPNFhwuZc-z6z2ioeg7VE\",\n                \"ANTHROPIC_MODEL\": \"minimax-m2.5\"\n            }\n        }\n    },\n    \"models\": {\n        \"providers\": {\n            \"ollama\": {\n                \"baseUrl\": \"http://172.23.96.1:11434\",\n\n=== 3104 端口占用 ===\nLISTEN    0         511               127.0.0.1:3104             0.0.0.0:*       users:((\"openclaw-gatewa\",pid=97397,fd=39))                                    \n\n=== openclaw-router 状态 ===\n{\"messages\":0,\"chars\":0}","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/main"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776072817604}}
{"type":"message","id":"7254080a","parentId":"3515b55e","timestamp":"2026-04-13T09:33:55.190Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK, so:1. `config.json` correctly points to 3105 for sceneClassifier ✅\n2. 3104 is bound by `openclaw-gateway` (pid 97397) internally - this is the gateway's internal endpoint\n3. openclaw-router (pid 434) on 3101 has 0 messages and isn't being used effectively\n\nNow back to the main issue: context.json has `classification: null` for every message. This is a BUG. Let me think more carefully...\n\nActually, wait. Looking at the HOOK.md for auto-score-classify:\n```yaml\nevents: [\"message:preprocessed\"]\n```\n\n\"message:preprocessed\" is BEFORE the agent processes the message. \n\nThe hook fires on every preprocessed message, but here's the issue - it writes to a hardcoded session path `~/.openclaw/sessions/{sessionKey}/context.json`. For the current session `agent=main=main`, it's writing to `agent:main:main/context.json`. The webchat session should be different from the agent session, so the hook might be writing to the wrong place entirely.\n\nActually, looking at the current state - `agent:main:main/context.json` exists and shows `classification: null` with a recent timestamp, which means the hook IS running. But it's writing null for classification even though the curl to 3105 works. This could be a timing issue where the HTTP request to 3105 is slow and the promise hasn't resolved yet when the handler tries to write to the file, even with `Promise.allSettled`. Or the hook might be running in an isolated context where 3105 isn't accessible from the network namespace where the gateway is running. Let me trace through the actual handler code to see what's happening - it checks for the right event type and action, extracts the message text, and then constructs the result object, so I need to see if the issue is in how it's calling the classifier or handling the response.","thinkingSignature":"62b27e7cd1b35730daca766a2903e8b95ab5700115675219352c8979b451a571"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_xqqsb8ge8tpv_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"=== 强制触发一次classification ===\"\n# 手动发一个有意义的消息测试\ncurl -s -X POST http://localhost:3105/classify \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\"text\":\"这段要记住：我的名字是小Claw\"}' 2>/dev/null\n\necho \"\"\necho \"=== 当前session key 确认 ===\"\ncat ~/.openclaw/sessions/agent\\:main\\:main/context.json | python3 -c \"\nimport sys, json\nd = json.load(sys.stdin)\nprint('timestamp:', d.get('timestamp'))\nprint('preview:', d.get('messagePreview','')[:50])\nprint('classification type:', type(d.get('classification')))\nprint('scoring OK:', d.get('scoring') is not None)\n\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":35956,"output":590,"cacheRead":18887,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":55433,"cost":{"input":0.0107868,"output":0.000708,"cacheRead":0.0011332199999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.01262802}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776072817621,"responseId":"062beb70235735fa332a39da125f976a"}}
