{"type":"message","id":"d87b2320","parentId":"1ab52163","timestamp":"2026-04-13T09:34:10.836Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_laakku5uciy5_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"=== handler.js 第1-50行 ===\n// auto-score-classify hook\n// Concurrent classification (3105) + scoring (3103) on every inbound message\n// + ephemeral memory capture for meaningful messages\n\nimport fs from \"node:fs\";\nimport path from \"node:path\";\nimport http from \"node:http\";\n\nasync function fetchJSON(url, body, timeoutMs = 3000) {\n  return new Promise((resolve) => {\n    const postData = JSON.stringify(body);\n    const req = http.request(\n      url,\n      {\n        method: \"POST\",\n        headers: { \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\", \"Content-Length\": Buffer.byteLength(postData) },\n      },\n      (res) => {\n        let data = \"\";\n        res.on(\"data\", (chunk) => (data += chunk));\n        res.on(\"end\", () => {\n          try { resolve(JSON.parse(data)); }\n          catch { resolve(null); }\n        });\n      }\n    );\n    req.on(\"error\", () => resolve(null));\n    req.setTimeout(timeoutMs, () => { req.destroy(); resolve(null); });\n    req.write(postData);\n    req.end();\n    setTimeout(() => { try { req.destroy(); } catch {} }, timeoutMs);\n  });\n}\n\nasync function runClassification(text) {\n  return fetchJSON(\"http://127.0.0.1:3105/classify\", { text }, 3000);\n}\n\nasync function runScoring(prompt) {\n  return fetchJSON(\"http://127.0.0.1:3103/api/score\", { prompt }, 3000);\n}\n\nfunction ensureDir(dir) {\n  if (!fs.existsSync(dir)) {\n    fs.mkdirSync(dir, { recursive: true });\n  }\n}\n\n// ─── Meaningfulness filter ───────────────────────────────────────────────────\nconst MEANINGFUL_PATTERNS = ["}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":53,"aggregated":"=== handler.js 第1-50行 ===\n// auto-score-classify hook\n// Concurrent classification (3105) + scoring (3103) on every inbound message\n// + ephemeral memory capture for meaningful messages\n\nimport fs from \"node:fs\";\nimport path from \"node:path\";\nimport http from \"node:http\";\n\nasync function fetchJSON(url, body, timeoutMs = 3000) {\n  return new Promise((resolve) => {\n    const postData = JSON.stringify(body);\n    const req = http.request(\n      url,\n      {\n        method: \"POST\",\n        headers: { \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\", \"Content-Length\": Buffer.byteLength(postData) },\n      },\n      (res) => {\n        let data = \"\";\n        res.on(\"data\", (chunk) => (data += chunk));\n        res.on(\"end\", () => {\n          try { resolve(JSON.parse(data)); }\n          catch { resolve(null); }\n        });\n      }\n    );\n    req.on(\"error\", () => resolve(null));\n    req.setTimeout(timeoutMs, () => { req.destroy(); resolve(null); });\n    req.write(postData);\n    req.end();\n    setTimeout(() => { try { req.destroy(); } catch {} }, timeoutMs);\n  });\n}\n\nasync function runClassification(text) {\n  return fetchJSON(\"http://127.0.0.1:3105/classify\", { text }, 3000);\n}\n\nasync function runScoring(prompt) {\n  return fetchJSON(\"http://127.0.0.1:3103/api/score\", { prompt }, 3000);\n}\n\nfunction ensureDir(dir) {\n  if (!fs.existsSync(dir)) {\n    fs.mkdirSync(dir, { recursive: true });\n  }\n}\n\n// ─── Meaningfulness filter ───────────────────────────────────────────────────\nconst MEANINGFUL_PATTERNS = [","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/main"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776072850823}}
{"type":"message","id":"23736159","parentId":"d87b2320","timestamp":"2026-04-13T09:34:41.432Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait - I see the issue! Look at line 47 vs line 44:\n```javascript\nasync function runClassification(text) {\n  return fetchJSON(\"http://127.0.0.1:3105/classify\", { text }, 3000);\n}\n\nasync function runScoring(prompt) {\n  return fetchJSON(\"http://127.0.0.1:3103/api/score\", { prompt }, 3000);\n}\n```\n\nClassification takes `text` as parameter, scoring takes `prompt` as parameter! Both call fetchJSON with the same body structure `{ text: ... }` or `{ prompt: ... \n\n}`.\n\nBut 3103's actual API expects a `prompt` field based on what we see in context.json (it returns a valid score=24). So the field name difference between `text` and `prompt` might not matter for 3103 since it's returning the same result either way.\n\nThe real problem is that classification keeps coming back as null while scoring works fine. Both should fail or succeed together since they're using the same fetchJSON logic, but 3105 is returning null for classification. Let me actually verify what the 3105 API returns for different input formats to understand why one succeeds and the other fails.\n\nWait—I think I see the issue now. The node test runs in a different network context than the hook does when it's loaded as an ES module. The hook imports the fetchJSON function at the top level, so it might be using a different runtime configuration that breaks the HTTP request to 3105.\n\nBut actually, both curl and node can reach 3105 fine, so it's not a general network issue. Let me reconsider: if 3103 is returning a valid score, then the hook itself is definitely running and the http module works. So the problem must be specific to the 3105 call itself—maybe there's something different about how the request is being made or the response is being parsed when the hook runs.\n\nWait, I think I see it now. The HOOK.md specifies `message:preprocessed` as the event, but the hook checks for `event.type === \"message\"` and `event.action === \"preprocessed\"`. If the gateway's event format doesn't match what the hook expects, the handler would exit early and never update context.json. Yet the file was just modified, so something is clearly running.\n\nLet me focus on the actual problem: 3105 is returning null while 3103 works fine. Both use the same fetchJSON function, so the issue might be specific to how 3105 handles the request or parses the response. Let me trace through what's actually happening with that particular endpoint.\n\nThe 3105 response contains Chinese characters in the \"response\" field, which could cause character encoding issues during JSON parsing. Though `JSON.parse` should handle UTF-8 fine, and my curl test confirmed the parsing works correctly. But wait—the `MessagePreview` field in context.json shows `\\u7280\\u5229` which is garbled Chinese, suggesting the text field itself might be corrupted or double-encoded somewhere in the request pipeline. the double-encoding is happening at the gateway level before the hook even receives the message, not within the hook's JSON handling itself. This would explain why 3103 succeeds with `{ text: \"...\" }` but 3105 fails with null - they're processing different versions of the same corrupted text string.\n\nSince this is getting too speculative without more debugging, let me step back and do a systematic review of the actual problems instead of chasing the root cause of this one particular issue.\n\nLooking at what's clearly broken: context.json has classification set to null, which means the classification pipeline is dead. I should also check whether on-message.sh is actually being triggered and if those context messages are even reaching the hook. Meanwhile, openclaw-router has been sitting at zero messages since it was fixed to point to 3101, so either the hook isn't firing or nothing is sending it messages. Let me focus on identifying which issues are actually actionable versus which ones might be working as intended.","thinkingSignature":"a23676a8626a885134555b91be8aadacc265cf3e14c5cbd0b5b2ab514caec0c7"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_g8o9ke28iovn_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"=== auto-score-classify hook 完整代码 ===\"\ncat ~/.openclaw/hooks/auto-score-classify/handler.js"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":37438,"output":885,"cacheRead":18887,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":57210,"cost":{"input":0.011231399999999999,"output":0.001062,"cacheRead":0.0011332199999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.01342662}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776072850837,"responseId":"062beb91bbfe7bf2dd68e91305ef415c"}}
{"type":"message","id":"2cc22b53","parentId":"23736159","timestamp":"2026-04-13T09:34:41.547Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_g8o9ke28iovn_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"=== auto-score-classify hook 完整代码 ===\n// auto-score-classify hook\n// Concurrent classification (3105) + scoring (3103) on every inbound message\n// + ephemeral memory capture for meaningful messages\n\nimport fs from \"node:fs\";\nimport path from \"node:path\";\nimport http from \"node:http\";\n\nasync function fetchJSON(url, body, timeoutMs = 3000) {\n  return new Promise((resolve) => {\n    const postData = JSON.stringify(body);\n    const req = http.request(\n      url,\n      {\n        method: \"POST\",\n        headers: { \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\", \"Content-Length\": Buffer.byteLength(postData) },\n      },\n      (res) => {\n        let data = \"\";\n        res.on(\"data\", (chunk) => (data += chunk));\n        res.on(\"end\", () => {\n          try { resolve(JSON.parse(data)); }\n          catch { resolve(null); }\n        });\n      }\n    );\n    req.on(\"error\", () => resolve(null));\n    req.setTimeout(timeoutMs, () => { req.destroy(); resolve(null); });\n    req.write(postData);\n    req.end();\n    setTimeout(() => { try { req.destroy(); } catch {} }, timeoutMs);\n  });\n}\n\nasync function runClassification(text) {\n  return fetchJSON(\"http://127.0.0.1:3105/classify\", { text }, 3000);\n}\n\nasync function runScoring(prompt) {\n  return fetchJSON(\"http://127.0.0.1:3103/api/score\", { prompt }, 3000);\n}\n\nfunction ensureDir(dir) {\n  if (!fs.existsSync(dir)) {\n    fs.mkdirSync(dir, { recursive: true });\n  }\n}\n\n// ─── Meaningfulness filter ───────────────────────────────────────────────────\nconst MEANINGFUL_PATTERNS = [\n  /记住|以后都|决定用|别用|改用|这个要记|记下来/,\n];\n\nfunction isMeaningful(text, classification, scoring) {\n  const c = classification || {};\n  const s = scoring || {};\n  \n  // 1. Explicit user intent\n  if (MEANINGFUL_PATTERNS.some(p => p.test(text))) return true;\n  \n  // 2. System-level important\n  if (c.intercepted === true) return true;\n  if (c.scene === 'fault_recovery') return true;\n  \n  // 3. High risk (>=3)\n  if ((s.factors?.risk || 0) >= 3) return true;\n  \n  // 4. MEGA task\n  if (s.recommendedStrategy === 'MEGA_TASK') return true;\n  \n  return false;\n}\n\n// ─── Ephemeral memory writer ──────────────────────────────────────────────────\nconst EPHEMERAL_DIR = path.join(\n  process.env.OPENCLAW_WORKSPACE_DIR || path.join(process.env.HOME || \"/home/ai\", \".openclaw\", \"workspace\"),\n  \"memory\",\n  \"ephemeral\"\n);\n\nfunction writeEphemeral(entry) {\n  try {\n    ensureDir(EPHEMERAL_DIR);\n    // File per hour: YYYY-MM-DD-HH.jsonl\n    const now = new Date();\n    const hourStr = now.toISOString().slice(0, 13).replace('T', '-');\n    const filePath = path.join(EPHEMERAL_DIR, `${hourStr}.jsonl`);\n    const line = JSON.stringify(entry) + '\\n';\n    fs.appendFileSync(filePath, line, 'utf-8');\n  } catch (e) {\n    // Silently ignore write errors - ephemeral should not break main flow\n  }\n}\n\n// ─── Main handler ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nexport default async function handler(event) {\n  if (event.type !== \"message\" || event.action !== \"preprocessed\") {\n    return;\n  }\n\n  const text = event.context?.bodyForAgent || \"\";\n  if (!text || text.trim().length === 0) return;\n\n  const sessionKey = event.sessionKey || \"default\";\n  const sessionDir = path.join(process.env.HOME || \"/home/ai\", \".openclaw/sessions\", sessionKey);\n  ensureDir(sessionDir);\n\n  const [classificationResult, scoringResult] = await Promise.allSettled([\n    runClassification(text),\n    runScoring(text),\n  ]);\n\n  const classification = classificationResult.status === \"fulfilled\" ? classificationResult.value : null;\n  const scoring = scoringResult.status === \"fulfilled\" ? scoringResult.value : null;\n\n  const result = {\n    classification,\n    scoring,\n    timestamp: new Date().toISOString(),\n    messagePreview: text.slice(0, 120),\n  };\n\n  const outPath = path.join(sessionDir, \"context.json\");\n  try {\n    fs.writeFileSync(outPath, JSON.stringify(result, null, 2), \"utf-8\");\n  } catch {\n    // ignore write errors silently\n  }\n\n  // ─── Ephemeral memory capture ─────────────────────────────────────────────\n  if (isMeaningful(text, classification, scoring)) {\n    writeEphemeral({\n      timestamp: new Date().toISOString(),\n      sessionKey,\n      text,\n      textPreview: text.length > 200 ? text.slice(0, 200) + '...' : text,\n      classification,\n      scoring,\n    });\n  }\n}"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":53,"aggregated":"=== auto-score-classify hook 完整代码 ===\n// auto-score-classify hook\n// Concurrent classification (3105) + scoring (3103) on every inbound message\n// + ephemeral memory capture for meaningful messages\n\nimport fs from \"node:fs\";\nimport path from \"node:path\";\nimport http from \"node:http\";\n\nasync function fetchJSON(url, body, timeoutMs = 3000) {\n  return new Promise((resolve) => {\n    const postData = JSON.stringify(body);\n    const req = http.request(\n      url,\n      {\n        method: \"POST\",\n        headers: { \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\", \"Content-Length\": Buffer.byteLength(postData) },\n      },\n      (res) => {\n        let data = \"\";\n        res.on(\"data\", (chunk) => (data += chunk));\n        res.on(\"end\", () => {\n          try { resolve(JSON.parse(data)); }\n          catch { resolve(null); }\n        });\n      }\n    );\n    req.on(\"error\", () => resolve(null));\n    req.setTimeout(timeoutMs, () => { req.destroy(); resolve(null); });\n    req.write(postData);\n    req.end();\n    setTimeout(() => { try { req.destroy(); } catch {} }, timeoutMs);\n  });\n}\n\nasync function runClassification(text) {\n  return fetchJSON(\"http://127.0.0.1:3105/classify\", { text }, 3000);\n}\n\nasync function runScoring(prompt) {\n  return fetchJSON(\"http://127.0.0.1:3103/api/score\", { prompt }, 3000);\n}\n\nfunction ensureDir(dir) {\n  if (!fs.existsSync(dir)) {\n    fs.mkdirSync(dir, { recursive: true });\n  }\n}\n\n// ─── Meaningfulness filter ───────────────────────────────────────────────────\nconst MEANINGFUL_PATTERNS = [\n  /记住|以后都|决定用|别用|改用|这个要记|记下来/,\n];\n\nfunction isMeaningful(text, classification, scoring) {\n  const c = classification || {};\n  const s = scoring || {};\n  \n  // 1. Explicit user intent\n  if (MEANINGFUL_PATTERNS.some(p => p.test(text))) return true;\n  \n  // 2. System-level important\n  if (c.intercepted === true) return true;\n  if (c.scene === 'fault_recovery') return true;\n  \n  // 3. High risk (>=3)\n  if ((s.factors?.risk || 0) >= 3) return true;\n  \n  // 4. MEGA task\n  if (s.recommendedStrategy === 'MEGA_TASK') return true;\n  \n  return false;\n}\n\n// ─── Ephemeral memory writer ──────────────────────────────────────────────────\nconst EPHEMERAL_DIR = path.join(\n  process.env.OPENCLAW_WORKSPACE_DIR || path.join(process.env.HOME || \"/home/ai\", \".openclaw\", \"workspace\"),\n  \"memory\",\n  \"ephemeral\"\n);\n\nfunction writeEphemeral(entry) {\n  try {\n    ensureDir(EPHEMERAL_DIR);\n    // File per hour: YYYY-MM-DD-HH.jsonl\n    const now = new Date();\n    const hourStr = now.toISOString().slice(0, 13).replace('T', '-');\n    const filePath = path.join(EPHEMERAL_DIR, `${hourStr}.jsonl`);\n    const line = JSON.stringify(entry) + '\\n';\n    fs.appendFileSync(filePath, line, 'utf-8');\n  } catch (e) {\n    // Silently ignore write errors - ephemeral should not break main flow\n  }\n}\n\n// ─── Main handler ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nexport default async function handler(event) {\n  if (event.type !== \"message\" || event.action !== \"preprocessed\") {\n    return;\n  }\n\n  const text = event.context?.bodyForAgent || \"\";\n  if (!text || text.trim().length === 0) return;\n\n  const sessionKey = event.sessionKey || \"default\";\n  const sessionDir = path.join(process.env.HOME || \"/home/ai\", \".openclaw/sessions\", sessionKey);\n  ensureDir(sessionDir);\n\n  const [classificationResult, scoringResult] = await Promise.allSettled([\n    runClassification(text),\n    runScoring(text),\n  ]);\n\n  const classification = classificationResult.status === \"fulfilled\" ? classificationResult.value : null;\n  const scoring = scoringResult.status === \"fulfilled\" ? scoringResult.value : null;\n\n  const result = {\n    classification,\n    scoring,\n    timestamp: new Date().toISOString(),\n    messagePreview: text.slice(0, 120),\n  };\n\n  const outPath = path.join(sessionDir, \"context.json\");\n  try {\n    fs.writeFileSync(outPath, JSON.stringify(result, null, 2), \"utf-8\");\n  } catch {\n    // ignore write errors silently\n  }\n\n  // ─── Ephemeral memory capture ─────────────────────────────────────────────\n  if (isMeaningful(text, classification, scoring)) {\n    writeEphemeral({\n      timestamp: new Date().toISOString(),\n      sessionKey,\n      text,\n      textPreview: text.length > 200 ? text.slice(0, 200) + '...' : text,\n      classification,\n      scoring,\n    });\n  }\n}","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/main"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776072881536}}
{"type":"message","id":"7fa6b9e0","parentId":"2cc22b53","timestamp":"2026-04-13T09:35:08.527Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I notice something about the handler - it doesn't await the Promise.allSettled before writing context.json. Wait, actually it does:```javascript\nconst [classificationResult, scoringResult] = await Promise.allSettled([...]);\n```\n\nThis IS awaited. So the classification and scoring must both resolve before the write.\n\nBut context.json shows `classification: null` and scoring is non-null. This is very strange.\n\nLet me try a different approach - let me add some debugging to the hook and see what happens. But actually, the user wants me to be critical, not to fix things. Let me think about what could cause this.\n\nWait - I just realized something. \n\nThe context.json file was modified at 17:30:59, which corresponds to the message \"犀利、严格的进行评审、检查\". But when I look at the actual content, the timestamp is \"2026-04-13T09:30:59.115Z\" in the file, and the messagePreview shows \"\\u7280\\u5229\" - which decodes to \"犀利\". So the hook definitely wrote something, but there's a mismatch between what I expected and what's actually there.\n\nThe real issue is that classification is null even though 3105 returned a valid response, and the messagePreview is double-encoded Unicode. Both the scoring and classification calls should be completing successfully since the timestamp, preview, and scoring fields are all populated, yet classification remains null. Let me trace through the actual handler to see what's happening.\n\nI notice the handler is using `Promise.allSettled` which means both calls run concurrently, but the gateway might be invoking the hook differently than expected. Rather than getting bogged down in debugging this further, I should move on to the actual review since the issue could be a timeout or encoding problem that's already been partially addressed.\n\nFor the next step, I need to systematically check each component: the 18790 port that was dead and should now be fixed, the 3105 classification pipeline that's producing null values, the openclaw-router with its inactive context-api, the memory.log showing old wiki-auto-learn entries, and whether the cron jobs are functioning correctly.","thinkingSignature":"ed6222184e0505d8e218ea500b002da5e4375f66f3df044e8c743a7cef6612aa"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_00m0r95ba5uw_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"=== wiki-learn cron 最近执行输出 ===\"\n~/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/bin/openclaw cron runs b3c6834e-c671-4b21-b6d4-0dc9c86f0e84 2>/dev/null | head -20\n\necho \"\"\necho \"=== memory-keeper cron 最近执行 ===\"\n~/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/bin/openclaw cron runs e3ff05f4-6d75-4c58-8f4c-d4de23b82ab1 2>/dev/null | head -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":39450,"output":592,"cacheRead":18887,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":58929,"cost":{"input":0.011835,"output":0.0007103999999999999,"cacheRead":0.0011332199999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.013678619999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776072881551,"responseId":"062bebb598c0d9bb4a021623ea793170"}}
