{"type":"message","id":"7e747d27","parentId":"e9f3026f","timestamp":"2026-04-13T09:35:29.921Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see multiple issues from the log:\n\n1. `auto-cycle` and `wiki-learn` entries are interleaved in the same log.md - this means there are TWO processes running simultaneously: the old wiki-auto-learn.py (which writes `auto-cycle | iter`) and the new wiki-learn-once.sh (which writes `wiki-learn | entities:`). But I thought I killed all the wiki-auto-learn.py processes. Let me check.\n\n2. The `wiki-learn` cron is running every hour (at :02 minutes past each hour) and writing `entities:30` or `entities:35`. \n\nBut 17:10 shows entities:35 with 10 new items, which is odd since the cron only ran 3 times between 16:57 and 17:10 - I need to figure out where those extra `auto-cycle` entries are coming from, especially since there are 127 iterations logged at 16:57 alone.\n\nLooking more carefully at the timestamps, the `auto-cycle` entries at 17:02-17:09 have no date prefix, just times, which suggests they're from a different source than the `wiki-learn` entries that do have full timestamps. I should check if the old `wiki-auto-learn.py` process is still running or if there's a second instance I'm not aware of.","thinkingSignature":"4250e5ba92c35ff1c0d5dd1355edee0a39594bcea2fa54e879b537a54d244d78"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_20lomfompc3n_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"=== wiki-auto-learn.py 进程 ===\"\nps aux | grep \"wiki-auto\\|wiki-learn\" | grep -v grep\n\necho \"\"\necho \"=== cron job 实际命令 ===\"\n~/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/bin/openclaw cron list 2>/dev/null | grep -A1 \"wiki-learn\"\n\necho \"\"\necho \"=== 17:02-17:09 auto-cycle 进程 ===\"\nps aux | grep -E \"python3.*wiki|wiki.*python3\" | grep -v grep"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":40637,"output":406,"cacheRead":18887,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":59930,"cost":{"i