{"type":"message","id":"c5958e9d","parentId":"fd7c6183","timestamp":"2026-04-13T09:36:07.774Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So there are no wiki-auto-learn.py processes running now, but the log shows auto-cycle entries. The auto-cycle entries might be from BEFORE I killed the processes. Let me look at the timestamps more carefully.\n\nActually, looking at the log output again:\n```\n## [2026-04-13 16:57] auto-cycle | iter 127 | sources:35 | fixed:0\n## [2026-04-13 16:57] wiki-learn | entities:30 | new:0 | skip(block):0 | skip(space):17 | fixed:0\n## [2026-04-13 17:02] auto-cycle | iter 130 | sources:35 | fixed:0\n[2026-04-13 17:02:48] === wiki-learn-once 启动 ===\n\n\n## [2026-04-13 17:02] wiki-learn | entities:30 | new:0 | skip(block):0 | skip(space):17 | fixed:0\n[2026-04-13 17:02:50] === wiki-learn-once 完成 ===\n## [2026-04-13 17:09] auto-cycle | iter 102 | sources:35 | fixed:0\n## [2026-04-13 17:10] wiki-learn | entities:35 | new:10 | skip(block):0 | skip(space):14 | fixed:0\n```\n\nThe timestamps show auto-cycle entries appearing right before and after wiki-learn entries, which suggests they're being logged in sequence rather than from separate processes. The old auto-cycle process was writing to log.md every few seconds at 16:57, which stopped once I killed it at 17:00. The wiki-learn cron continued running and produced its own entries at 17:02 and 17:10. Now I'm doing a thorough review of the system—the context.json classification is null even though curl and node tests to 3105 work fine, which is suspicious. I also notice the context-api on 3101 has received zero messages, meaning on-message.sh probably isn't sending anything to it.\n\nLooking at the HOOK.md, on-message.sh should be triggered by message events through a separate context-hook.js mechanism. I need to check if that's actually configured and working. The log.md is also cluttered with auto-cycle entries every 10 seconds, though that should stop now that the old process is gone. The session directory shows zero message history for the current session, which suggests the session might not have persisted properly.\n\nThe session summary hook should have written something when the session started, but the current session at `agent=main=main` only has the context.json that was just modified. I'm trying to figure out if this is actually the session created by the /new command or if it's a different one, since the session structure seems unclear.","thinkingSignature":"c5c2204f8471d6a6caf795e1899bb9e768dcfe6491ca3d5a2033654335e27abb"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_p91x6tcxgerj_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"=== session 目录详情 ===\"\nls -la ~/.openclaw/sessions/agent\\:main\\:main/\necho \"\"\nls ~/.openclaw/sessions/agent\\:main\\:main/ | head -10\n\necho \"\"\necho \"=== runtime session key ===\"\necho \"agent=main=main\"\n\necho \"\"\necho \"=== session 创建时间 ===\"\nstat ~/.openclaw/sessions/agent\\:main\\:main/ | grep -E \"Birth|Modify\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":41316,"output":705,"cacheRead":18887,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":60908,"cost":{"input":0.0123948,"output":0.000846,"cacheRead":0.0011332199999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.014374019999999998}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776072947202,"responseId":"062bebf2c0abb4be36982ab58d9d3186"}}
