{"type":"message","id":"ec450899","parentId":"454b530c","timestamp":"2026-04-13T09:36:34.581Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting! The `agent=main=main` session directory was created at 01:42 (AM), not when the user did /new today. And it only has a `context.json` - no message history JSONL file. \n\nThis is strange. The session for this current conversation doesn't have a message history file. Let me check the `agent=fast_agent:main` session.Actually, looking at the runtime info at the top:```\nRuntime: agent=main | host=ai | repo=/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/main | os=Linux```\n\nThe session is `agent=main` (not agent=main=main). \n\nSo the runtime session key is `agent=main`, and the session directory might be stored differently. Looking at the session directory, it seems like the current webchat session is `agent=main` (which maps to `agent=main:main` in the sessions directory), created at 01:42 this morning. But that doesn't align with when the user actually started this conversation today. Let me figure out where the actual message history is being stored for this webchat session.\n\nThe session has no message history JSONL file—just the context.json that the hook writes to. When I look at `sessions_list`, it shows this is a direct webchat. So it seems like message history might not be persisted locally in JSONL files for this type of session, or the hook's session directory resolution is mapping to the wrong place. The context.json in `agent=main=main` gets updated by the hook, but I'm not sure if that's actually where this conversation's messages are being stored.\n\nLet me compile what I've found. The auto-score-classify hook has a critical bug where classification always returns null—the hook writes to context.json but never actually populates the classification field, yet the 3105 endpoint itself works fine. Meanwhile, openclaw-router's context-api at port 3101 has never received any messages, which means on-message.sh isn't sending to it despite the port being fixed. And there's an old auto-cycle process that was writing to log.md every few seconds—I killed it, but I need to verify it's actually gone.\n\nThe session directories themselves look malformed: `agent=main=main` contains a context.json but no message history, which is anomalous. There's also a mismatch with session-summary where I'm writing to a hardcoded path like `memory/2026-04-13-session-summary.md` while the hook expects a different location.\n\nFor the ephemeral layer, I'm seeing only 9 total entries across all files when there should be more captures from today. The fact that context.json was updated at 17:30:59 for the \"犀利\" message means the hook is firing, but the classification call itself appears to be failing silently.\n\nLet me add some debugging to the hook to trace where the classification is breaking down.","thinkingSignature":"6a2ed6c46e573d82ab46826fb6779458808564d6cb2e1c620c282efc804b5518"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_kar4pc1i209c_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"=== 强制写测试ephemeral ===\"\necho '{\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-13T09:35:00.000Z\",\"sessionKey\":\"test\",\"text\":\"test\",\"textPreview\":\"test\",\"classification\":{\"scene\":\"task\",\"confidence\":0.9},\"scoring\":{\"score\":50}}' >> ~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/ephemeral/2026-04-13-09.jsonl\n\necho \"=== ephemeral 09点UTC当前 ===\"\nwc -l ~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/ephemeral/2026-04-13-09.jsonl\ntail -2 ~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/ephemeral/2026-04-13-09.jsonl | python3 -c \"import sys,json; [print(json.loads(l).get('textPreview','')) for l in sys.stdin]\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":42152,"output":793,"cacheRead":18887,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":61832,"cost":{"input":0.0126456,"output":0.0009515999999999999,"cacheRead":0.0011332199999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.014730420000000001}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776072967875,"responseId":"062bec0709ca0ad10709abb032c973c2"}}
