{"type":"message","id":"7258785d","parentId":"7ebeb89f","timestamp":"2026-04-13T09:37:05.965Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting! The node test with the exact same code returns OK from 3105. So the code works when run from command line.But the hook's context.json consistently shows `classification: null`. This means the hook is either:\n1. Running but the 3105 request fails for some reason specific to the hook's execution environment2. The hook isn't actually running for the current messages (even though context.json was modified)\n\nWait - context.json WAS modified at 17:30:59. And the node test works. So there must be something different about how the hook runs inside the gateway process.\n\nLet me try a completely different hypothesis: maybe the hook is using an outdated version of the handler.js. \n\nI should verify which version of the auto-score-classify hook is actually registered with the gateway right now. If the gateway cached an old version before my fix, it would still be running the old code that points to 3108 instead of 3105. Let me check the gateway's hook configuration to see what's actually being executed.","thinkingSignature":"9a6d3ffec34958428e19c985959c310b6c859a92b48e18706f12b7ad3e561730"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_46b2jy6irh36_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"=== gateway 实际加载的hook配置 ===\"\ncurl -s -H \"Authorization: Bearer $(cat ~/.openclaw/config.json | python3 -c 'import sys,json; print(json.load(sys.stdin).get(\"gatewayToken\",\"\"))' 2>/dev/null)\" \\\n  http://localhost:3001/api/hooks 2>/dev/null | python3 -m json.tool 2>/dev/null | head -40"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43735,"output":326,"cacheRead":18887,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":62948,"cost":{"input":0.0131205,"output":0.00039119999999999997,"cacheRead":0.0011332199999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.014644919999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse",