{"type":"message","id":"74fc08be","parentId":"20616a67","timestamp":"2026-04-13T09:42:14.895Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to fix the issues I identified. Let me focus on the two critical issues:\n\n1. **classification null** - hook is writing null for classification\n2. **on-message.sh never triggered** - context-api gets 0 messages\n\nLet me start by understanding why classification is null. The gateway's hook calls 3105 but gets null. Let me look at this from a different angle - maybe the issue is with how the hook's `handler` function is being called by the gateway.\n\nLet me check if the hook is actually registered correctly and if the gateway is calling it properly. Also, let me try to restart the gateway to force reload the hooks.\n \nI think I see it now - the hook was originally hardcoded to call 3104, but we changed it to 3105. The problem is the gateway process is still running the old cached version with the 3104 reference. I need to restart the gateway to pick up the hook file changes.\n\nBut wait, actually the hook is a separate file that gets loaded dynamically, not compiled into the gateway binary. So even after restart, if the gateway reads the hook file fresh each time, it should pick up the 3105 change. Unless... the hook handler has some kind of caching or the file read is happening at startup only.\n\nLet me trace through what I actually changed - it was just the URL in the handler.js file from 3108 to 3105. The question is whether the gateway reloads hooks dynamically or only at startup. Given that the classification has been null for a while despite the fix, I'm thinking either the gateway isn't picking up the change or there's something else going on with how the classification result gets handled after the request completes.\n\nI should probably restart the gateway to force a clean reload of the hook, and also look at whether the auto-score-classify hook is even being invoked corr