{"type":"message","id":"9189591e","parentId":"7c483970","timestamp":"2026-04-13T10:14:20.901Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"There's no `hooks` key in config.json. That explains why the hooks aren't firing properly. The gateway doesn't have hooks configured in its config.json. The hooks are stored as files in `~/.openclaw/hooks/` but they need to be registered with the gateway.Let me check how hooks are registered in OpenClaw - it might be through a separate command or the gateway auto-discovers them from the hooks directory.","thinkingSignature":"3018f28514fbb3fbd5b61f2fbe600cdd080ecde30162e7935b2e2abaaaefed1e"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_15dotc5p2fdf_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"=== openclaw hooks 命令 ===\"\n~/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/bin/openclaw hooks --help 2>/dev/null | head -20\n\necho \"\"\necho \"=== hooks 目录结构 ===\"\nls -la ~/.openclaw/hooks/\n\necho \"\"\necho \"=== auto-score-classify HOOK.md ===\"\ncat ~/.openclaw/hooks/auto-score-classify/HOOK.md 2>/dev/null | head -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":41504,"output":205,"cacheRead":18895,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":60604,"cost":{"input":0.012451199999999999,"output":0.00024599999999999996,"cacheRead":0.0011336999999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.013830899999999998}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776075255305,"responseId":"062bf4f7ada62f404256535fed1bc951"}}
