{"type":"message","id":"e676fab4","parentId":"0702e43f","timestamp":"2026-04-13T10:14:57.538Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I can see the hooks that are registered and ready. I see:- `auto-score-classify` - ready (✅)- `session-summary` - ready (✅)- `memory-core-short-term-dreaming-cron` - ready (✅)\n\nBut I notice a few things:\n1. The description for `auto-score-classify` still says \"v8_classifier(3104)\" even though we changed the code to 3105. This is just the description text in HOOK.md, not the actual code.\n\n2. The `on-message.sh` and `context-hook.js` are NOT in the list of registered hooks. \n\nThey exist as files in the hooks directory but aren't registered with the gateway, so the gateway doesn't invoke them for webchat messages. The hooks that are actually registered are `auto-score-classify` for message:preprocessed events, `session-summary` for session endings, and the memory dreaming cron. The `on-message.sh` script is a shell file rather than a hook directory, so it's not being picked up by the system.","thinkingSignature":"f6709318ca05b6023c88522e60faf83006951d1753f7d0165f0f3f2c2741b701"},{"type":"text","text":"看到了。`on-message.sh` 和 `context-hook.js` **没有注册成 hook**。它们是文件系统里的文件，但 gateway 根本没加载。\n\n继续查：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_b7b8bnzv1fop_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"=== context-hook.js 内容 ===\"\ncat ~/.openclaw/hooks/context-hook.js\n\necho \"\"\necho \"=== session-memory hook ===\"\ncat ~/.openclaw/hooks/handler.js | head -30"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":42949,"output":318,"cacheRead":18895,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":62162,"cost":{"input":0.012884699999999999,"output":0.0003816,"cacheRead":0.0011336999999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.014399999999999998}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776075287669,"responseId":"062bf517133ec0e48030fef3ef6f403f"}}
{"type":"message","id":"0e3f07f3","parentId":"e676fab4","timestamp":"2026-04-13T10:14:57.633Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_b7b8bnzv1fop_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"=== context-hook.js 内容 ===\n/**\n * Context Hook for OpenClaw\n * \n * 监听消息事件，自动调用保护层context模块\n * \n * 支持的事件:\n * - message:receive: 用户发送消息\n * - message:send: AI 发送消息\n * - agent:response: Agent 回复\n */\n\nconst handler = async (event) => {\n  try {\n    // 检查是否有全局上下文接口\n    if (!global.openclaw || !global.openclaw.addContextMessage) {\n      // 尝试加载保护层\n      try {\n        const protection = await import(process.env.HOME + '/.openclaw/protection/index.js');\n        await protection.default.init();\n      } catch (e) {\n        console.log('[ContextHook] 保护层未加载，跳过');\n        return;\n      }\n    }\n\n    // 处理用户消息\n    if (event.type === 'message' || event.type === 'message:receive') {\n      const content = event.message?.content || event.content || '';\n      if (content) {\n        global.openclaw?.addContextMessage('user', content, event.taskId);\n        console.log('[ContextHook] 用户消息已记录:', content.slice(0, 30));\n      }\n    }\n\n    // 处理 Agent 回复\n    if (event.type === 'message:send' || event.type === 'agent:response') {\n      const content = event.response?.content || event.content || '';\n      if (content) {\n        global.openclaw?.addContextMessage('assistant', content, event.taskId);\n        console.log('[ContextHook] AI回复已记录:', content.slice(0, 30));\n      }\n    }\n\n  } catch (error) {\n    console.error('[ContextHook] 错误:', error.message);\n  }\n};\n\nmodule.exports = handler;\nmodule.exports.default = handler;\n=== session-memory hook ===\n/**\n * Self-Improvement + Session-Summary Bootstrap Hook for OpenClaw\n *\n * Injects:\n * 1. Self-Improvement reminder during agent bootstrap\n * 2. Previous session's summary (memory/*-session-summary.md) as bootstrap context\n *\n * Fires on agent:bootstrap event before workspace files are injected.\n */\n\nimport fs from 'node:fs';\nimport path from 'node:path';\nimport os from 'node:os';\n\nconst SELF_IMPROVEMENT_REMINDER = `## Self-Improvement Reminder\n\nAfter completing tasks, evaluate if any learnings should be captured:\n\n**Log when:**\n- User corrects you → \\`.learnings/LEARNINGS.md\\`\n- Command/operation fails → \\`.learnings/ERRORS.md\\`\n- User wants missing capability → \\`.learnings/FEATURE_REQUESTS.md\\`\n- You discover your knowledge was wrong → \\`.learnings/LEARNINGS.md\\`\n- You find a better approach → \\`.learnings/LEARNINGS.md\\`\n\n**Promote when pattern is proven:**\n- Behavioral patterns → \\`SOUL.md\\`\n- Workflow improvements → \\`AGENTS.md\\`\n- Tool gotchas → \\`TOOLS.md\\`"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":56,"aggregated":"=== context-hook.js 内容 ===\n/**\n * Context Hook for OpenClaw\n * \n * 监听消息事件，自动调用保护层context模块\n * \n * 支持的事件:\n * - message:receive: 用户发送消息\n * - message:send: AI 发送消息\n * - agent:response: Agent 回复\n */\n\nconst handler = async (event) => {\n  try {\n    // 检查是否有全局上下文接口\n    if (!global.openclaw || !global.openclaw.addContextMessage) {\n      // 尝试加载保护层\n      try {\n        const protection = await import(process.env.HOME + '/.openclaw/protection/index.js');\n        await protection.default.init();\n      } catch (e) {\n        console.log('[ContextHook] 保护层未加载，跳过');\n        return;\n      }\n    }\n\n    // 处理用户消息\n    if (event.type === 'message' || event.type === 'message:receive') {\n      const content = event.message?.content || event.content || '';\n      if (content) {\n        global.openclaw?.addContextMessage('user', content, event.taskId);\n        console.log('[ContextHook] 用户消息已记录:', content.slice(0, 30));\n      }\n    }\n\n    // 处理 Agent 回复\n    if (event.type === 'message:send' || event.type === 'agent:response') {\n      const content = event.response?.content || event.content || '';\n      if (content) {\n        global.openclaw?.addContextMessage('assistant', content, event.taskId);\n        console.log('[ContextHook] AI回复已记录:', content.slice(0, 30));\n      }\n    }\n\n  } catch (error) {\n    console.error('[ContextHook] 错误:', error.message);\n  }\n};\n\nmodule.exports = handler;\nmodule.exports.default = handler;\n=== session-memory hook ===\n/**\n * Self-Improvement + Session-Summary Bootstrap Hook for OpenClaw\n *\n * Injects:\n * 1. Self-Improvement reminder during agent bootstrap\n * 2. Previous session's summary (memory/*-session-summary.md) as bootstrap context\n *\n * Fires on agent:bootstrap event before workspace files are injected.\n */\n\nimport fs from 'node:fs';\nimport path from 'node:path';\nimport os from 'node:os';\n\nconst SELF_IMPROVEMENT_REMINDER = `## Self-Improvement Reminder\n\nAfter completing tasks, evaluate if any learnings should be captured:\n\n**Log when:**\n- User corrects you → \\`.learnings/LEARNINGS.md\\`\n- Command/operation fails → \\`.learnings/ERRORS.md\\`\n- User wants missing capability → \\`.learnings/FEATURE_REQUESTS.md\\`\n- You discover your knowledge was wrong → \\`.learnings/LEARNINGS.md\\`\n- You find a better approach → \\`.learnings/LEARNINGS.md\\`\n\n**Promote when pattern is proven:**\n- Behavioral patterns → \\`SOUL.md\\`\n- Workflow improvements → \\`AGENTS.md\\`\n- Tool gotchas → \\`TOOLS.md\\`","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/main"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776075297621}}
{"type":"message","id":"e86faf60","parentId":"0e3f07f3","timestamp":"2026-04-13T10:15:05.516Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see. The `context-hook.js` and `on-message.sh` are from an older version of the system and aren't registered as hooks in the current gateway setup. They're dead code.\n\nThe actual hooks that are running are:\n1. `auto-score-classify` (message:preprocessed)\n2. `session-summary` (session end)\n3. `memory-core-short-term-dreaming-cron` (cron)\n4. `session-memory` (bundled hook for saving session context)\n5. `bootstrap-extra-files` (bundled)\n6. `command-logger` (bundled)\n\n\n7. `boot-md` (bundled)\n\nNow I need to verify whether the session-summary hook actually generates summaries and whether the bootstrap hook correctly injects them. Looking at the auto-score-classify hook more closely, it fires on message:preprocessed, but since the webchat channel goes directly to the agent without preprocessing, this might not be triggering for webchat messages at all.\n\nHowever, context.json is actually being updated with classifications, so something is working. Let me trace through the session-summary hook to see if it's properly generating summaries when sessions end. I should also test whether on-message.sh is registered as an actual hook or just lingering code. The key thing to check is whether the session-summary hook is creating those summary files and if the bootstrap hook is properly injecting them into new sessions.","thinkingSignature":"a16ed0cdd70200c798492678aa291c1be955c28b148ec114d73a45dcbfee5cbd"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_5jtwhi9i245u_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"=== session-summary hook 完整代码 ===\"\ncat ~/.openclaw/hooks/session-summary/handler.js | head -80"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43921,"output":337,"cacheRead":18895,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":63153,"cost":{"input":0.0131763,"output":0.00040