{"type":"message","id":"af5743bd","parentId":"75d7fa4f","timestamp":"2026-04-13T10:16:25.254Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The session-summary hook fires on `command:new` or `command:reset`. But looking at the `openclaw hooks list` output, the events are listed as `command:new` and `command:reset`. \n\nSo when the user types `/new`, the gateway should emit a `command:new` event, which should trigger the session-summary hook.\n\nBut there's a question: does the hook receive the `previousSessionEntry` context with the session file path? The hook tries to resolve the session file from `context?.previousSessionEntry?.sessionFile` or `context?.sessionEntry?.sessionFile`.\n\nThe key issue is: does the gateway actually provide `previousSessionEntry` in the context when firing the `command:new` event? If not, the session-summary hook won't be able to read the session content.\n\n\nLet me test this by triggering /new and seeing if the hook actually fires and gets the context it needs.","thinkingSignature":"9eeaafbdf82cd4b9592edcdedf0d3e968a62b0e3b18f9c5acf402f701c816e40"},{"type":"text","text":"session-summary 在 `command:new` 时触发。验证链路最直接的方式：手动触发一次 /new，看 hook 是否真的跑。\n\n但先确认 session 文件位置——webchat 可能不走 `.jsonl` 文件：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_yr550t3j0x36_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"=== 找所有 session 文件 ===\"\nfind ~/.openclaw/sessions -name \"*.jsonl\" 2>/dev/null | head -10\nfind ~/.openclaw/sessions -name \"*.json\" 2>/dev/null | head -10\n\necho \"\"\necho \"=== session 目录树 ===\"\nls -la ~/.openclaw/sessions/"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":49362,"output":336,"cacheRead":18895,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":68593,"cost":{"input":0.0148086,"output":0.0004032,"cacheRead":0.0011336999999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0163455}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776075376424,"responseId":"062bf56fe1f1730fc5a1a57f132eaf53"}}
{"type":"message","id":"80540dfa","parentId":"af5743bd","timestamp":"2026-04-13T10:16:25.338Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_yr550t3j0x36_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"=== 找所有 session 文件 ===\n/home/ai/.openclaw/sessions/agent:main:main/context.json\n/home/ai/.openclaw/sessions/agent:fast_agent:main/context.json\n\n=== session 目录树 ===\ntotal 16\ndrwxrwxr-x  4 ai ai 4096 Apr 13 02:11 .\ndrwx------ 32 ai ai 4096 Apr 13 02:23 ..\ndrwxrwxr-x  2 ai ai 4096 Apr 13 02:11 agent:fast_agent:main\ndrwxrwxr-x  2 ai ai 4096 Apr 13 01:42 agent:main:main"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":49,"aggregated":"=== 找所有 session 文件 ===\n/home/ai/.openclaw/sessions/agent:main:main/context.json\n/home/ai/.openclaw/sessions/agent:fast_agent:main/context.json\n\n=== session 目录树 ===\ntotal 16\ndrwxrwxr-x  4 ai ai 4096 Apr 13 02:11 .\ndrwx------ 32 ai ai 4096 Apr 13 02:23 ..\ndrwxrwxr-x  2 ai ai 4096 Apr 13 02:11 agent:fast_agent:main\ndrwxrwxr-x  2 ai ai 4096 Apr 13 01:42 agent:main:main","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/main"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776075385329}}
{"type":"message","id":"f092bd84","parentId":"80540dfa","timestamp":"2026-04-13T10:16:43.043Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see the problem now. The webchat sessions only have `context.json` files, no `.jsonl` message history files. The session content is stored in the gateway's internal database (as confirmed by the `database: ok` in the health check), not in the filesystem.\n\nThe session-summary hook uses `getRecentSessionContent(sessionFilePath, messageCount)` which reads from a `.jsonl` file. But for webchat sessions, there's no `.jsonl` file - only a `context.json`.\n\nSo the session-summary hook would:1. Try to find the previous session file\n2. Look for a `.jsonl` file at the path from `previousSessionEntry.sessionFile`3. \n\nFail because no `.jsonl` exists for webchat sessions\n\nThe bundled `session-memory` hook has the same issue - it expects a `.jsonl` file. Even if it could read the session content, the `generateSlugViaLLM` function in session-summary would fail because there's no LLM configured at 3102. Looking at the session-summary hook, it tries to call an LLM via `http.request` to `3102` to generate a slug for the session, but that endpoint doesn't exist either.\n\nThe hook falls back to `context.sessionKey` when the LLM call fails, so the session-summary file would still be created with a fallback name, just not as descriptive. The real blocker is that the hook can't read the session content without the `.jsonl` file, which prevents proper session context recovery. Let me trace through the hook's logic more carefully - it resolves the session file from the event context, and for webchat sessions the `sessionEntry.sessionFile` might not be set at all since the session is stored in the database rather than a file.\n\nIf the session file path is null, the message extraction would return null, which means even if the hook fires, it can't access the actual session content to generate a summary. The bundled `session-memory` hook does have access to the database session entry though, so I need to understand what that hook actually provides to the event context.\n\nThe core issue is becoming clear: the webchat session doesn't have a `.jsonl` file on disk—the gateway stores everything in the database instead. So when the `/new` command triggers the session-summary hook, there's no file to read from, even if the hook itself is firing correctly. The session-summary hook is likely running and creating files, but with empty or minimal content because it can't find the actual session data to summarize.\n\nBut there's another layer to this: even if the hook could read the session file, it's trying to call a LLM at port 3102 that doesn't exist, so the slug generation would fail anyway. I need to verify whether port 3102 is actually available or if that's another broken dependency.","thinkingSignature":"9e781f2f0717a60fd20a4296fd99c1710972fb207e25aef40ebe62c11903e0fb"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ml8z42vjmp6e_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"=== 3102 端口 ===\"\nss -tlnp 2>/dev/null | grep 3102\ncurl -s http://localhost:3102/ 2>/dev/null | head -c 100\n\necho \"\"\necho \"=== session-summary hook LLM 调用 ===\"\ngrep -n \"3102\\|localhost\\|http\" ~/.openclaw/hooks/session-summary/handler.js | head -15"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":49849,"output":694,"cacheRead":18895,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":69438,"cost":{"input":0.0149547,"output":0.0008328,"cacheRead":0.0011336999999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0169212}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776075385340,"responseId":"062bf57802c6fdcce1dab638857b843e"}}
{"type":"message","id":"07c47e72","parentId":"f092bd84","timestamp":"2026-04-13T10:16:43.174Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_ml8z42vjmp6e_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"=== 3102 端口 ===\nLISTEN    0         511               127.0.0.1:3102             0.0.0.0:*       users:((\"openclaw-gatewa\",pid=140547,fd=22))                                   \nLISTEN    0         511                   [::1]:3102                [::]:*       users:((\"openclaw-gatewa\",pid=140547,fd=23))                                   \n<!doctype html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n  <head>\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\" />\n    <meta name=\"viewport\" con\n=== session-summary hook LLM 调用 ===\n17:import http from \"node:http\";\n299:    const req = http.request(\n300:      \"http://127.0.0.1:3102/v1/chat/completions\","}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":90,"aggregated":"=== 3102 端口 ===\nLISTEN    0         511               127.0.0.1:3102             0.0.0.0:*       users:((\"openclaw-gatewa\",pid=140547,fd=22))                                   \nLISTEN    0         511                   [::1]:3102                [::]:*       users:((\"openclaw-gatewa\",pid=140547,fd=23))                                   \n<!doctype html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n  <head>\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\" />\n    <meta name=\"viewport\" con\n=== session-summary hook LLM 调用 ===\n17:import http from \"node:http\";\n299:    const req = http.request(\n300:      \"http://127.0.0.1:3102/v1/chat/completions\",","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/main"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776075403161}}
{"type":"message","id":"ed0f6711","parentId":"07c47e72","timestamp":"2026-04-13T10:17:00.867Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting! Port 3102 is actually the gateway itself (pid 140547). The session-summary hook calls `http://127.0.0.1:3102/v1/chat/completions` which is the gateway's LLM API endpoint. So the LLM call should work through the gateway.\n\nNow let me understand the complete flow:\n1. When /new is issued → `command:new` event fires\n2. session-summary hook is triggered\n3. Hook reads session content from `context.previousSessionEntry.sessionFile` (should be a .jsonl file)4. Hook calls LLM via gateway (3102) to generate summary\n\n\n5. Hook writes summary to `memory/YYYY-MM-DD-session-summary.md`\n\nBut here's the problem: webchat sessions store their data in the database, not as .jsonl files. The session file path would be null for webchat, so the hook can't read the content. Let me check if the gateway's session storage actually uses .jsonl files or if there's a way to access that data through the session entry context.\n\nActually, looking at the `openclaw hooks list` output, the `session-memory` bundled hook is marked as ready and it's supposed to save session context when /new or /reset is issued. But webchat sessions are stored in the database, not as JSONL files, so `context.previousSessionEntry.sessionFile` would be null. The session-summary hook would then try to get recent session content with a null path and fail. Even if it did work, there's another issue - the hook checks `event.type === \"command\" && (event.action === \"new\" || event.action === \"reset\")`, but webchat messages aren't \"command\" type events, so the hook wouldn't fire for regular messages anyway.\n\nThe session-summary hook only fires when the user explicitly issues the `/new` command, not when the session ends. So the hook is designed to run on `command:new`, which means it needs the user to actively trigger it. The webchat session does have a `context.json` file in `~/.openclaw/sessions/agent:main:main/`, but I need to figure out whether that's a actual session file or just the classification/scoring context. The session file might be stored in the gateway database rather than as a .jsonl file, so the hook wouldn't be able to read it anyway.\n\nNow I'm thinking I should manually trigger a /new command to test if the session-summary hook actually fires and runs. But actually, the gateway logs would be more telling—if session-summary ran, there'd be log entries, and if it succeeded, a new summary file would appear in memory with today's date. Let me check the memory directory for any recent summary files.","thinkingSignature":"b261499d7cfc3df01dbedbdade182cf4df355bb0b032d5031a47efc945be4e0f"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_wvk4u1lfzo5j_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"=== memory/ 目录最近修改的文件 ===\"\nfind ~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/ -name \"*.md\" -newer ~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-04-13-session-summary.md 2>/dev/null\nfind ~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/ -name \"*summary*\" -o -name \"*session*\" 2>/dev/null | xargs ls -la 2>/dev/null | tail -10\n\necho \"\"\necho \"=== 检查 gateway 日志 ===\"\ntail -50 ~/.openclaw/logs/gateway.log 2>/dev/null | grep -E \"session-summary|summary|hook\" | tail -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":50742,"output":726,"cacheRead":18895,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":70363,"cost":{"input":0.0152226,"output":0.0008711999999999999,"cacheRead":0.0011336999999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0172275}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776075403178,"responseId":"062bf58ab1232e0af0860109aac11930"}}
