{"type":"message","id":"bf6ff841","parentId":"80898308","timestamp":"2026-04-13T10:17:24.160Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"There's no gateway.log file. The gateway logs at `warn` level, so it wouldn't log hook activities anyway. Let me just try to trigger /new via the sessions API and see if the hook fires.Actually, let me think about this differently. Instead of trying to debug why session-summary doesn't work (which requires /new to be issued), let me just verify that the classification issue is fixed and focus on what's actually broken that I can fix now.\n\nThe key issues:\n1. ✅ **classification null** - FIXED by gateway restart\n2. ❌ **context-api** - Dead code, not registered as hook\n\n\n3. ❌ **session-summary** - Never runs because webchat sessions lack .jsonl files\n\nNow I should test whether issuing /new actually creates a new summary file to confirm whether this bottleneck is real.","thinkingSignature":"41ad76e4c8f0f9d0bb42431027ffe5feb29d2b94f811b462b737dee1def90dc1"},{"type":"text","text":"现在做最终验证——触发一次 /new 看 session-summary 是否跑：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_xue5mr8y8t0m_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"=== 触发 /new 前 ===\"\nls -la ~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/*session-summary* 2>/dev/null\n\necho \"\"\necho \"=== 通过 sessions_send 触发 /new ===\"\n# 注意：这会在当前 session 发一个 /new，触发 command:new 事件\necho \"发送 /new 到当前 session\"\n~/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/bin/openclaw sessions send agent:main:main \"/new\" 2>/dev/null | head -5\n\nsleep 3\n\necho \"\"\necho \"=== 触发 /new 后 ===\"\nls -la ~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/*session-summary* 2>/dev/null\nfind ~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/ -name \"*.md\" -newer /tmp/now 2>/dev/null | head -10"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":52943,"output":381,"cacheRead":18895,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":72219,"cost":{"input":0.0158829,"output":0.0004572,"cacheRead":0.0011336999999999999,"cacheWrite":0