{"type":"message","id":"40f0f722","parentId":"7ed81807","timestamp":"2026-04-13T10:21:00.041Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to think about the session-summary issue and propose a solution. Let me analyze the problem:\n\n**Problem**: session-summary hook can't read webchat session content because:\n1. Hook reads from `.jsonl` session files via `context.previousSessionEntry.sessionFile`\n2. Webchat sessions store messages in gateway database, not in `.jsonl` files\n3. Result: hook runs but gets no content, writes empty/placeholder summary\n\nLet me think about solutions:\n\n**Option 1: Modify session-summary hook to use gateway API**\n- Instead of reading from `.jsonl` file, call gateway API to get session content\n- But this requires gateway API endpoint that exposes session messages\n\n\n- The session-memory hook saves context to memory on /new, but webchat doesn't use `.jsonl` files either, so this won't help\n\n**Option 2: Check if gateway stores webchat sessions elsewhere**\n- Maybe there's a database file or another storage location I should be looking at\n\n**Option 3: Rely on bootstrap's existing logic**\n- Bootstrap hook reads the latest `*-session-summary.md` from memory\n- Even if the hook can't access the actual session content, it might still inject summaries correctly\n- The real question is whether bootstrap can access what the hook wrote\n\n**Option 4: Change the hook's data source**\n- Instead of relying on session content it can't read, the hook could pull from context.json, ephemeral memory, or other available sources\n\nLet me trace through the hook code more carefully to see what context fields it actually has access to.","thinkingSignature":"453ddf63c5ed2cb624879edf936d7d835f182f820508f33df2bb138fcf17153a"},{"type":"text","text":"先读代码，找 session-summary hook 实际能拿到什么数据：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_xeg925sfldql_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"sed -n '460,510p' ~/.openclaw/hooks/session-summary/handler.js"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":54,"output":382,"cacheRead":18895,"cacheWrite":51677,"totalTokens":71008,"cost":{"input":0.0000162,"output":0.0004584,"cacheRead":0.0011336999999999999,"cacheWrite":0.019378875,"total":0.020987175}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776075644800,"responseId":"062bf67c0ce9a91a4444744b1dd939e7"}}
{"type":"message","id":"69c243ba","parentId":"40f0f722","timestamp":"2026-04-13T10:21:00.130Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_xeg925sfldql_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\",\n    \"<!-- summary-only -->\",\n    summary,\n    \"\",\n    `<!-- source: ${sessionKey} -->`,\n  ].join(\"\\n\");\n\n  await fs.promises.writeFile(filePath, fullContent, \"utf-8\");\n  console.log(`[session-summary] Written: ${filename}`);\n}\n\n/**\n * @param {string} summary\n * @param {string} time\n * @returns {string}\n */\nfunction slugFromSummary(summary, time) {\n  const match = summary.match(/^## 主题$\\s*([^\\n]+)/m);\n  if (!match) return time.replace(/:/g, \"\");\n\n  return match[1]\n    .toLowerCase()\n    .replace(/[^a-z0-9\\u4e00-\\u9fff]+/g, \"-\")\n    .replace(/^-+|-+$/g, \"\")\n    .slice(0, 40) || time.replace(/:/g, \"\");\n}\n\n// ─── Core ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\n/**\n * @param {{ type: string, action: string, sessionKey: string, context: HookContext, messages: unknown[] }} event\n */\nasync function run(event) {\n  const isTarget = event.type === \"command\" && (event.action === \"new\" || event.action === \"reset\");\n  if (!isTarget) return;\n\n  const now = new Date();\n  const date = now.toISOString().split(\"T\")[0];\n  const time = now.toISOString().split(\"T\")[1].split(\".\")[0].slice(0, 5);\n\n  // 1. 解析 session 文件路径（优先 previousSessionEntry）\n  const sessionFile = resolveSessionFile(event.context || {});\n\n  // 2. 读取消息内容\n  const content = sessionFile ? await extractMessages(sessionFile) : \"\";\n\n  // 3. 读取 ephemeral 记忆碎片\n  // 从 previousSessionEntry.sessionId 获取前一个 session 的 key（sessionId = sessionKey）\n  const prevSessionId = event.context?.previousSessionEntry?.sessionId || event.sessionKey;\n  const { entries, preview: ephemeralPreview } = await readEphemeralEntries(prevSessionId);"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":47,"aggregated":"\"\",\n    \"<!-- summary-only -->\",\n    summary,\n    \"\",\n    `<!-- source: ${sessionKey} -->`,\n  ].join(\"\\n\");\n\n  await fs.promises.writeFile(filePath, fullContent, \"utf-8\");\n  console.log(`[session-summary] Written: ${filename}`);\n}\n\n/**\n * @param {string} summary\n * @param {string} time\n * @returns {string}\n */\nfunction slugFromSummary(summary, time) {\n  const match = summary.match(/^## 主题$\\s*([^\\n]+)/m);\n  if (!match) return time.replace(/:/g, \"\");\n\n  return match[1]\n    .toLowerCase()\n    .replace(/[^a-z0-9\\u4e00-\\u9fff]+/g, \"-\")\n    .replace(/^-+|-+$/g, \"\")\n    .slice(0, 40) || time.replace(/:/g, \"\");\n}\n\n// ─── Core ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\n/**\n * @param {{ type: string, action: string, sessionKey: string, context: HookContext, messages: unknown[] }} event\n */\nasync function run(event) {\n  const isTarget = event.type === \"command\" && (event.action === \"new\" || event.action === \"reset\");\n  if (!isTarget) return;\n\n  const now = new Date();\n  const date = now.toISOString().split(\"T\")[0];\n  const time = now.toISOString().split(\"T\")[1].split(\".\")[0].slice(0, 5);\n\n  // 1. 解析 session 文件路径（优先 previousSessionEntry）\n  const sessionFile = resolveSessionFile(event.context || {});\n\n  // 2. 读取消息内容\n  const content = sessionFile ? await extractMessages(sessionFile) : \"\";\n\n  // 3. 读取 ephemeral 记忆碎片\n  // 从 previousSessionEntry.sessionId 获取前一个 session 的 key（sessionId = sessionKey）\n  const prevSessionId = event.context?.previousSessionEntry?.sessionId || event.sessionKey;\n  const { entries, preview: ephemeralPreview } = await readEphemeralEntries(prevSessionId);","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/main"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776075660122}}
{"type":"message","id":"72284cd3","parentId":"69c243ba","timestamp":"2026-04-13T10:21:14.159Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can see:\n1. `sessionFile` is resolved from `resolveSessionFile(event.context || {})`\n2. If no sessionFile, content = \"\"\n3. `ephemeral` is read using `prevSessionId`\n\nSo the hook DOES try to read ephemeral, but it's using the current sessionKey. Let me check what ephemeral entries exist for the current session.\n\nBut the main problem is: webchat sessions don't have `.jsonl` files. So `sessionFile` will be null and `content` will be empty.\n\nLet me look at what context the hook actually receives from the gateway event. The hook receives `event.context` which has `previousSessionEntry`. But for webchat, the session is the same - it's a persistent webchat session, not a fresh /new session.\n \nThe real issue is that session-summary fires on `/new`, but in webchat the session is actually persistent. When I trigger `/new` via sessions_send, the gateway creates a fresh session with a new sessionKey, and `previousSessionEntry` should point to the old session. The problem is the old session's messages are in the gateway database, not in a `.jsonl` file that the hook can read. So even though `ephemeral` entries might exist for the current sessionKey, the hook can't access the actual conversation history from the previous persistent session.\n\nI could fix this by either making the hook call the gateway API directly to fetch the previous session's messages, or by writing those messages to a `.jsonl` file that the hook can read. But both approaches have complications—the gateway API might not expose this data, and writing files adds complexity. Alternatively, I could simplify the bootstrap approach to just rely on ephemeral memory and context.json instead of trying to reconstruct the session history from files. The cleanest fix is probably to modify the session-summary hook to use the gateway API instead of relying on session files. But I need to verify that the gateway actually exposes an endpoint to retrieve previous session content, and I should examine how the session-memory hook stores context to understand the data flow better.","thinkingSignature":"b3aadf6420fae7b6e20509bdd40a0556a1550dd44fda5f8ee57b78d70cdab253"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_q0kezt56fiia_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"=== session-memory hook 完整流程 ===\"\ncat ~/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/bundled/session-memory/handler.js 2>/dev/null | wc -l\necho \"行\"\n\necho \"\"\necho \"=== session-memory 写的文件路径 ===\"\ngrep -n \"writeFile\\|sessionFile\\|session.*path\\|memory.*write\" ~/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/bundled/session-memory/handler.js 2>/dev/null | head -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":52585,"output":574,"cacheRead":18895,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":72054,"cost":{"input":0.015775499999999998,"output":0.0006887999999999999,"cacheRead":0.0011336999999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.017598}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776075660132,"responseId":"062bf68b4fe29cc86623446252e51a81"}}
