{"type":"message","id":"93f8d078","parentId":"4e4cd61a","timestamp":"2026-04-13T10:21:33.484Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Very interesting! There ARE session-memory files:- `2026-04-13-14-session.md` (14:48)- `2026-04-13-无会话内容.md` (15:17) - this is the one written when session-summary ran but found no content- `2026-04-13-framework-fix.md` (13:46)These were written by the session-memory hook (bundled), not the session-summary hook (custom). And `2026-04-13-无会话内容.md` confirms that the hook ran but found no session content.\n\nNow let me understand the full picture:\n\n**session-memory hook** (bundled, active):\n\n\n- Listens for `command:new` and `command:reset` events\n- Writes a session summary to `memory/YYYY-MM-DD-{time}-session.md`\n- But since there's no `.jsonl` file for webchat, it saves \"无会话内容\" (no session content)\n\n**session-summary hook** (custom, registered):\n- Also listens for `command:new` and `command:reset`\n- Tries to read from `sessionFile` (which doesn't exist for webchat) and extracts nothing\n- Relies on ephemeral entries to fill the gap\n\nBoth hooks fire on the same event and do similar work - the custom one creates summaries while the bundled one creates session records. Looking at the `2026-04-13-14-session.md` file should clarify what the bundled hook is actually storing.","thinkingSignature":"5bc256df42540ad19f1ffdb0bf136109bbde75b0edd36eefd556bdc596d16782"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_24a5kcj2eay6_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"=== 14-session.md 内容 ===\"\ncat ~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-04-13-14-session.md\n\necho \"\"\necho \"=== 无会话内容.md ===\"\ncat ~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-04-13-无会话内容.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":54499,"output":396,"cacheRead":18895,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":73790,"cost":{"input":0.016349699999999998,"output":0.0004752,"cacheRead":0.0011336999999999999,"cacheWri