{"type":"message","id":"7aff670f","parentId":"3e67c595","timestamp":"2026-04-13T10:23:07.049Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The gateway token is redacted in config.json and stored securely. I can't easily get it.\n\nLet me think about this differently. Instead of calling the gateway API with authentication:\n\n1. **The bundled session-memory hook DOES work** for webchat (as proven by `2026-04-13-14-session.md` having real content). How does IT get the content?\n\n2. **The session-memory hook and session-summary hook both listen to the same events**. If session-memory can get content, session-summary should be able to use a similar approach.\n\nLet me look at how session-memory accesses session content. It uses `sessionEntry.sessionFile` - same as session-summary. But it also has access to the hook context...\n \nWait, session-memory is bundled into the gateway process itself, so it probably has direct internal access to session data that a standalone hook running externally doesn't. That would explain why it can retrieve content while the external hook can't. I could try reading from the session-memory output file instead, since session-summary already knows how to work with file-based inputs.\n\nLooking at what session-memory writes to `memory/YYYY-MM-DD-{slug}.md`, the session-summary hook could parse these files to get conversation content. The challenge is that session-memory uses LLM-generated slugs based on session content, so predicting the exact filename is difficult. But both hooks fire on the same `/new` event, so the session-memory file from the previous session should already exist by the time session-summary runs—I just need to figure out how to locate it.\n\nExamining the session-memory handler more closely, it retrieves the previous session's file path and uses that to extract conversation content before the `/new` took effect. So when `/new` is called, the hook gets the old session's `.jsonl` file path and reads the last 15 messages from it. The session-summary hook tries to do the same thing but something's going wrong with its file path resolution.","thinkingSignature":"415f1cec75c167d45c884c92c65e16571a402e959cf488fb42a7cd8c824d3329"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_euv00t4kpcsq_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"=== session-memory 如何获取 previousSessionFile ===\"\nsed -n '100,160p' ~/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/bundled/session-memory/handler.js"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":59434,"output":471,"cacheRead":18895,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":78800,"cost":{"input":0.0178302,"output":0.0005652,"cacheRead":0.0011336999999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0195291}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776075774104,"responseId":"062bf6fd7f3e306baf7797ef2b6322e6"}}
