et sessionContent = null;\n\t\tif (sessionFile) {\n\t\t\tsessionContent = await getRecentSessionContentWithResetFallback(sessionFile, messageCount);\n\t\t\tlog.debug(\"Session content loaded\", {\n\t\t\t\tlength: sessionContent?.length ?? 0,\n\t\t\t\tmessageCount\n\t\t\t});\n\t\t\tconst allowLlmSlug = !(process.env.OPENCLAW_TEST_FAST === \"1\" || process.env.VITEST === \"true\" || process.env.VITEST === \"1\" || false) && hookConfig?.llmSlug !== false;\n\t\t\tif (sessionContent && cfg && allowLlmSlug) {\n\t\t\t\tlog.debug(\"Calling generateSlugViaLLM...\");\n\t\t\t\tslug = await generateSlugViaLLM({\n\t\t\t\t\tsessionContent,\n\t\t\t\t\tcfg\n\t\t\t\t});","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/main"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776075787130}}
{"type":"message","id":"3f3ee2a4","parentId":"49031e7a","timestamp":"2026-04-13T10:23:14.626Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the key difference. The session-memory hook has a `findPreviousSessionFile` function that actively searches for session files:\n\n```javascript\nconst recoveredSessionFile = await findPreviousSessionFile({\n    sessionsDir,\n    currentSessionFile,\n    sessionId: currentSessionId\n});\n```\n\nAnd it adds `path.join(workspaceDir, \"sessions\")` to the search directories. Let me find this function.\n\nBut more importantly, I see that the session-memory hook does find session files and reads content. The `currentSessionFile` might be null initially, but it searches in the sessions directory.\n\n\nThe real question is whether the custom session-summary hook has access to the same `findPreviousSessionFile` utility, or if it's trying to resolve session files through a different mechanism.","thinkingSignature":"ddca5866121532ac6d63e09c0a362b13638dde2ca48ccb8078876f5560c1caab"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_05qxpn8n117f_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"=== session-summary 依赖的模块 ===\"\ngrep -n \"import\\|require\\|findPreviousSessionFile\\|resolveSessionFile\" ~/.openclaw/hooks/session-summary/handler.js | head -20\n\necho \"\"\necho \"=== session-summary 的 resolveSessionFile ===\"\nsed -n '70,110p' ~/.openclaw/hooks/session-summary/handler.js"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":60633,"output":261,"cacheRead":18895,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":79789,"cost":{"input":0.0181899,"output":0.00031319999999999997,"cacheRead":0.0011336999999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0196368}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776075787149,"responseId":"062bf70bd6667d0745548446dccce03a"}}
