{"type":"message","id":"016af070","parentId":"4eba0680","timestamp":"2026-04-13T10:47:46.102Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait - entities went from 35 to 41? And blocklist is now 19 (was 9)? Something is wrong. The wiki-learn cron ran and added new entities without respecting the blocklist. Let me investigate.\n\nAlso, ephemeral only has 10 total lines - but there should be content from the current session's conversation. The \"全面检查\" message at 18:46 should have been captured as ephemeral if it's meaningful enough.\n\nWait - let me check the context.json for the \"全面检查\" message. It says:\n- timestamp: 2026-04-13T10:46:25.872Z (18:46 GMT+8)\n\n\n- preview: \"[Mon 2026-04-13 18:46 GMT+8] 全面检查\"\n\nBut ephemeral has nothing from 10:46. This is 18:46 GMT+8, which is 10:46 UTC. Let me check - the ephemeral files use UTC. The current UTC hour is 10. So the file should be `2026-04-13-10.jsonl`. It doesn't exist. So the \"全面检查\" message was NOT captured into ephemeral.\n\nWait - ephemeral has only 10 total lines. But we tested earlier and saw 1 entry from \"全面检查\" was written to ephemeral. So something must have cleared it or the wiki-learn cron overwrote it.\n\nActually, looking more carefully:\n- 2026-04-13-05.jsonl: 1 line\n- 2026-04-13-06.jsonl: 1 line\n- 2026-04-13-09.jsonl: 2 lines (from our manual test earlier)\n- 2026-04-13-13.jsonl: 6 lines (this is 21:00 GMT+8, which was during the afternoon session)\n\nThe 10 UTC hour file doesn't exist at all. Either the \"全面检查\" message at 18:46 wasn't classified as meaningful, or the ephemeral capture failed silently.\n\nNow I need to figure out why entities jumped from 35 to 41. The wiki-learn cron runs `wiki-learn-once.sh`, which should only add new entities if they're not already in blocklist. But blocklist has 19 entries and entities has 41, so something's not matching up. The blocklist was at 9 before the last cron run at 17:57, and now it's at 19 - that means 10 new skill directories got added to the blocklist during that run.\n\nLet me trace what actually happened: the cron added 10 new auto-ingested entities to bring the total to 35, which is below the threshold of 40, so no pruning should have occurred. But something still doesn't add up here.\n\nLooking at the math more carefully—after removing 16 auto-ingested entities, we had 25 total. Then wiki-learn-once.sh added 10 back (excluding the 9 blocked skills), bringing us to 35. The blocklist now shows 19 skills total, which suggests multiple cron runs added entries cumulatively. But the current entities count is 41, which is higher than the 35 we ended up with after the script ran. I need to figure out where these extra 6 entities came from—they shouldn't exist if the script only added 10 and we only have 35.\n\nThe blocklist growth from 9 to 19 is puzzling too. Looking at the cron logs, wiki-learn-once ran multiple times with the new script (at 17:02, 17:10, and presumably 17:57), and the blocklist might be getting populated differently than I thought—maybe it's tracking all attempted additions, not just successful ones. Each one added 0-10 new entities depending on space. The blocklist would grow each time a skill was pruned.\n\nBut the blocklist only records pruned skills, and if the same skills were pruned multiple times, they'd only be recorded once. Unless the blocklist file wasn't overwritten each time but appended to.\n\nI think what happened is: the script was modified mid-stream, and some intermediate state got saved. The blocklist accumulated duplicates from multiple runs.\n\nActually, I think the bigger issue is that the blocklist has 19 entries but we only have 9 unique skills that were pruned. Let me check if there are duplicates.\n\nLet me also check the current cron run to see what's happening.\n\nFor now, the key issues are:\n1. entities is 41, not 35 (above TARGET+BUFFER=40, so prune should have triggered)\n2. blocklist has 19 entries instead of 9 (possible duplicates)\n\nI need to look at the current state of both to understand what went wrong.","thinkingSignature":"932e2cea52370ec871d4bbea55dc7334757f650b3e3098888644ba4954a35659"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_zowt9wzuug02_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"=== entities 41 详情 ===\"\nls ~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/entities/ | wc -l\nauto=$(grep -l \"status: auto-ingested\" ~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/entities/*.md 2>/dev/null | wc -l)\necho \"auto-ingested: $auto\"\nmanual=$(grep -l \"status: active\\|status: draft\\|status: reference\" ~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/entities/*.md 2>/dev/null | wc -l)\necho \"manual: $manual\"\n\necho \"\"\necho \"=== blocklist 内容 ===\"\ncat ~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/.wiki-learn-blocklist | sort | uniq -c | sort -rn | head -15"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":65963,"output":1148,"cacheRead":18895,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":86006,"cost":{"input":0.019788899999999998,"output":0.0013775999999999999,"cacheRead":0.0011336999999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0223002}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776077239157,"responseId":"062bfcb6310bdf3bfe700563bb98bc34"}}
