{"type":"message","id":"6e064bd4","parentId":"4dcbd57c","timestamp":"2026-04-13T10:48:02.409Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So the blocklist has 19 entries (with some duplicates - each skill listed twice except for 9 unique skills). This happened because `wiki-learn-once.sh` was run multiple times and each time it appended to the blocklist without deduplicating.\n\nThe entities is 41 (16 auto-ingested + 22 manual + some others). The TARGET is 30 and BUFFER is 5, so the prune threshold is 40. We're at 41, so the next cron run should prune.\n\nBut the real problem: the blocklist has DUPLICATES. The script uses `>> \"$BLOCKLIST\"` which appends, not replaces. \n\nI need to deduplicate the blocklist and set TARGET=30, BUFFER=3 to make the pruning trigger at 33 instead of 40. I should also investigate why ephemeral isn't capturing the \"全面检查\" message.\n\nLooking at the ephemeral files, the current hour is 10 UTC (18:46 GMT+8), but there's no `2026-04-13-10.jsonl` file. The \"全面检查\" message should have been captured since it has risk=0 but classification shows `intercepted: false` and `scene: clarify`, which doesn't match any of the `isMeaningful` conditions—unless the hook just stopped running after the gateway restart at 18:31.\n\nActually, checking the timestamp more carefully: the context.json shows 18:46:25 which is GMT+8, so 10:46 UTC. The ephemeral file for that hour doesn't exist, meaning `writeEphemeral` wasn't called for the \"全面检查\" message. This could mean either the hook isn't firing or `isMeaningful` returned false for that specific message.\n\nBut looking at the hook's event filter - it only triggers on `message:preprocessed` events. If the gateway restarted at 18:31 and the \"全面检查\" message came in at 18:46, the hook should be running unless the gateway didn't fully reload the hook after the restart.\n\nLet me just verify whether ephemeral is capturing anything by sending a test message with explicitly meaningful