{"type":"message","id":"72a0a832","parentId":"8685ee12","timestamp":"2026-04-13T10:48:11.673Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK, so the ephemeral file can be created. Now the issue is: why didn't the hook write to the current hour's file? Let me check if the hook is actually running for each message. The context.json was updated at 18:46:25 (showing \"全面检查\"), but no ephemeral was written for that message.\n\nWait - maybe the hook IS running but `isMeaningful` returns false for that message. The \"全面检查\" message has:\n- scoring: probably 0 (short query)- classification: scene=clarify, intercepted=false\n- No matching keyword patterns\n\nSo `isMeaningful` returns false → no ephemeral written. This is actually correct behavior.\n\n\nThe hook is working as designed - it's intentionally filtering out ephemeral entries based on the `isMeaningful` criteria. The real problem is the blocklist has duplicates and entities keeps growing beyond the target threshold, so I need to clean up the blocklist first.","thinkingSignature":"a2f87141b0939a848d403464d9fe3542db5afecea9aa16c2622fff110da11925"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ue2ekw1ozd6r_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"=== 清理 blocklist 重复 ===\"\nsort -u ~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/.wiki-learn-blocklist > /tmp/bl && mv /tmp/bl ~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/.wiki-learn-blocklist\necho \"去重后: $(wc -l < ~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/.wiki-learn-blocklist) 个\"\ncat ~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/.wiki-learn-blocklist"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":67998,"output":303,"cacheRead":18895,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":87196,"cost":{"input":0.020399399999999998,"output":0.0003636,"cacheRead":0.0011336999999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.021896699999999998}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776077282522,"responseId":"062bfce2aa83529c85d920d73649ea0f"}}
