w script finally ran at 18:02.\n\nLet me trace through what happened: at 16:57 we had 35 entities after pruning, then between 16:57 and 18:01 the old script kept adding more, and by 18:01 it reported 35 again but had actually grown beyond that. The cron at 18:00 triggered the new script which should have reset things to 30, but something went wrong.\n\nLooking at the blocklist now showing 19 entries suggests the script was somehow adding to it incrementally rather than replacing it, which would explain the entity count explosion and why the pruning didn't stick.\n\nThe 18:02 run shows \"entities:30 | new:0 | skip:13\", which indicates no new entities were added, but then we jump to 41 by 18:46 - that's a 9-11 entity increase in 44 minutes, which shouldn't happen if the new script is actually running and respecting the blocklist. Something is still adding entities outside the control of the current script.\n\nLooking back at the 17:10 run more carefully, I see \"entities:35 | new:10\" meaning 10 new entities were added while 14 were skipped for space, but the blocklist only grew from 9 to 13 (4 new entries). That means 6 pruned entities weren't recorded in the blocklist - they came from the initial cleanup at 17:00 when we had 16 auto-ingested entities removed. The blocklist was only tracking what was pruned during that specific cleanup, not everything that got removed. I need to reconsider how the blocklist gets populated. Looking at the code, it only adds entries when skills are pruned via `blocklist_add`, not when they're removed during initial cleanup. So the blocklist should have grown to 16 after `prune_to_target` ran at 16:12, but it only shows 9—which means either the cleanup happened before blocklist was initialized, or the blocklist logic wasn't triggered the way I thought.\n\nLet me trace through what happened: at 17:00 I deleted all auto-ingested entities manually, then ran the script which added 10 and removed 11, ending at 30 with blocklist at 9. The ol