{"type":"message","id":"2882c983","parentId":"f72bc028","timestamp":"2026-04-13T10:50:17.736Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK, so now we're back to 35 entities. The blocklist has 15 entries. The script added 10 new auto-ingested entities and skipped 14 (because space ran out). We're at exactly the BUFFER boundary (TARGET=30 + BUFFER=5 = 35). No pruning needed.\n\nBut wait - the blocklist still only has 15 entries. The script just added 10 new entities that are NOT in the blocklist. When these get pruned in the future, they'll be added to the blocklist. So the blocklist will eventually have all the pruned skills.\n\nFor now, the system is stable at 35 entities. \n\nThe cron should maintain this equilibrium going forward since it keeps adding skills until hitting the BUFFER limit, then prunes when necessary. The two remaining issues are that 35 is still above the original TARGET of 30, and there's a bug in the blocklist deduplication logic - it only happens during initialization rather than when new entries are added during pruning. I should fix both the deduplication and lower the TARGET to better align with the actual stable state. The system is stable at 35 entities, which is close enough to the target. Now I need to fix the deduplication bug in wiki-learn-once.sh and make sure it handles the blocklist properly when pruning happens after the next cron run.","thinkingSignature":"d114299efde172e3c01f4ba371b79d664bd02774b61b6dc4bbe8ff711cd6d028"},{"type":"text","text":"现在 35 个，稳定了。修复 blocklist 去重 bug：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_5nhw48mdljch_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/wiki-learn-once.sh","offset":60,"limit":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":74307,"output":348,"cacheRead":18895,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":93550,"cost":{"input":0.0222921,"output":0.00041759999999999996,"cacheRead":0.0011336999999999999,"c