{"type":"message","id":"26e7d868","parentId":"f0390c9e","timestamp":"2026-04-13T11:01:08.974Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait - the blocklist has 15 items. But the script should skip all 15 when adding new skills. Why did it add 10 more? Let me check the script's blocklist checking logic again. Maybe the blocklist was still empty at the time of the last cron run, or the blocklist checking has a bug.\n\nWait - the blocklist was cleared when I ran `> \"$BLOCKLIST\"` during my earlier cleanup. But then I rebuilt it. Let me check if the blocklist is correct.Actually, I think the issue is that the last cron run happened BEFORE my cleanup (at 18:02, my cleanup was at 18:48-18:50). So at 18:02, entities went from 41 (with auto-ingested from the old wiki-auto-learn.py processes still running) to 35. Then at 18:48-18:50 I cleaned up again. But then something added more to get to 45 now.\nHmm but there's no evidence of wiki-auto-learn.py processes running. Let me check - maybe the entities were added by the manual `bash wiki-learn-once.sh` that I ran at 18:50, which brought entities from 25 to 35 (adding 10). And now at 18:59 it's 45...Wait - the log shows `## [2026-04-13 18:50] wiki-learn | entities:35 | new:10`. That was the manual run at 18:50. So entities=35 at 18:50. Now at 18:59 it's 45. That's 10 more added.\n \nI'm trying to trace where those extra 10 came from. The cron at 18:02 added 10 to reach 35, then my manual run at 18:50 kept it at 35. But between 18:50 and now, something must have added another 10. Let me look at the cron schedule - it runs at :02 every hour in Asia/Shanghai, so there should've been another run at 19:02, but that would be after 18:59. Unless there's something else running that's adding these entities.\n\nActually, I need to look at the process list more carefully. The grep command with a space after \"wiki\" would've matched more than just the python processes - it would've caught the grep itself. So the 3 residual processes might not be python processes at all.","thinkingSignature":"19586e81a8b910ea6f02c7ae18c58c34660370b7b736ad43832b8448c4e1731d"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_sj3p14dkaex3_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"=== 真正在跑的相关进程 ===\"\nps aux | grep -E \"python|node|bash\" | grep -v grep | grep -v \"snap\\|systemd\" | head -15\n\necho \"\"\necho \"=== cron 下次运行 ===\"\n~/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/bin/openclaw cron list 2>/dev/null | grep -A1 \"wiki-learn\" | head -3"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":80529,"output":614,"cacheRead":18895,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":100038,"cost":{"input":0.024158699999999998,"output":0.0007368,"cacheRead":0.0011336999999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0260292}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776078050515,"responseId":"062bffe2d3f83cf90ec59ef044f5f2b9"}}
