{"type":"message","id":"d9195c03","parentId":"8ed9802a","timestamp":"2026-04-13T11:01:36.116Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Found it! Two issues:\n\n1. **openclaw-router (pid 169771)** is running AGAIN! It was killed but a NEW process started at 18:57. Someone is restarting it automatically (maybe a watchdog or systemd service).\n\n2. **entities: 45** - something keeps adding them. It could be the wiki-learn cron session is still running and adding entities.\n\nWait - `openclaw-router/context-api.js` is running at pid 169771, started at 18:57. That's AFTER I killed it at ~18:54. Something is restarting it automatically. This is suspicious.\n\nLet me check if there's a systemd service or something else managing openclaw-router.","thinkingSignature":"cf88af767de8934e7c484b82798f6f0f85555228f58d4e286ab5a805ae474fb7"},{"type":"text","text":"找到问题了：\n1. **openclaw-router (pid 169771) 自动重启**（18:57 新进程）\n2. **entities 45 个还在增加**\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_8ckzt96o4jh2_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"=== openclaw-router 谁在跑 ===\"\nps aux | grep \"openclaw-router\" | grep -v grep | awk '{print $1,$2,$3,$11,$12}'\n\necho \"\"\necho \"=== entities 45 个详情 ===\"\nauto=$(grep -l \"status: auto-ingested\" ~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/entities/*.md 2>/dev/null | wc -l)\necho \"auto-ingested: $auto\"\nls ~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/entities/ | wc -l\necho \"总计\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":81931,"output":315,"cacheRead":18895,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":101141,"cost":{"input":0.0245793,"output":0.00037799999999999997,"cacheRead":0.0011336999999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.026091}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776078086429,"responseId":"062c0005a99d8079a6330df94afb4bec"}}
