{"type":"message","id":"f2731aef","parentId":"4702a28d","timestamp":"2026-04-13T11:01:43.049Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So openclaw-router keeps restarting - likely from a cron or watchdog. Let me check the cron - maybe the isolated session is spawning it.Actually, the wiki-learn cron runs as an isolated agentTurn. It runs `~/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/wiki-learn-once.sh` as a bash command inside the isolated session. So it's not spawning openclaw-router.\n\nLet me check if there's a systemd service or startup script that's restarting openclaw-router.\n\nActually, let me check more carefully - I killed openclaw-router at ~18:54, but a new one appeared at 18:57. Let me check if there's a cron or something else that's starting it.","thinkingSignature":"80d0d2d5377c4eed3e802f9d512525fb84a64fbef206a3e74c0110b75750efb9"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ja7xv0ms4dn8_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"=== 找 openclaw-router 启动来源 ===\"\n# 检查 ps 父进程\ncat /proc/169771/status 2>/dev/null | grep PPid\n\necho \"\"\n# 检查是否是 cron/agent 启动的\nps aux | grep -E \"169771|170285\" | grep -v grep | awk '{print $1,$2,$3,$11}'\n\necho \"\"\necho \"=== cron isolated session ===\"\nls /tmp/ | grep -i openclaw 2>/dev/null\nls ~/.openclaw/sessions/isolated* 2>/dev/null | head -5"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":82324,"output":285,"cacheRead":18895,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":101504,"cost":{"input":0.0246972,"output":0.00034199999999999996,"cacheRead":0.0011336999999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0261729}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776078096227,"responseId":"062c000e9f4eae6fa8835375ba9e0b75"}}
