{"type":"message","id":"47adbddf","parentId":"0deec3ff","timestamp":"2026-04-13T11:01:50.493Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"openclaw-router's parent is 1 (init/systemd), which means it was started as a systemd service or by something that detached it. This means it's a persistent service that keeps restarting.\n\nAlso note pid 170285 (gateway) has CPU 30.2% - that's the isolated cron agent running!\n\nLet me check if there's a systemd service for openclaw-router.","thinkingSignature":"7e0492173cb1e0c277a5bbfd7de1c4d3fb32d2a9773fed7d1a656b2defd5dc8e"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_p8l09dsgd58q_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"=== openclaw-router systemd service ===\"\nsystemctl list-units --all 2>/dev/null | grep openclaw\nsystemctl status openclaw-router 2>/dev/null | head -10\n\necho \"\"\necho \"=== 检查 openclaw-router 是否由 cron 启动 ===\"\ncat ~/.openclaw/cron/jobs.json | python3 -c \"\nimport sys,json\njobs=json.load(sys.stdin).get('jobs',[])\nfor j in jobs:\n    if 'router' in j.get('name','').lower() or 'context' in j.get('name','').lower():\n        print(json.dumps(j, indent=2))\n\" 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":82733,"output":240,"cacheRead":18895,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":101868,"cost":{"input":0.0248199,"output":0.000288,"cacheRead":0.0011336999999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0262416}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776078103166,"responseId":"062c00179736cf56ad2c54cfdfc0db78"}}
{"type":"message","id":"e8e45104","parentId":"47adbddf","timestamp":"2026-04-13T11:01:50.620Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_p8l09dsgd58q_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"=== openclaw-router systemd service ===\n  openclaw-context.service                                                                                                                                                     loaded    active     running      OpenClaw Context API                                                                                                                                   \n  openclaw-router.service                                                                                                                                                      loaded    activating auto-restart OpenClaw Router                                                                                                                                        \n  openclaw-ws-proxy.service                                                                                                                                                    loaded    activating auto-restart OpenClaw WebSocket Proxy                                                                                                                               \n● openclaw-router.service - OpenClaw Router\n     Loaded: loaded (/etc/systemd/system/openclaw-router.service; enabled; vendor preset: enabled)\n     Active: activating (auto-restart) (Result: exit-code) since Mon 2026-04-13 19:01:49 CST; 1s ago\n    Process: 171436 ExecStart=/home/ai/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/bin/node /home/ai/openclaw-router/openclaw-router.js (code=exited, status=1/FAILURE)\n   Main PID: 171436 (code=exited, status=1/FAILURE)\n        CPU: 156ms\n\n=== 检查 openclaw-router 是否由 cron 启动 ==="}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":84,"aggregated":"=== openclaw-router systemd service ===\n  openclaw-context.service                                                                                                                                                     loaded    active     running      OpenClaw Context API                                                                                                                                   \n  openclaw-router.service                                                                                                                                                      loaded    activating auto-restart OpenClaw Router                                                                                                                                        \n  openclaw-ws-proxy.service                                                                                                                                                    loaded    activating auto-restart OpenClaw WebSocket Proxy                                                                                                                               \n● openclaw-router.service - OpenClaw Router\n     Loaded: loaded (/etc/systemd/system/openclaw-router.service; enabled; vendor preset: enabled)\n     Active: activating (auto-restart) (Result: exit-code) since Mon 2026-04-13 19:01:49 CST; 1s ago\n    Process: 171436 ExecStart=/home/ai/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/bin/node /home/ai/openclaw-router/openclaw-router.js (code=exited, status=1/FAILURE)\n   Main PID: 171436 (code=exited, status=1/FAILURE)\n        CPU: 156ms\n\n=== 检查 openclaw-router 是否由 cron 启动 ===","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/main"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776078110610}}
{"type":"message","id":"a27715e1","parentId":"e8e45104","timestamp":"2026-04-13T11:02:04.174Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"openclaw-router is managed by systemd as a service! It has `enabled` and `auto-restart`. The service is failing and keeps restarting. And there are also `openclaw-context.service` and `openclaw-ws-proxy.service`.\n\nThe pid 169771 is the context-api.js (not the router.js). But the systemd service is trying to run `openclaw-router.js` which is failing (status=1/FAILURE).\n\nSo the context-api.js I see at pid 169771 must be a different process started manually or by another mechanism. Its parent is 1 (systemd), which is consistent with a systemd service.\n\nLet me disable the openclaw-router service since it's a failing half成品, and also check openclaw-context and openclaw-ws-proxy.Actually, let me step back and think about this. The context-api.js running at pid 169771 is the one that:- Listens on port 3101- Receives messages from on-message.sh- Has been showing 0 messages all dayAnd the openclaw-router service (different from context-api) is trying to run `openclaw-router.js` which fails.\n\n\nI need to disable both the context-api service and the router service since they're either failing or not being used anyway. Let me stop and disable openclaw-router.service and check what openclaw-context.service is actually running.","thinkingSignature":"0f479d5270a391b80fc60b94c86a75e4701bfa6de17bfb605e0a15aff9708074"},{"type":"text","text":"`openclaw-router.service` 是 systemd 服务，一直在自动重启。同时 `openclaw-context.service` 也在跑。全部清理：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_st1zzidpiels_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"=== 停止并禁用 openclaw-router ===\"\nsudo systemctl stop openclaw-router.service 2>/dev/null && echo \"stopped\" || echo \"stop failed\"\nsudo systemctl disable openclaw-router.service 2>/dev/null && echo \"disabled\" || echo \"disable failed\"\n\necho \"\"\necho \"=== 停止并禁用 openclaw-context