{"type":"message","id":"98e5777b","parentId":"0344c3e7","timestamp":"2026-04-13T11:02:13.513Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"systemctl failed because we're not running as root in this environment. But we successfully killed the process. Let me check if there's a way to disable without sudo, or if we need to tell the user to run these commands.\n\nLet me try with the actual paths. Actually, the services failed to stop probably because of permission issues. But killing pid 169771 worked. Let me check if it restarted.\n\nAlso let me focus on the core issue: entities keeps growing because wiki-auto-learn.py keeps running. Let me find out who is spawning it.\n\nActually, looking at the process list again - there's a gateway isolated session process (pid 170285, CPU 30.2%). \n\nThat might be the cron wiki-learn session still running. The cron schedule shows \"in 1m\" with last run 59m ago, but that's only a 2-minute difference when it should be much larger if the job finished. Something's definitely wrong with how the cron is reporting its state.","thinkingSignature":"4aa7a982fa1901ac7aa9a1d2cd2a674bac08bb16a0eca6c9c4675f7333f61edd"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_zh8ahkgv2pcu_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"=== 验证 3101 端口 ===\"\nss -tlnp 2>/dev/null | grep 3101 || echo \"3101 释放 ✓\"\n\necho \"\"\necho \"=== entities 清理 ===\"\nARCHIVE=\"$HOME/.openclaw/workspace/memory/entities-archive\"\nmkdir -p \"$ARCHIVE\"\n\n# 移出所有 auto-ingested\nfor f in ~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/entities/*.md; do\n    [ -f \"$f\" ] || continue\n    if grep -q \"status: auto-ingested\" \"$f\" 2>/dev/null; then\n        mv \"$f\" \"$ARCHIVE/$(basename $f)\"\n    fi\ndone\n\necho \"清理后:\"\nls ~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/entities/ | wc -l\n\necho \"\"\necho \"=== 跑脚本验证 ===\"\nbash ~/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/wiki-learn-once.sh"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":83788,"output"