{"type":"message","id":"271a9c38","parentId":"815834fc","timestamp":"2026-04-13T11:02:23.201Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"openclaw-router is back (pid 171540 on port 3101). The systemd service keeps restarting it. I can't stop it with sudo in this environment.\n\nAnd entities is now 31 (was 25 + 6 new = 31). Within the TARGET+BUFFER=31 range. Good.\n\nLet me check if I can address the systemd services issue. Actually, the user needs to run the sudo commands themselves since this is a permission issue.\n\nBut let me also check - the wiki-learn cron \"in 1m\" but last run was \"59m ago\". That doesn't add up. Let me check the cron job state again.Wait - looking at the output again: \"in 1m 59m ago\". \n\nSo the cron shows it's scheduled for 1 minute from now but last ran 59 minutes ago, which is contradictory since it should run every hour. The cron state seems corrupted or misreported.","thinkingSignature":"5e454fbc6b3a553aaee33ea4ee56f53341ff09fbdb72029d65c9df19db3dd6b5"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_th3wptyaykne_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"=== 确认 3101 进程 ===\"\nps aux | grep \"171540\\|context-api\" | grep -v grep | awk '{print $1,$2,$11}'\n\necho \"\"\necho \"=== cron job state ===\"\n~/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/bin/openclaw cron list 2>/dev/null | grep -E \"wiki|next|last\" | head -3"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":84564,"output":299,"cacheRead":18895,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":103758,"cost":{"input":0.025369199999999998,"output":0.0003588,"cacheRead":0.0011336999999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0268617}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776078133920,"responseId":"062c003513e8a6373f1cd7cba7cc26c2"}}
