{"type":"message","id":"63a4d590","parentId":"07c8bf29","timestamp":"2026-04-13T11:02:40.455Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_20n36kyedt4o_1","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"=== 确认 3101 进程 ===\nai 171540 /home/ai/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/bin/node\n\n=== cron job state ===\nb3c6834e-c671-4b21-b6d4-0dc9c86f0e84 wiki-learn               cron 0 * * * * @ Asia/Shangha... in <1m     60m ago    ok        isolated  main       -\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"crisp-claw","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"=== 确认 3101 进程 ===\nai 171540 /home/ai/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/bin/node\n\n=== cron job state ===\nb3c6834e-c671-4b21-b6d4-0dc9c86f0e84 wiki-learn               cron 0 * * * * @ Asia/Shangha... in <1m     60m ago    ok        isolated  main       -\n","name":"echo === 确认 3101 进程 ==="},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776078160446}}
{"type":"message","id":"d9963603","parentId":"63a4d590","timestamp":"2026-04-13T11:03:10.597Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so the 3101 process keeps restarting (pid 171540 now). This is the systemd service auto-restarting. I can't stop it from this environment without sudo.\n\nThe cron \"in <1m\" but \"60m ago\" - this is the cron stagger mechanism. It says \"in <1m\" meaning less than 1 minute until next run, but the last run was 60 minutes ago. That's weird because the cron should run every hour.\n\nWait - actually looking at it again: \"in <1m 60m ago\" means \"next run in less than 1 minute, last run was 60 minutes ago\". \n\nIf it runs every hour, the next should be at 19:03 (since it ran at 18:02) which is in ~1 minute. And it last ran 60 minutes ago (at 18:02). That makes sense if the cron was initially misconfigured and didn't run at 19:02. But now it's about to run at 19:03. Let me think about this: cron \"0 * * * *\" means at minute 0 of every hour. If the stagger is 300000ms = 5 minutes, then it runs at 19:00 + random(0-5min). So it should run at 19:00-19:05. And the next one should be at 20:00-20:05. So \"in <1m\" at 19:02 is suspicious... unless the cron just fired at 19:02 (which is at minute 2, not minute 0).\n\nThe cron expression \"0 * * * *\" should fire at 19:00, but with stagger it could be 19:00-19:05. So if we're at 19:02 and it says \"in <1m\", that would mean it's scheduled for 19:03, which doesn't align with \"0 * * * *\". Maybe the system time is off or there's drift between the cron scheduler and wall clock time.\n\nActually, the staggerMs of 300000 means it fires within a 5-minute window after the hour. So if it's 19:02 and next run shows \"in <1m\", that suggests it might fire at 19:03. This could be a timezone mismatch—the cron is set for UTC but the stagger is applied in local time (CST). The previous run 60 minutes ago would be around 18:02 CST, which aligns with the expected hourly schedule offset by the stagger window.\n\nBut there's something off with the math: 19:02 minus 60 minutes is 18:02, yet if the cron runs at minute 0 every hour UTC (which is minute 50 CST), then the last run should have been at 18:50 CST, not 18:02. This discrepancy suggests either the cron isn't firing on the expected schedule or the timezone conversion is causing confusion about when things actually ran.\n\nRather than getting caught up in the timing details, I should focus on the real issues: the openclaw-router service keeps restarting and I need sudo access to stop it, the entities are currently sitting at 31 which is acceptable, and the blocklist is functioning correctly with the 15 entries I've set. Let me provide the user with a comprehensive status update.","thinkingSignature":"126d5a2c855940dd0df1b62506a1100305c412dadfd6f43ceb7bc75ba0c80323"},{"type":"text","text":"**🔴 严重发现：openclaw-router 是 systemd 服务，一直在自动重启**\n\n```\nopenclaw-router.service\n  loaded, activating (auto-restart)\n  我杀掉 pid 169771 → 新进程 pid 171540 又出现\n  需要 sudo systemctl stop+disable\n```\n\ncontext-api 也在跑（`openclaw-context.service`）。两个服务都需要 sudo 才能停止。\n\n---\n\n**评审汇报**\n\n| 问题 | 严重性 | 状态 |\n|------|--------|------|\n| openclaw-router.service (systemd) | 🔴 CRITICAL | 进程在跑，systemd 会自动重启，需 sudo |\n| openclaw-context.service (systemd) | 🔴 CRITICAL | 同上，需 sudo |\n| entities 45→31 | ✅ 已清 | 当前 31 |\n| 3101 端口 | ⚠️ 被占用 | 新进程 pid 171540 |\n| blocklist 去重 | ✅ 已修 | 15 个，无重复 |\n| context-api 死代码 | 🔴 CRITICAL | 一直 0 条消息，但因 systemd 无法停止 |\n\n**需要手动执行（需要 sudo）**\n\n```bash\nsudo systemctl stop openclaw-router.service\nsudo systemctl disable openclaw-router.service\nsudo systemctl stop openclaw-context.service\nsudo systemctl disable openclaw-context.service\n```\n\n[[reply_to_current]] 系统性审查完成。发现 systemd 服务这个深层问题——context-api 和 router 都是自动重启的服务，不是普通进程。这解释了为什么杀不掉。需要你手动执行上面的 sudo 命令。"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":85086,"output":994,"cacheRead":18895,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":104975,"cost":{"input":0.025525799999999998,"output":0.0011928,"cacheRead":0.0011336999999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0278523}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776078160460,"responseId":"062c0050a3605c6e98910a1f80688df4"}}
