{"type":"message","id":"3c42ad7f","parentId":"db242a85","timestamp":"2026-04-13T11:04:53.663Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_rh3fnxq6590x_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/bin/bash\n# Wiki Auto-Learn 单次执行脚本\n# 配合 cron 使用，每小时触发一次\n#\n# 策略：\n#   1. 只摄入新 skill（不在 entities/ 且不在 blocklist/ 中）\n#   2. blocklist 防止被删的 entity 重复摄入\n#   3. 有空间才添加，超标才 prune\n\nWORKSPACE=\"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace\"\nENTITIES=\"$WORKSPACE/memory/entities\"\nRAW=\"$WORKSPACE/memory/raw\"\nLOG=\"$WORKSPACE/memory/log.md\"\nSKILLS_DIR=\"$WORKSPACE/skills\"\nARCHIVE=\"$WORKSPACE/memory/entities-archive\"\nBLOCKLIST=\"$WORKSPACE/memory/.wiki-learn-blocklist\"  # 被删除的 skill 名列表\n\nTARGET=28\nBUFFER=3\n\nmkdir -p \"$RAW/docs\" \"$RAW/papers\" \"$RAW/notes\" \"$ARCHIVE\"\n\necho \"[$(date '+%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S')] === wiki-learn-once 启动 ===\"\n\n# ===== 辅助：计算可丢弃分数（越小越先删）=====\ndisposability_score() {\n    local f=$1\n    local score\n    if grep -q \"status: auto-ingested\" \"$f\" 2>/dev/null; then\n        score=0\n    else\n        score=500\n    fi\n    local lines=$(wc -l < \"$f\")\n    echo $((score + lines))\n}\n\n# ===== 辅助：从 blocklist 加载已删除 skill 名 =====\nload_blocklist() {\n    [ -f \"$BLOCKLIST\" ] && cat \"$BLOCKLIST\" || true\n}\n\n# ===== 辅助：添加 skill 到 blocklist（防重复）=====\nblocklist_add() {\n    local name=$1\n    # 跳过已存在的\n    grep -qFx \"$name\" \"$BLOCKLIST\" 2>/dev/null && return\n    echo \"$name\" >> \"$BLOCKLIST\"\n}\n\n# ===== 辅助：精简到目标数量（同时写 blocklist）=====\nprune_to_target() {\n    local target=$1\n    local current=$(ls \"$ENTITIES\"/*.md 2>/dev/null | wc -l)\n    local pruned=0\n\n    while [ \"$current\" -gt \"$target\" ]; do\n        local victim=$(ls \"$ENTITIES\"/*.md 2>/dev/null | while read f; do\n            echo \"$(disposability_score \"$f\") $f\"\n        done | sort -n | head -1 | cut -d' ' -f2-)\n\n        [ -z \"$victim\" ] || [ ! -f \"$victim\" ] && break\n\n        local fname=$(basename \"$victim\" .md)\n        mv \"$victim\" \"$ARCHIVE/$(basename $victim)\"\n        # 如果 skill 目录还在，加入 blocklist 防止下次重摄入\n        [ -d \"$SKILLS_DIR/$fname\" ] && blocklist_add \"$fname\"\n        echo \"  🗑  精简: $fname\"\n        pruned=$((pruned + 1))\n        current=$(ls \"$ENTITIES\"/*.md 2>/dev/null | wc -l)\n    done\n\n    [ \"$pruned\" -gt 0 ] && echo \"  🔪 精简完成: 移出 $pruned 个\"\n}\n\n# ===== 1. 加载 blocklist =====\nBLOCKED=$(load_blocklist | tr '\\n' '|')\necho \"  🚫 blocklist: ${BLOCKED:-无}\"\n\n# ===== 2. 检查空间 =====\nCURRENT=$(ls \"$ENTITIES\"/*.md 2>/dev/null | wc -l)\nAVAILABLE=$((TARGET + BUFFER - CURRENT))\necho \"  📊 当前 $CURRENT / 目标 $TARGET / 可新增 $AVAILABLE\"\n\n# ===== 3. 扫描 skills/，按空间添加（排除 blocklist）=====\nNEW_ENTITIES=0\nSKIPPED_SPACE=0\nSKIPPED_BLOCK=0\nfor skill in \"$SKILLS_DIR\"/*/; do\n    [ -d \"$skill\" ] || continue\n    name=$(basename \"$skill\")\n\n    # 已在 entities/ 中则跳过\n    [ -f \"$ENTITIES/${name}.md\" ] && continue\n\n    # 在 blocklist 中则跳过（曾被删除，不重摄入）\n    if [ -n \"$BLOCKED\" ] && echo \"$BLOCKED\" | grep -qE \"(^|)$name(|)$\"; then\n        SKIPPED_BLOCK=$((SKIPPED_BLOCK + 1))\n        continue\n    fi\n\n    # 空间不足则跳过\n    if [ \"$AVAILABLE\" -le 0 ]; then\n        SKIPPED_SPACE=$((SKIPPED_SPACE + 1))\n        continue\n    fi\n\n    cat > \"$ENTITIES/${name}.md\" << EOF\n---\ntitle: $name\ntype: skill\nstatus: auto-ingested\nlast_updated: $(date '+%Y-%m-%d')\ntags: [skill, auto]\n---\n\n# $name\n\n> 自动从 skills/ 目录摄入\n\n## 来源\n\n- 类型: skill\n- 路径: skills/$name\n- 摄入时间: $(date \"+%Y-%m-%d %H:%M\")\n\n## 相关页面\n\n- [[skills]] - 技能清单\n- [[ai-usage]] - AI 使用方式\nEOF\n    echo \"  📥 新技能实体页: $name\"\n    NEW_ENTITIES=$((NEW_ENTITIES + 1))\n    AVAILABLE=$((AVAILABLE - 1))\ndone\n\n[ \"$SKIPPED_BLOCK\" -gt 0 ] && echo \"  🚫 跳过(blocklist): $SKIPPED_BLOCK 个\"\n[ \"$SKIPPED_SPACE\" -gt 0 ] && echo \"  ⏭  跳过(空间不足): $SKIPPED_SPACE 个\"\n\n# 扫描 docs/ 作为 Raw Sources\nDOCS_COUNT=$(ls \"$WORKSPACE/docs\"/*.md 2>/dev/null | wc -l)\necho \"  📂 Raw Sources: docs/$DOCS_COUNT\"\n\n# ===== 4. Lint: 死链检查与修复 =====\nFIXED=0\nfor link in $(grep -roh '\\[\\[[a-z0-9-]*\\]\\]' \"$ENTITIES\"/*.md 2>/dev/null | sed 's/\\[\\[//;s/\\]\\]//g' | sort -u); do\n    if [ ! -f \"$ENTITIES/${link}.md\" ]; then\n        sed -i \"s/\\[\\[$link\\]\\]//g\" \"$ENTITIES\"/*.md 2>/dev/null\n        FIXED=$((FIXED + 1))\n    fi\ndone\n[ \"$FIXED\" -gt 0 ] && echo \"  🔧 修复死链: $FIXED 个\"\n\n# ===== 5. 超标清理 =====\nCURRENT=$(ls \"$ENTITIES\"/*.md 2>/dev/null | wc -l)\nif [ \"$CURRENT\" -gt $((TARGET + BUFFER)) ]; then\n    echo \"  🔪 超标清理: 当前 $CURRENT，精简到 $TARGET\"\n    prune_to_target \"$TARGET\"\nfi\n\n# ===== 6. 记录 log =====\nENTITY_COUNT=$(ls \"$ENTITIES\"/*.md 2>/dev/null | wc -l)\necho \"## [$(date '+%Y-%m-%d %H:%M')] wiki-learn | entities:$ENTITY_COUNT | new:$NEW_ENTITIES | skip(block):$SKIPPED_BLOCK | skip(space):$SKIPPED_SPACE | fixed:$FIXED\" >> \"$LOG\"\n\necho \"  ✅ entities:$ENTITY_COUNT | new:$NEW_ENTITIES\"\necho \"[$(date '+%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S')] === wiki-learn-once 完成 ===\"\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776078293653}}
{"type":"message","id":"8900e2e2","parentId":"3c42ad7f","timestamp":"2026-04-13T11:05:30.775Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"This script looks mostly good. Let me identify issues:\n\n**Issue 1**: The `disposability_score()` uses `wc -l < \"$f\"` which gives line count of the file. But the file might have been moved/deleted by another concurrent process. The script checks `[ ! -f \"$victim\" ]` which is good.\n\n**Issue 2**: `prune_to_target()` uses `sort -n` which sorts numerically. The disposability_score outputs numbers like \"0/home/...\" or \"500/home/...\". The `cut -d' ' -f2-` assumes a space separator, but if a path contains spaces, this will break. However, these are entity file paths which shouldn't have spaces. \n\nThe grep patterns in `blocklist_add()` and the grep check could be more efficient, but they work correctly for entity names without special characters.\n\nThe blocklist logic itself is sound—each pruned skill gets added to the blocklist and won't be re-ingested unless explicitly removed. The `AVAILABLE` variable correctly limits how many entities get added per run. The main concern is the line count race condition, though it's minor since `ls \"$ENTITIES\"/*.md` is checked before each deletion.\n\nThere's a subtle bug in the grep pattern: the regex `(^|)$name(|)$` should match entity names as boundaries, but `grep -qE` treats `^` and `$` as line boundaries, not string boundaries. If blocklist contains \"agent\" and I'm checking \"agent-team-orchestration\", the pattern should reject it since \"agent\" alone doesn't appear as a complete entry on either side of the separator.\n\nLooking at the actual blocklist content, entity names use underscores and hyphens, and the pattern `(^|)agent-team-orchestration(|$)` correctly matches \"agent-team-orchestration\" as a standalone token. The issue is that `$name` in the loop is just the basename of the skill directory without the `.md` extension, and if a name contains regex special characters like `+` or `.`, the grep pattern could break.\n\nThe real problem is that blocklist entries might have extensions while `$name` doesn't, so \"agent-team-orchestration\" in the blocklist won't match \"agent-team-orchestration\" from the filename. The blocklist was initialized with names that don't have extensions (like \"agent-team-orchestration\"), but the grep check fails because it's comparing a bare name against entries that may have been written with extensions by other processes. The grep pattern actually works correctly: `(^|)agent-team-orchestration(|$)` matches the line exactly as written, so blocked entries won't be re-ingested even without the `.md` extension. Now looking at the `disposability_score()` function itself, there's a `grep -q \"status: auto-ingested\"` that could potentially match content elsewhere in the file rather than just the frontmatter, though in practice this shouldn't be an issue since the entity files are well-formed.\n\nFor the blocklist regex, using `sort -u` when initializing would be cleaner than having duplicates in the file, even though `blocklist_add()` already prevents duplicates. I should also check for regex special characters in skill names that could break the grep pattern matching.\n\nLooking at `resolveSessionFile` in the session-summary handler, it returns either a Promise from `findPreviousSessionFile` or a string/null from `previousSessionFile.sessionFile`, but since the caller awaits it, this should work correctly. In `findPreviousSessionFile`, I'm reading the sessions directory to find matching session files, but there's a potential issue if the directory doesn't exist or is empty.\n\nIn the ephemeral filter, I'm checking message significance through several conditions: explicit user intent patterns, intercepted messages, fault recovery scenarios, high-risk flags, mega tasks, substantial content over 80 characters, and medium complexity with logic/duration factors of 2 or higher. The filtering logic appears sound, though I notice the `extractTextFromBlocks` function isn't actually being called anywhere.\n\nLooking at the broader context, `extractMessages` does invoke it correctly, and the global `MEANINGFUL_PATTERNS` is properly referenced. But examining the auto-score-classify hook, I see it's calling `3105/classify` which actually returns an LLM-generated response rather than a classification label—the response contains \"[LLM响应] 基于你的输入，建议操作如下：...\" so I need to verify what the actual classification result structure looks like. Looking at the scene classification flow, the `/classify` endpoint is returning a `scene` field that gets written to context.json, so the full chain is working end-to-end. The LLM response wrapper is just how the scene-classifier presents its output, but what's actually being captured is the structured classification data with the scene label.\n\nThe entity page template references `[[skills]]` as a link, but if that page doesn't exist, the lint step should catch and remove it. However, I'm noticing a potential issue with the blocklist pattern matching—using `(^|)agent-team-orchestration(|$)` with `-qE` could incorrectly match other entity names that contain the blocked name as a substring, like if \"agent-team-orchestration-foo\" existed, the grep would find it within that longer string even though it's not an exact match.\n\nFor the wiki-learn-once.sh script, the `disposability_score` function also has a problem: if the entity file gets deleted or becomes inaccessible after the initial `ls` check but before `wc -l` is called, `wc -l < \"$f\"` would fail silently and return an empty string, which would then cause `score + lines` to fail in the arithmetic context.\n\nHowever, the script does check `[ ! -f \"$victim\" ]` before processing each file, so there's already a safeguard against deleted files. The real question is whether concurrent runs could create race conditions, but given the `prune_to_target` function only runs when `CURRENT > TARGET + BUFFER`, there's enough buffer to prevent issues. The `while read f` loop in the subshell should handle filenames with spaces correctly since they're quoted, so the implementation seems sound despite some theoretical edge cases with the disposability scoring approach.\n\nLooking at the actual issues worth addressing: the grep pattern in `blocklist_add()` lacks escaping for regex special characters, the `disposability_score` could fail if the file disappears mid-calculation, and the blocklist initialization might introduce duplicates. These are worth fixing, though they're not critical failures given the current setup.","thinkingSignature":"6f78e6388619f0cb7bbc1ed308fc14e686045fb0760c18c47888395339e81bb3"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_rwpd6wkccc4w_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/ai/.openclaw/hooks/session-summary/handler.js","offset":60,"limit":40}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":86201,"output":1411,"cacheRead":18895,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":106507,"cost":{"input":0.0258603,"output":0.0016932,"cacheRead":0.0011336999999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0286872}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776078293667,"responseId":"062c00d47794a131021eb4b504919d5a"}}
{"type":"message","id":"0f145904","parentId":"8900e2e2","timestamp":"2026-04-13T11:05:30.870Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_rwpd6wkccc4w_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":" * @returns {string|null}\n */\nfunction resolveSessionFile(context, workspaceDir) {\n  const prev = context?.previousSessionEntry;\n  if (prev?.sessionFile) return prev.sessionFile;\n\n  const curr = context?.sessionEntry;\n  if (curr?.sessionFile) return curr.sessionFile;\n\n  // Webchat sessions have no .jsonl files — search sessions directory\n  if (workspaceDir) {\n    const sessionsDir = path.join(workspaceDir, 'sessions');\n    const sessionId = prev?.sessionId || curr?.sessionId;\n    return findPreviousSessionFile(prev?.sessionFile || curr?.sessionFile, sessionId, sessionsDir);\n  }\n  return null;\n}\n\n// ─── Session File Search (bundled hook compatible) ─────────────────────────────\n\n/**\n * 从 sessions 目录搜索匹配当前 session 的 .jsonl 文件。\n * 来自 bundled session-memory hook 的 findPreviousSessionFile 逻辑。\n * @param {string|undefined} currentSessionFile\n * @param {string|undefined} sessionId\n * @param {string} sessionsDir\n * @returns {Promise<string|null>}\n */\nasync function findPreviousSessionFile(currentSessionFile, sessionId, sessionsDir) {\n  try {\n    const files = await fs.promises.readdir(sessionsDir);\n    const fileSet = new Set(files);\n    // 1. reset 文件匹配\n    if (currentSessionFile) {\n      const base = path.basename(currentSessionFile).replace(/\\.reset\\..+$/, '');\n      if (fileSet.has(base)) return path.join(sessionsDir, base);\n    }\n    // 2. sessionId.jsonl 精确匹配\n    if (sessionId?.trim()) {\n      const canonical = `${sessionId.trim()}.jsonl`;\n\n[491 more lines in file. Use offset=100 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776078330852}}
{"type":"message","id":"ad88346a","parentId":"0f145904","timestamp":"2026-04-13T11:05:52.672Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The session-summary handler.js looks okay. Let me check the auto-score-classify handler for the ephemeral filter.","thinkingSignature":"ba33d704ed7c92765b584e874af1b8dcef26e7e69895c7e837d7d56ed3308f60"},{"type":"text","text":"**代码审查结果**\n\n---\n\n## wiki-learn-once.sh\n\n**🔴 严重问题：无**\n\n**🟡 中等问题**\n\n**1. `disposability_score()` 文件存在性竞态**\n```bash\nvictim=$(ls \"$ENTITIES\"/*.md ... | ... | cut -d' ' -f2-)\n[ -z \"$victim\" ] || [ ! -f \"$victim\" ] && break\nmv \"$victim\" \"$ARCHIVE/...\"\n```\n两次文件操作之间另一个进程可能删除了文件。但实际上已有 `[ ! -f \"$victim\" ]` 保护，影响小。\n\n**2. `blocklist_add()` 无 regex 转义**\n```bash\ngrep -qFx \"$name\"   # ← $name 若含 |.+*? 等regex元字符会误匹配\n```\nSkill 名称目前无特殊字符，暂可接受。\n\n**🟢 低优先级**\n- `load_blocklist()` 未去重，`sort -u` 初始化可替代\n- `DOCS_COUNT` 只计文件数，从不用于后续逻辑（死代码）\n\n---\n\n## session-summary/handler.js\n\n**🟢 轻微问题**\n\n**1. `extractTextFromBlocks` 定义但从未调用**\n```javascript\nfunction extractTextFromBlocks(content) { ... }  // 第72-89行\n```\n`extractMessages` 内部调用它，函数本身被使用，但不是\"死代码\"——这个没问题。\n\n**2. `resolveSessionFile` 的 JSDoc 说返回 `string|null`，但实际返回 `string|Promise<string|null>`**\n```javascript\n* @returns {string|null}\nfunction resolveSessionFile(context, workspaceDir) {\n  ...\n  return findPreviousSessionFile(...) if (workspaceDir)  // ← 返回 Promise\n}\n```\n类型声明错误，但 `await` 能正确处理。\n\n---\n\n## auto-score-classify/handler.js\n\n**🔴 无严重问题**\n\n**🟡 中等问题**\n\n**1. `extractTextFromBlocks` 未使用**\n同 session-summary，这是真实死代码——内联实现了相同逻辑但不用它。\n\n**2. `MEANINGFUL_PATTERNS` 全局常量在函数之后才定义（hoisting 没问题，但顺序混乱）**\n\n---\n\n## 总体评价\n\n| 文件 | 评分 | 主要问题 |\n|------|------|----------|\n| wiki-learn-once.sh | 🟡 及格 | regex 元字符未转义；竞态有保护但理论上存在 |\n| session-summary/handler.js | 🟢 良好 | JSDoc 类型错误，无实际影响 |\n| auto-score-classify/handler.js | 🟡 及格 | 死代码片段，顺序混乱 |\n\n最需修复的是 `blocklist_add()` 的 regex 转义：\n```bash\nblocklist_add() {\n    local name=$(printf '%s' \"$1\" | sed 's/[[.*+?^$]/\\\\&/g')\n    grep -qFx -- \"$name\" \"$BLOCKLIST\" 2>/dev/null && return\n    echo \"$name\" >> \"$BLOCKLIST\"\n}\n```\n\n要修吗？"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":88009,"output":677,"cacheRead":18895,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":107581,"cost":{"input":0.026402699999999998,"output":0.0008124,"cacheRead":0.0011336999999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0283488}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776078330875,"responseId":"062c00faed26be8807a2e22ec1061abe"}}
