{"type":"message","id":"9e1c59d2","parentId":"51f92a08","timestamp":"2026-04-13T11:36:07.324Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, I notice `load_blocklist()` now does `sort -u` on every call. But since `sort -u` modifies the file in-place, this could cause issues if the file is being read while sorted. Also, `sort -u` writes to stdout, not in-place... Actually `sort -u file` does output to stdout, not in-place. Let me check.\n\nActually `sort -u file` outputs sorted+unique content to stdout. It doesn't modify the file in-place. So `[ -f \"$BLOCKLIST\" ] && sort -u \"$BLOCKLIST\" || true` outputs the sorted content to stdout, which is then used in the `BLOCKED=$(...)` command substitution. This is fine.","thinkingSignature":"b6326c45f42946da6880c6f74e4606e9b0a74b97a843cdab0b1fdb740cead5a1"},{"type":"text","text":"修复完成：\n\n| 文件 | 修复内容 |\n|------|----------|\n| wiki-learn-once.sh | `load_blocklist()` 加 `sort -u` 去重；`blocklist_add()` 加 `--` 分隔符 |\n| session-summary | JSDoc `@returns` 改为 `string\\|Promise<string\\|null>` |\n\n[[reply_to_current]] 2 个代码问题已修复。剩余无实际影响的均为已知局限，不动。"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":91185,"output":246,"cacheRead":18895,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":110326,"cost":{"input":0.027355499999999998,"output":0.00029519999999999997,"cacheRead":0.0011336999999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.028784399999999998}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776080160184,"responseId":"062c081ef06653654cd626ae7da9a100"}}
