{"type":"message","id":"fab6381d","parentId":"e855d2f5","timestamp":"2026-04-13T11:51:38.083Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So the handler writes the raw result from 3105 directly as `classification`. What does 3105 actually return?\n\n```json\n{\n  \"response\": \"[LLM响应] 基于你的输入，建议操作如下：...\",\n  \"intercepted\": false,\n  \"scene\": \"clarify\",\n  \"meta\": \"ambiguous\",\n  \"confidence\": 0.5324\n}\n```\n\nSo `context.json` ends up with:\n```json\n{\n  \"classification\": {\n    \"response\": \"...\",\n    \"intercepted\": false,\n    \"scene\": \"clarify\",\n    \"meta\": \"ambiguous\",\n    \"confidence\": 0.5324\n  },\n  \"scoring\": { ... },\n  \"timestamp\": \"...\",\n  \"messagePreview\": \"...\"\n}\n```\n\nBut the HOOK.md shows `label`, `top_candidates`, etc. from the old 3104 format. This is a documentation bug. And the `isMeaningful` function only checks `c.intercepted === true` and `c.scene === 'fault_recovery'`, not the old fields. So the handler IS correctly adapted to the 3105 format, but HOOK.md's example is completely wrong and shows the old 3104 format.","thinkingSignature":"4862a4627f5c14c9274a11052d485fb47ec299cbe6c3dea7a3ea99686bc55633"},{"type":"text","text":"HOOK.md 示例用的是旧 3104 格式，和实际写入的 3105 格式完全不同。修：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_bzryrtlxa8fq_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"sed -n '23,45p' ~/.openclaw/hooks/auto-score-classify/HOOK.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":50810,"output":332,"cacheRead":18895,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":70037,"cost":{"input":0.015243,"output":0.0003984,"cacheRead":0.0011336999999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0167751}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776081090481,"responseId":"062c0bc13c8c78aa7b24d870e8f5f557"}}
