{"type":"message","id":"94f32c61","parentId":"dd3c21e1","timestamp":"2026-04-13T11:51:55.954Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_i4h0bmvsz6oh_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"=== wiki-learn-once.sh 完整逻辑审查 ===\n#!/bin/bash\n# Wiki Auto-Learn 单次执行脚本\n# 配合 cron 使用，每小时触发一次\n#\n# 策略：\n#   1. 只摄入新 skill（不在 entities/ 且不在 blocklist/ 中）\n#   2. blocklist 防止被删的 entity 重复摄入\n#   3. 有空间才添加，超标才 prune\n\nWORKSPACE=\"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace\"\nENTITIES=\"$WORKSPACE/memory/entities\"\nRAW=\"$WORKSPACE/memory/raw\"\nLOG=\"$WORKSPACE/memory/log.md\"\nSKILLS_DIR=\"$WORKSPACE/skills\"\nARCHIVE=\"$WORKSPACE/memory/entities-archive\"\nBLOCKLIST=\"$WORKSPACE/memory/.wiki-learn-blocklist\"  # 被删除的 skill 名列表\n\nTARGET=28\nBUFFER=3\n\nmkdir -p \"$RAW/docs\" \"$RAW/papers\" \"$RAW/notes\" \"$ARCHIVE\"\n\necho \"[$(date '+%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S')] === wiki-learn-once 启动 ===\"\n\n# ===== 辅助：计算可丢弃分数（越小越先删）=====\ndisposability_score() {\n    local f=$1\n    local score\n    if grep -q \"status: auto-ingested\" \"$f\" 2>/dev/null; then\n        score=0\n    else\n        score=500\n    fi\n    local lines=$(wc -l < \"$f\")\n    echo $((score + lines))"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":50,"aggregated":"=== wiki-learn-once.sh 完整逻辑审查 ===\n#!/bin/bash\n# Wiki Auto-Learn 单次执行脚本\n# 配合 cron 使用，每小时触发一次\n#\n# 策略：\n#   1. 只摄入新 skill（不在 entities/ 且不在 blocklist/ 中）\n#   2. blocklist 防止被删的 entity 重复摄入\n#   3. 有空间才添加，超标才 prune\n\nWORKSPACE=\"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace\"\nENTITIES=\"$WORKSPACE/memory/entities\"\nRAW=\"$WORKSPACE/memory/raw\"\nLOG=\"$WORKSPACE/memory/log.md\"\nSKILLS_DIR=\"$WORKSPACE/skills\"\nARCHIVE=\"$WORKSPACE/memory/entities-archive\"\nBLOCKLIST=\"$WORKSPACE/memory/.wiki-learn-blocklist\"  # 被删除的 skill 名列表\n\nTARGET=28\nBUFFER=3\n\nmkdir -p \"$RAW/docs\" \"$RAW/papers\" \"$RAW/notes\" \"$ARCHIVE\"\n\necho \"[$(date '+%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S')] === wiki-learn-once 启动 ===\"\n\n# ===== 辅助：计算可丢弃分数（越小越先删）=====\ndisposability_score() {\n    local f=$1\n    local score\n    if grep -q \"status: auto-ingested\" \"$f\" 2>/dev/null; then\n        score=0\n    else\n        score=500\n    fi\n    local lines=$(wc -l < \"$f\")\n    echo $((score + lines))","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/main"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776081115948}}
{"type":"message","id":"492b4541","parentId":"94f32c61","timestamp":"2026-04-13T11:52:10.537Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, there's a subtle bug here. The `disposability_score` function has a logic issue:```bash\nif grep -q \"status: auto-ingested\" \"$f\" 2>/dev/null; then\n    score=0\nelse\n    score=500\nfi\nlocal lines=$(wc -l < \"$f\")\necho $((score + lines))\n```\n\nThis means:\n- auto-ingested files: score = 0 + lines\n- manual files: score = 500 + lines\n\nBut manual files could be very short (like `user.md` or `framework.md` which have very few lines), while auto-ingested files are longer. \n\nThe formula `0 + lines` for auto-ingested vs `500 + lines` for manual means auto-ingested files always have lower scores regardless of content length, so they get prioritized for deletion. But manual files with high line counts could easily exceed auto-ingested ones, making this comparison unreliable for determining which files should actually be removed.\n\nThe real question is whether this scoring system aligns with the stated goal of removing auto-ingested files first while preserving manual ones. If a manual file has 400 lines and an auto-ingested file has 100, the auto-ingested file still wins with a score of 100 versus 900, which happens to be correct—but the logic is fragile because it depends entirely on the line count difference rather than a principled ranking.\n\nThe bigger problem is that the function adds the auto-ingested flag to the score but doesn't account for whether the file was actually created by the wiki-learn process. If a manual file has 600 lines and an auto-ingested one has 100, the auto-ingested file gets removed first as intended. But if the system generates many short auto-ingested files, they could all cluster around similar scores, making the deletion order less predictable.\n\nI'm realizing there's a more fundamental issue: the script is using the `SKILLS_DIR` variable, but I need to trace where that's actually pointing to understand which directory it's monitoring for changes.","thinkingSignature":"d9e5348d92be9c47db56cbe11437eb89c3c15b6ae1c31281c0061cbc3fdf00c1"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_4m7i5pdl8cig_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"=== SKILLS_DIR 指向哪里？===$SKILLS_DIR\"\necho \"--- 实际 ---\"\nls -la ~/.openclaw/skills/ 2>/dev/null | head -5\necho \"\"\necho \"--- workspace/skills ---\"\nls -la ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/ 2>/dev/null | head -5\necho \"\"\necho \"=== cron job 实际执行的目录 ===\"\nps aux | grep wiki-learn-once | grep -v grep | head -3"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":52745,"output":545,"cacheRead":18895,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":72185,"cost":{"input":0.0158235,"output":0.000654,"cacheRead":0.0011336999999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0176112}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776081115956,"responseId":"062c0bdbf569aad58e7ffcaea4acec24"}}
