{"type":"message","id":"390176f4","parentId":"3ad26f3f","timestamp":"2026-04-13T11:52:18.816Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"SKILLS_DIR is set to `/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/skills`. But when the cron job runs in an isolated session, it should inherit the HOME variable. The script hardcodes `WORKSPACE=\"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace\"` - not using $HOME.\n\nSo the script uses:\n- `WORKSPACE=\"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace\"` (hardcoded, not using HOME)\n- `SKILLS_DIR=\"$WORKSPACE/skills\"` → `/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/skills`\n\nThis is fine since HOME=/home/ai in this environment. But wait, the script also accesses `~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/entities`. \n\nSince the workspace path is hardcoded rather than derived from an environment variable, it should remain consistent across sessions. Now I need to examine the wiki-learn-once.sh script to see how it's actually consuming skills and processing them.","thinkingSignature":"9412c2d082fd3e7a6a5ad612d702a8f845577615bb2f20cc386ce92e1056833d"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_pethfe6hdmmt_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"=== wiki-learn-once.sh 新增 skill 逻辑 ===\"\nsed -n '70,105p' ~/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/wiki-learn-once.sh"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":53515,"output":247,"cacheRead":18895,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":72657,"cost":{"input":0.0160545,"output":0.0002964,"cacheRead":0.0011336999999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0174846}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776081130633,"responseId":"062c0beae5d6513446add80323b3239e"}}
{"type":"message","id":"b2087d27","parentId":"390176f4","timestamp":"2026-04-13T11:52:18.926Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_pethfe6hdmmt_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"=== wiki-learn-once.sh 新增 skill 逻辑 ===\n        current=$(ls \"$ENTITIES\"/*.md 2>/dev/null | wc -l)\n    done\n\n    [ \"$pruned\" -gt 0 ] && echo \"  🔪 精简完成: 移出 $pruned 个\"\n}\n\n# ===== 1. 加载 blocklist =====\nBLOCKED=$(load_blocklist | tr '\\n' '|')\necho \"  🚫 blocklist: ${BLOCKED:-无}\"\n\n# ===== 2. 检查空间 =====\nCURRENT=$(ls \"$ENTITIES\"/*.md 2>/dev/null | wc -l)\nAVAILABLE=$((TARGET + BUFFER - CURRENT))\necho \"  📊 当前 $CURRENT / 目标 $TARGET / 可新增 $AVAILABLE\"\n\n# ===== 3. 扫描 skills/，按空间添加（排除 blocklist）=====\nNEW_ENTITIES=0\nSKIPPED_SPACE=0\nSKIPPED_BLOCK=0\nfor skill in \"$SKILLS_DIR\"/*/; do\n    [ -d \"$skill\" ] || continue\n    name=$(basename \"$skill\")\n\n    # 已在 entities/ 中则跳过\n    [ -f \"$ENTITIES/${name}.md\" ] && continue\n\n    # 在 blocklist 中则跳过（曾被删除，不重摄入）\n    if [ -n \"$BLOCKED\" ] && echo \"$BLOCKED\" | grep -qE \"(^|)$name(|)$\"; then\n        SKIPPED_BLOCK=$((SKIPPED_BLOCK + 1))\n        continue\n    fi\n\n    # 空间不足则跳过\n    if [ \"$AVAILABLE\" -le 0 ]; then\n        SKIPPED_SPACE=$((SKIPPED_SPACE + 1))\n        continue"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":65,"aggregated":"=== wiki-learn-once.sh 新增 skill 逻辑 ===\n        current=$(ls \"$ENTITIES\"/*.md 2>/dev/null | wc -l)\n    done\n\n    [ \"$pruned\" -gt 0 ] && echo \"  🔪 精简完成: 移出 $pruned 个\"\n}\n\n# ===== 1. 加载 blocklist =====\nBLOCKED=$(load_blocklist | tr '\\n' '|')\necho \"  🚫 blocklist: ${BLOCKED:-无}\"\n\n# ===== 2. 检查空间 =====\nCURRENT=$(ls \"$ENTITIES\"/*.md 2>/dev/null | wc -l)\nAVAILABLE=$((TARGET + BUFFER - CURRENT))\necho \"  📊 当前 $CURRENT / 目标 $TARGET / 可新增 $AVAILABLE\"\n\n# ===== 3. 扫描 skills/，按空间添加（排除 blocklist）=====\nNEW_ENTITIES=0\nSKIPPED_SPACE=0\nSKIPPED_BLOCK=0\nfor skill in \"$SKILLS_DIR\"/*/; do\n    [ -d \"$skill\" ] || continue\n    name=$(basename \"$skill\")\n\n    # 已在 entities/ 中则跳过\n    [ -f \"$ENTITIES/${name}.md\" ] && continue\n\n    # 在 blocklist 中则跳过（曾被删除，不重摄入）\n    if [ -n \"$BLOCKED\" ] && echo \"$BLOCKED\" | grep -qE \"(^|)$name(|)$\"; then\n        SKIPPED_BLOCK=$((SKIPPED_BLOCK + 1))\n        continue\n    fi\n\n    # 空间不足则跳过\n    if [ \"$AVAILABLE\" -le 0 ]; then\n        SKIPPED_SPACE=$((SKIPPED_SPACE + 1))\n        continue","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/main"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776081138918}}
{"type":"message","id":"701148d9","parentId":"b2087d27","timestamp":"2026-04-13T11:52:46.721Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see a bug in the blocklist check:\n```bash\nif [ -n \"$BLOCKED\" ] && echo \"$BLOCKED\" | grep -qE \"(^|)$name(|)$\"; then\n```This is using `grep -qE` with a dynamic pattern built from the blocklist. But the blocklist contains skill names separated by `|`. If a skill name contains regex special characters, this will break. But we already fixed `blocklist_add` to escape. However, when loading the blocklist with `sort -u`, the names aren't escaped. So if `agent-team-orchestration` is in the blocklist, and we have a skill named `agent`, the pattern `(^|)agent(|)$` would match \"agent\" but also potentially \"agent-team-orchestration\" (if grep finds it at position 0 or after a `|`).Actually wait:\n\n\n```bash\nBLOCKED=$(load_blocklist | tr '\\n' '|')  # e.g. \"a|b|c|\"\necho \"$BLOCKED\" | grep -qE \"(^|)$name(|)$\"\n```\n\nFor `name=\"agent\"`, BLOCKED=\"agent-team-orchestration|claude-code-40-tools-complete-report|...\", the pattern `(^|)agent(|)$` would match \"agent\" at the start of the string since `^` allows a match there, but it wouldn't match within \"agent-team\" because the hyphen breaks the boundary. So the pattern itself is sound for exact matching.\n\nNow I'm realizing the real problem: `agent-team-orchestration` would contain \"agent\" as a substring, and with the alternation `(^|)agent(|)`, the regex engine would find \"agent\" at position 0 and treat it as a valid match even though the full string is \"agent-team-orchestration\". This means any skill name that's a substring of a blocklisted skill would incorrectly get filtered out. The pattern `(^|)agent(|)` matches \"agent\" at position 0, but then `$` requires the end of string to follow immediately, which doesn't work—\"agent-team-...\" continues with a hyphen. However, if `grep -qE` with `$` anchored to the end of \"agent\" could match position 0 where \"agent\" is followed by `$`, that would only succeed if the string is exactly \"agent\" with nothing after it.\n\nBut wait, I need to reconsider the actual regex behavior here. The alternation `(^|)agent(|)` tries both `^agent` and `agent$` at position 0. The second alternative `agent$` would match if \"agent\" at position 0 is also at the end of the string. So for the input \"agent-team-orchestration\", `grep -E` would search for any line containing this pattern and find \"agent\" embedded within the larger string, not as a standalone token.\n\nThe fundamental problem is that `grep -E` searches for substrings, not exact matches. To properly validate that a skill name isn't in the blocklist, I'd need to escape the blocked names and use word boundaries, or split them into an array and check each one individually rather than building a regex from them.","thinkingSignature":"c8ac488076dde84f8ed2117ed53ea6a022c099a7c90e1dd5acbe3402ec04f9a1"},{"type":"text","text":"**发现严重 bug：blocklist grep 是子串匹配，不是精确匹配**\n\n```bash\nBLOCKED=\"agent-team-orchestration|...\"\ngrep -qE \"(^|)$name(|)$\"  # \"agent\" 会匹配到 \"agent-team-orchestration\" 中的 \"agent\"\n```\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_1lm9bfj3xwly_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/wiki-learn-once.sh","edits":[{"oldText":"# ===== 1. 加载 blocklist =====\nBLOCKED=$(load_blocklist | tr '\\n' '|')\necho \"  🚫 blocklist: ${BLOCKED:-无}\"","newText":"# ===== 1. 加载 blocklist（精确匹配，用数组避免子串误匹配）=====\nBLOCKED_NAMES=($(load_blocklist))\necho \"  🚫 blocklist: ${BLOCKED_NAMES[*]:-无}\""},{"oldText":"    # 在 blocklist 中则跳过（曾被删除，不重摄入）\n    if [ -n \"$BLOCKED\" ] && echo \"$BLOCKED\" | grep -qE \"(^|)$name(|)$\"; then\n        SKIPPED_BLOCK=$((SKIPPED_BLOCK + 1))\n        continue\n    fi","newText":"    # 在 blocklist 中则跳过（曾被删除，不重摄入，精确匹配）\n    is_blocked=false\n    for blocked in \"${BLOCKED_NAMES[@]}\"; do\n        [ \"$name\" = \"$blocked\" ] && is_blocked=true && break\n    done\n    if $is_blocked; then\n        SKIPPED_BLOCK=$((SKIPPED_BLOCK + 1))\n        continue\n    fi"}]}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":54147,"output":1059,"cacheRead":18895,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":74101,"cost":{"input":0.0162441,"output":0.0012707999999999999,"cacheRead":0.0011336999999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0186486}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776081138930,"responseId":"062c0bf2bbccc5aa5a163a36c38112f0"}}
