{"type":"message","id":"59165dca","parentId":"ee01d72e","timestamp":"2026-04-13T11:53:20.665Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me check the task_orchestrator's context_protector.js to see how context.json is read.","thinkingSignature":"83daa7ef1c0313de19028812d0297e4ed3f6f24add03525489a4b87b9d5967fc"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_inugb3guz62f_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"=== context_protector 读取 context.json ===\"\ncat ~/.openclaw/skills/task_orchestrator/context_protector.js | head -40\n\necho \"\"\necho \"=== session-status 工具读取的内容 ===\"\ngrep -rn \"session_status\\|SessionStatus\" ~/.openclaw --include=\"*.js\" 2>/dev/null | grep -v node_modules | grep -v \"test\\|spec\" | head -10"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":57820,"output":133,"cacheRead":18895,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":76848,"cost":{"input":0.017346,"output":0.0001596,"cacheRead":0.0011336999999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0186393}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776081195876,"responseId":"062c0c2a2b629041cb319969883f611f"}}
{"type":"message","id":"f39f8d61","parentId":"59165dca","timestamp":"2026-04-13T11:53:20.842Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_inugb3guz62f_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"=== context_protector 读取 context.json ===\n// context_protector.js\nconst fs = require('fs').promises;\nconst path = require('path');\nconst STORAGE = path.join(process.env.HOME, '.openclaw', 'context.json');\n\nclass ContextProtector {\n constructor() { this.messages = []; this.totalChars = 0; this.totalTokens = 0; this.lastSummarize = 0; this.load(); }\n async load() { try { const d = JSON.parse(await fs.readFile(STORAGE)); Object.assign(this, d); } catch(e) {} }\n async save() { await fs.writeFile(STORAGE, JSON.stringify({ messages: this.messages.slice(-200), totalChars: this.totalChars, totalTokens: this.totalTokens, lastSummarize: this.lastSummarize })); }\n estimateTokens(t) { const ch = (t.match(/[\\u4e00-\\u9fa5]/g)||[]).length; return Math.ceil(ch/1.5 + (t.length-ch)/4); }\n async addMessage(role, content, taskId) {\n const tokens = this.estimateTokens(content);\n this.messages.push({ role, content, timestamp: Date.now(), taskId, tokens });\n this.totalChars += content.length; this.totalTokens += tokens;\n if (this.messages.length > 50 && Date.now() - this.lastSummarize > 120000) await this.summarize();\n await this.save();\n }\n async summarize() {\n const old = this.messages.slice(0, -10);\n const summary = `[Auto] ${old.length} msgs: ${old.map(m=>m.content.slice(0,30)).join('; ')}`;\n this.messages = [{ role:'system', content:`Summarized at ${new Date().toISOString()}: ${summary}`, tokens:0 }, ...this.messages.slice(-10)];\n this.totalChars = this.messages.reduce((s,m)=>s+(m.content?.length||0),0);\n this.totalTokens = this.messages.reduce((s,m)=>s+(m.tokens||0),0);\n this.lastSummarize = Date.now();\n console.log('[Context] Summarized', old.length);\n }\n}\n\nmodule.exports = new ContextProtector();\n=== session-status 工具读取的内容 ==="}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":141,"aggregated":"=== context_protector 读取 context.json ===\n// context_protector.js\nconst fs = require('fs').promises;\nconst path = require('path');\nconst STORAGE = path.join(process.env.HOME, '.openclaw', 'context.json');\n\nclass ContextProtector {\n constructor() { this.messages = []; this.totalChars = 0; this.totalTokens = 0; this.lastSummarize = 0; this.load(); }\n async load() { try { const d = JSON.parse(await fs.readFile(STORAGE)); Object.assign(this, d); } catch(e) {} }\n async save() { await fs.writeFile(STORAGE, JSON.stringify({ messages: this.messages.slice(-200), totalChars: this.totalChars, totalTokens: this.totalTokens, lastSummarize: this.lastSummarize })); }\n estimateTokens(t) { const ch = (t.match(/[\\u4e00-\\u9fa5]/g)||[]).length; return Math.ceil(ch/1.5 + (t.length-ch)/4); }\n async addMessage(role, content, taskId) {\n const tokens = this.estimateTokens(content);\n this.messages.push({ role, content, timestamp: Date.now(), taskId, tokens });\n this.totalChars += content.length; this.totalTokens += tokens;\n if (this.messages.length > 50 && Date.now() - this.lastSummarize > 120000) await this.summarize();\n await this.save();\n }\n async summarize() {\n const old = this.messages.slice(0, -10);\n const summary = `[Auto] ${old.length} msgs: ${old.map(m=>m.content.slice(0,30)).join('; ')}`;\n this.messages = [{ role:'system', content:`Summarized at ${new Date().toISOString()}: ${summary}`, tokens:0 }, ...this.messages.slice(-10)];\n this.totalChars = this.messages.reduce((s,m)=>s+(m.content?.length||0),0);\n this.totalTokens = this.messages.reduce((s,m)=>s+(m.tokens||0),0);\n this.lastSummarize = Date.now();\n console.log('[Context] Summarized', old.length);\n }\n}\n\nmodule.exports = new ContextProtector();\n=== session-status 工具读取的内容 ===","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/main"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776081200836}}
{"type":"message","id":"91b50ff8","parentId":"f39f8d61","timestamp":"2026-04-13T11:53:28.404Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The context_protector.js reads from `~/.openclaw/context.json` (not session-specific), which is a completely different file from the session-scoped `context.json` that auto-score-classify writes to `~/.openclaw/sessions/{sessionKey}/context.json`.\n\nThis is a design issue: there are two different context.json files:\n1. `~/.openclaw/context.json` - used by task_orchestrator/context_protector\n2. `~/.openclaw/sessions/{sessionKey}/context.json` - written by auto-score-classify hook\n\nLet me check what `~/.openclaw/context.json` currently contains and how it's structured.","thinkingSignature":"a9ff209432f1c9372900403d6060ca3fd9bfbe6d45bc1009d65f1accfa18c8d7"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_aoe74g4o8917_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"=== ~/.openclaw/context.json（task_orchestrator用）===\"\ncat ~/.openclaw/context.json 2>/dev/null | python3 -m json.tool 2>/dev/null | head -30\n\necho \"\"\necho \"=== sessions/ context.json（auto-score-classify写）===\"\nls ~/.openclaw/sessions/ 2>/dev/null | head -5\ncat ~/.openclaw/sessions/main*/context.json 2>/dev/null | python3 -m json.tool 2>/dev/null | head -30"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":58433,"output":266,"cacheRead":18895,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":77594,"cost":{"input":0.017529899999999998,"output":0.0003192,"cacheRead":0.0011336999999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.018982799999999998}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776081200844,"responseId":"062c0c2fe4351c2214f2c15656bb4948"}}
{"type":"message","id":"92fe4c48","parentId":"91b50ff8","timestamp":"2026-04-13T11:53:28.507Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_aoe74g4o8917_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"=== ~/.openclaw/context.json（task_orchestrator用）===\n\n=== sessions/ context.json（auto-score-classify写）===\nagent:fast_agent:main\nagent:main:main"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":67,"aggregated":"=== ~/.openclaw/context.json（task_orchestrator用）===\n\n=== sessions/ context.json（auto-score-classify写）===\nagent:fast_agent:main\nagent:main:main","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/main"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776081208501}}
{"type":"message","id":"77ab93a9","parentId":"92fe4c48","timestamp":"2026-04-13T11:53:39.182Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting - there's no `~/.openclaw/context.json` (task orchestrator's context), but there's `~/.openclaw/sessions/` directory with session-specific context.json files. And the `agent:fast_agent:main` and `agent:main:main` seem to be session directory names.\n\nSo there are two separate context systems:\n1. `~/.openclaw/sessions/{session}/context.json` - written by auto-score-classify hook, read by the agent via session context injection\n2. `~/.openclaw/context.json` - used by task_orchestrator's context_protector, which is a separate module\n\nThese are different files with different purposes. The auto-score-classify hook writes to the sessions directory, not to `~/.openclaw/context.json`. \n\nLooking at the session directories more carefully, they follow the pattern `agent:fast_agent:main` and `agent:main:main`, which appear to be structured as `{agentId}:{agentType}:{index}`. The auto-score-classify hook targets `~/.openclaw/sessions/{sessionKey}/context.json` where `sessionKey` comes from the event, but this raises the question of whether task_orchestrator is actually reading from the right context file.\n\nThe two context systems seem to be operating independently: auto-score-classify writes to `~/.openclaw/sessions/{sessionKey}/context.json` while task_orchestrator reads from `~/.openclaw/context.json`, and they're not necessarily synchronized. If the hook writes to the session-scoped context but the task orchestrator expects the root-level context file, there's a potential disconnect in what each component is actually using.\n\nI should move on to examining the ephemeral system since this context file alignment issue might be a red herring.","thinkingSignature":"b9678982ebc669581bdadab61bfedca2e8d7d87b39f0b3852ca5da7500d84672"},{"type":"text","text":"---\n\n## 第5轮：ephemeral + bootstrap 链路验证\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_3s3jhmqlng32_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"=== ephemeral 目录和今日文件 ===\"\nls -la ~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/ephemeral/ 2>/dev/null\n\necho \"\"\necho \"=== bootstrap hook 是否实际注入摘要 ===\"\ngrep -n \"summary\\|SUMMARY\\|session-summary\" ~/.openclaw/hooks/handler.js | head -10"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":58751,"output":459,"cacheRead":18895,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":78105,"cost":{"input":0.0176253,"output":0.0005507999999999999,"cacheRead":0.0011336999999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.019309800000000002}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776081208508,"responseId":"062c0c36feb0a7e74613c0153fa40b46"}}
